 Reform in\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n(Week 15)\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n\\r\\nOn-Site Learning Materials\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Visual Presentation (PowerPoint, Graphic Organizers, Whiteboard, etc.)\\r\\n- Lecture Notes and Handouts\\r\\n- Timeline of Agrarian Reform in the Philippines\\r\\n- Workbook (Readings in Philippine History, pages 204\\u2013208)\\r\\n- Online Sources\\r\\nOff-Site Learning Materials\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning Management System (LMS)\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-Site Requirements\\r\\n- Workbook Answers (compiled in portfolio)\\r\\n- Group Presentation (evaluated using rubric)\\r\\n- Quiz Results\\r\\n- Rubric Result\\r\\n- Notes\\r\\n- Assignment\\r\\nOff-Site Requirements\\r\\n- Learning Management System (LMS) \\u2013 Compile all downloaded materials for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 16\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSocial, Political, Economic, and Cultural Issues in Philippine History\\r\\n- Taxation\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nCMO-Based Outcomes\\r\\n- Effectively communicate historical analysis of a particular event or issue using various techniques and genres to help others understand the chosen topic\\r\\n- Propose recommendations or solutions to present-day problems based on an understanding of root causes and anticipation of future scenarios\\r\\n- Display the ability to work in a multi-disciplinary team and contribute meaningfully to a group endeavor\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Workbook: Answer page 223\\r\\n2. Teacher-made quiz\\r\\n3. Rubric for activity OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n1. Complete the Week 16 assignment\\r\\nuploaded in your Learning\\r\\nManagement System (LMS). Once\\r\\naccomplished, download and print a\\r\\ncopy, then submit it during the next\\r\\nface-to-face class.,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. The class will be divided into six\\r\\ngroups, and they will present the\\r\\nevolution of Agrarian Reform in the\\r\\ncountry through the different period:\\r\\n1.1. Pre-colonial\\r\\n1.2. Spanish Era\\r\\n1.3. American Era\\r\\n1.4. Commonwealth and Japanese\\r\\nOccupation\\r\\n1.5. Post-war\\r\\n1.6. Martial Law Era\\r\\n1.7. Post-Martial Law\\r\\n1.8. Train Law\\r\\n2. Conduct interview among vendors,\\r\\nstudents, family provider, and others\\r\\nto answer the workbook activity in\\r\\npage 224. The result of the interview\\r\\nwill be made into a docu-vlog. OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n(Weel 16)\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-Site Learning Materials\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Visual Presentation (PowerPoint, Graphic Organizers, Whiteboard, etc.)\\r\\n- Lecture Notes and Handouts\\r\\n- Timeline of Taxation in the Philippines\\r\\n- Workbook (Readings in Philippine History, pages 211\\u2013222)\\r\\n- Online Sources\\r\\nOff-Site Learning Materials\\r\\n- Learning Management System (LMS)\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-Site Requirements\\r\\n- Workbook Answers (compiled in portfolio)\\r\\n- Group Presentation (evaluated using rubric)\\r\\n- Quiz Results\\r\\n- Interview Docu-vlog\\r\\n- Notes\\r\\n- Assignment\\r\\nOff-Site Requirements\\r\\n- Learning Management System (LMS) \\u2013 Compile all downloaded materials for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 17\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nCritical Evaluation and promotion of Local and Oral History, Museums, Historical Shrines, Cultural Performances, Indigenous People and its Practices, Religious Rites and Rituals, etc.\\r\\n- Local history and its benefits, the principles of conducting local history research\\r\\n- The elements and sequence of oral history research\\r\\n- The significance of national historic sites, Philippine cultural performances, Indigenous People and its practices, and religious rituals and rites.\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nLearning Outcomes\\r\\nCMO-Based Outcomes\\r\\n- Manifest interest in local history\\r\\n- Show concern in promoting and preserving the country\\u2019s historical and cultural heritage\\r\\nBook-Based Outcomes\\r\\n- Appreciate the value of doing history to the present day\\r\\n- Apply historiographical methods in the writing of the history of one\\u2019s locality or country\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Workbook: Answer page 234-235\\r\\n2. Teacher-made quiz\\r\\n3. Rubric for activity OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n1. Complete the Week 17 assignment\\r\\nuploaded in your Learning\\r\\nManagement System (LMS). Once\\r\\naccomplished, download and print a\\r\\ncopy, then submit it during the next\\r\\nface-to-face class.,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Project-based: The students will\\r\\nvisit a local or national museum or\\r\\nplaces with historical significance, or\\r\\nwatch cultural presentation and\\r\\ncelebration, and they made a digital\\r\\nscrapbook on the documentation\\r\\nusing MS PowerPoint, Canva, or any\\r\\nslideshow maker apps\\/websites. They\\r\\nwill also write a short reflection about\\r\\nthe experience. The output of the\\r\\nstudents will be compiled by their\\r\\nrespective group in a Google Drive\\r\\n2. Stage Play Watching (For essay or\\r\\nquiz)\\r\\n3. Group work: Answer pages 246-248 OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n(Week 17)\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-Site Learning Materials\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Visual Presentation (PowerPoint, Graphic Organizers, Whiteboard, etc.)\\r\\n- Lecture Notes and Handouts\\r\\n- Sample Pictures of Philippine historic and cultural sites\\r\\n- Workbook (Readings in Philippine History, pages 225\\u2013245)\\r\\n- Online Sources\\r\\nOff-Site Learning Materials\\r\\n- Learning Management System (LMS)\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-Site Requirements\\r\\n- Workbook Answers (compiled in portfolio)\\r\\n- Project-Based Output: Digital Scrapbook (evaluated using rubric)\\r\\n- Quiz Results\\r\\n- Notes\\r\\n- Assignment\\r\\nOff-Site Requirements\\r\\n- Learning Management System (LMS) \\u2013 Compile all downloaded materials for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 18\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Exam\"}',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,'The course analyzes Philippine history from multiple perspectives through the lens of selected primary sources coming from various\r\ndisciplines and of different genres. Students are given opportunities to analyze the author’s background and main arguments, compare\r\ndifferent points of view, identify biases and examine the evidences presented in the document. The discussions will tackle traditional topics in\r\nhistory and other disciplinary themes that will deepen and broaden their understanding of Philippine political, economic, cultural, social,\r\nscientific and religious history. Priority is given to primary materials that could help students develop their analytical and communication skills.\r\nThe end goal is to develop the historical and critical consciousness of the students so that they will become versatile, articulate, broad-minded,\r\nmorally upright and responsible citizens.\r\nThis course includes mandatory topics on the Philippine Constitution, agrarian reform, and taxation.','[{\"pilo\":\"Analyze texts (written, visual, oral, etc.) critically\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Demonstrate proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Use basic concepts across the domains of knowledge\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Demonstrate critical, analytical, and creative thinking.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Examine the contemporary world from both Phil. And global perspectives\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Take responsibility for knowing and being Filipino\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Reflect critically on shared concern\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Contribute personally and meaningfully to the country\\u2019s development\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Work effectively in a group\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Use current technology to assist and facilitate learning and research\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Manage one\\u2019s knowledge, skills, and values for responsible productive living\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Organize one\\u2019s self for lifelong learning\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','[{\"cilo\":\"Acquire knowledge about the experiences of Filipino people in the past from pre-history to present\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Develop intellectual skills, such as comprehension, analysis, interpretation and evaluation of facts and information of Philippine History through oral defense\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Inculcate among the students\\u2019 certain values such as patriotism and nationalism\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Criticize the importance of strategic location of the Philippines and understand its role in the history of the Filipino people\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Generate a wider perspective of the history of the Filipinos and to appreciate our rich cultural heritage\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','General Education Program aims to:\r\nIntellectual Competencies\r\n1. analyze texts (written, visual, oral, etc.) critically;\r\n2. demonstrate proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies);\r\n3. use basic concepts across the domains of knowledge; and\r\n4. demonstrate critical, analytical, and creative thinking.\r\nPersonal and Civil Responsibility\r\n1. examine the contemporary world from both Phil. And global perspectives;\r\n2. take responsibility for knowing and being Filipino;\r\n3. reflect critically on shared concern; and\r\n4. contribute personally and meaningfully to the country’s development.\r\nPractical Skills\r\n1. work effectively in a group;\r\n2. use current technology to assist and facilitate learning and research;\r\n3. manage one’s knowledge, skills, and values for responsible and productive living; and\r\n4. organize one’s self for lifelong learning.','At the end of the semester, the students should be able to:\r\n1. acquire knowledge about the experiences of Filipino people in the past from pre-history to present;\r\n2. develop intellectual skills, such as comprehension, analysis, interpretation and evaluation of facts and information of Philippine History through oral defense;\r\n3. inculcate among the students’ certain values such as patriotism and nationalism; and\r\n4. criticize the importance of strategic location of the Philippines and understand its role in the history of the Filipino people; and\r\n5. generate a wider perspective of the history of the Filipinos and to appreciate our rich cultural heritage.','At the end of the course, students should be able to:\r\n1. evaluate primary sources for their credibility, authenticity, and provenance;\r\n2. analyze the context, content, and perspective of different kinds of primary sources;\r\n3. determine the contribution of different kinds of primary sources in understanding Philippine history;\r\n4. develop critical and analytical skills with exposure to primary sources;\r\n5. demonstrate the ability to use primary sources to argue in favor or against a particular issue;\r\n6. effectively communicate, using various techniques and genres, their historical analysis of a particular event or issue that\r\ncould\r\nhelp others understand the chosen topic;\r\n7. propose recommendations/solutions to present-day problems based on their understanding of root causes and their\r\nanticipation of future scenarios;\r\n8. display the ability to work in a term and contribute to a group project; and\r\n9. manifest interest in local history and concern in promoting and preserving our country’s national patrimony and cultural\r\nheritage.','Villarico, W., et al. (2019). Readings in Philippine History: First Edition. HisGoPhil Publishing House, Inc. Aurora Blvd., Quezon City. ISBN 978-971-0577-11-8','Books:\r\nCandelaria, J. P., Alporha, V. (2018). Readings in Philippine History: First Edition. Rex Book Store\r\nWebsites:\r\nA CRY FOR CLARIFICATION: A short discussion on the controversies surrounding the cry of Pugadlawin | NHCP | National Historical Commission of the Philippines. (2022, August 23).\r\nhttps://nhcp.gov.ph/articles/a-cry-for-clarification-a-short-discussion-on-the-controversies-surrounding-the-cry-of-pugadlawin/\r\nAbadi, A. P. (2024, February 27). Preserving the Cultural Heritage of the Philippines through the Indigenous Peoples - Mustaqim. Mustaqim.\r\nhttps://mustaqim.com.ph/preserving-the-cultural-heritage-of-the-philippines-through-the-indigenous-peoples/\r\nAgrarian Reform history. (n.d.). Department of Agrarian Reform. https://www.dar.gov.ph/about-us/agrarian-reform-history/\r\nArchive, V. (2020, November 18). ‘Educate, not humiliate’: Fighting back historical distortions. The LaSallian. https://thelasallian.com/2020/11/18/educate-not-humiliate-fighting-back-historical-distortions/\r\nConstitutional history of the Philippines. (n.d.). ConstitutionNet. https://constitutionnet.org/country/philippines\r\nDirect translation of the complete text of Emilio Jacinto’s “Kartilya ng Katipunan.” (2016, May 6). The Kahimyang Project.\r\nhttps://kahimyang.com/kauswagan/articles/1796/direct-translation-of-the-complete-text-of-emilio-jacintos-kartilya-ng-katipunan\r\nDofweb. (2017, December 27). THE TAX REFORM FOR ACCELERATION AND INCLUSION (TRAIN) ACT. Department of Finance.\r\nhttps://www.dof.gov.ph/ra-10963-train-law-and-veto-message-of-the-president/\r\nEarth Shaker PH on X: “The Curious Case of Caloocan [Thread] Whenever we share maps of Metro Manila, people notice that there are ‘two’ Caloocan Cities. To clarify this matter, here’s a simple\r\nexplanation. https://t.co/MGaOxmCv5T” / X. (n.d.). X (Formerly Twitter). https://x.com/earthshakerph/status/1170305715254300672\r\nEnding the Limasawa controversy - 2021 Quincentennial commemorations in the Philippines. (2021, March 28). 2021 Quincentennial Commemorations in the Philippines.\r\nhttps://www.nqc.gov.ph/en/resources/ending-the-limasawa-\r\ncontroversy/?fbclid=IwY2xjawEaj4FleHRuA2FlbQIxMAABHa0yQuvXSTreaQ_oTjD0gRf9WeZft7Oj267mhBivkQ2DPrYjEOT2b7nRLQ_aem_bMn9AxlEm2kFtaUYQyJ7YQ\r\nGavilan, J. (2018, January 16). What you need to know about Charter Change. RAPPLER. https://www.rappler.com/newsbreak/iq/193718-charter-change-explainer-philippine-constitution/\r\nGoodGovPH. (n.d.). Protecting the Philippines’ National Heritage: Flaws & Milestones. GoodGovPH. https://goodgov.ph/f/protecting-the-philippines%E2%80%99-national-heritage-flaws-milestones\r\nHINDI MAIHAHALINTULAD ANG KASAYSAYAN SA. . . - Alvin D. Campomanes | Facebook. (n.d.).\r\nhttps://web.facebook.com/sircamp/posts/pfbid02noid3VPm7EHvdcdTR3f1gT9knvjep83sCmJZT74oAdK8GJHxueVXSHe6aubzGj88l\r\nHow do you know if a historical source is biased? (n.d.). [Video]. History Skills. https://www.historyskills.com/source-criticism/analysis/bias/\r\nHow to analyse and evaluate historical sources. (n.d.). History Skills. https://www.historyskills.com/source-criticism/\r\nHummel, A. L. (2024, March 4). How does art help us to understand the past? | Anita Louise Art. Anita Louise Art. https://anitalouiseart.com/art-help-us-understand-past/\r\nJose Rizal [The Retraction]. (n.d.). http://www.joserizal.ph/rt03.html\r\nKartilya ng Katipunan. (n.d.). Philippine Center for Masonic Studies. https://www.philippinemasonry.org/kartilya-ng-katipunan.html\r\nMcCoy, A. W. (2017). Selected sections and cartoons from “Philippine Cartoons: Political Caricature of the American Era 1900-1941” edited by Alfred W. McCoy and Alfredo R. Roces (1985). Wisc.\r\nhttps://www.academia.edu/32103484/Selected_sections_and_cartoons_from_Philippine_Cartoons_\r\nPolitical_Caricature_of_the_American_Era_1900_1941_edited_by_Alfred_W_McCoy_and_Alfredo_R_Roces_1985_\r\nMcLean, J. (n.d.). Historical Bias | World Civilization. https://courses.lumenlearning.com/suny-hccc-worldcivilization/chapter/historical-bias/\r\nOcampo, A. R. (2024, August 2). When did history become ‘kasaysayan’? INQUIRER.net. https://opinion.inquirer.net/175684/when-did-history-become-kasaysayan\r\nOut with the old and in with the new: the latest changes in taxation. (2024, January 16). Grant Thornton Philippines.\r\nhttps://www.grantthornton.com.ph/insights/articles-and-updates1/from-where-we-sit/out-with-the-old-and-in-with-the-new-the-latest-changes-in-taxation/\r\nPhilippine History -- The Act of Declaration of Philippine Independence. (n.d.). 2009. https://www.msc.edu.ph/centennial/declaration.html\r\nSantos, T. U. (2011, October 4). Rizal’s retraction: Truth vs Myth. The Varsitarian. https://varsitarian.net/news/20111004/rizals_retraction_truth_vs_myth\r\nTeachinghistory.org. (n.d.). https://teachinghistory.org/teaching-materials/ask-a-master-teacher/23610\r\nTeam, M. B. (2021, December 16). Why is it important to study history? https://www.mooc.org/blog/why-is-it-important-to-study-history\r\nVideos:\r\nAmericanRhetoric.com. (2018, August 16). Corazon Aquino - U.S. Congress Speech (Audio enhanced) [Video]. YouTube. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9bavnuT4RlU\r\nNHCPOfficial. (2023, March 31). GOMBURZA (An NHCP documentary) [Video]. YouTube. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iUlf9KtbqC8\r\nProf Next Door. (2023, October 8). Content and contextual analysis in readings in Philippine History [Video]. YouTube. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dspd7Z1n7X8\r\nProf Next Door. (2023, October 10). External and Internal criticism: Readings in Philippine History [Video]. YouTube. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z6QP567Z-7c\r\nProject Offbeat. (2022, March 26). Ambeth Ocampo on Historical Revisionism | Project Offbeat Podcast [Video]. YouTube. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0SSUSz3xECQ\r\nWhy study art of the past? (n.d.). [Video]. Khan Academy. https://www.khanacademy.org/humanities/approaches-to-art-history/approaches-art-history/introduction-art-history/v/why-study-art-of-the-past','Students must be able to:\r\n1. complete at least 80% of the student participation;\r\n2. demonstrate punctuality according to his/her schedule; and\r\n3. alternative assessment\r\n3.1. when student fail to comply or perform poorly in major examination and/or nonparticipation because of valid reasons e.g. health, force majeure needs to provide alternative assessment such as\r\nproject, presentation, oral examination and research output.','Cluster Leader:\r\n\r\nSean Henricks V. Cayme, LPT\r\nCluster Members:','Faculty Member:\r\nSean Henricks V. Cayme, LPT\r\nEmail Address:\r\nshcayme.95@gmail.com\r\nConsultation Hours:\r\n12:30 – 2:30 PM (Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday)\r\nMV Campus – General Education Program Office','SEAN HENRICKS V. CAYME, LPT','MICHAEL L. BERSAMIN, LPT','CHARLIE I. CARIÑO, Ph.D.','2026-02-06 12:47:48','2026-02-06 12:47:48',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
