(34,'DALUMATFIL','DALUMAT NG/SA FILIPINO','Minor','General Education','CHED',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'{\"Week 0\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives, Philosophy and School Organizational Structure School Policies Orientation in Online and Modular Learning System,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nRecite, internalize and explain the BCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives and Philosophy\\r\\nDeepen knowledge on the school\'s policies, guidelines, rules and regulations.\\r\\nFamiliarize on the new normal system of education through online, modular learning system and Blended Learning Delivery Modality (BLDM),, Assessment: ONSITE: Identify the Vision and Mission statements of BCP.\\r\\nCritically analyze these statements in 500 words, focusing on the following:\\r\\nThe clarity and coherence of the statements.\\r\\nHow these statements reflect the school\'s commitment to education.\\r\\nThe alignment of these statements with the current educational landscape.\\r\\nVerify that the BCP VMGO are align with the school goals thru checklist (PMED tools) OFFSITE: Navigate LMS and know the function of each feature.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Read and internalize the following printed materials for Students and Parents Orientation: OFF-SITE: Presentation and Lecture Discussion (PowerPoint Presentation) of Students and Parents Orientation:,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nInstructional Materials\\r\\nVideo Presentation of BCP Hymn\\r\\nYouTube Video Title: BESTLINK COLLEGE OF THE PHILIPPINES HYMN (BCP hymn)\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NuEYO11Wb4E\\r\\nStudent Hand Book\\r\\nLearning Management System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCheck alignment report\",\"Week 1\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDalumat-salita: salita ng taon\\/sawikaan,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Mapalalim \\u00e0ng \\r\\npagpapahalaga sa \\r\\nsariling Teorya ng mga Pilipino sa ibat-ibang larangan. \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Makagawa ng \\r\\nmga malikhain at \\r\\nmapanghikayat na \\r\\npresentasyon ng \\r\\nimpormasyon at analisis na akma sa ibat -ibang konteksto \\r\\n\\r\\n3.Makapagpahayag \\r\\nng mga makabuluhang \\r\\nkaisipan sa pamamagitan \\r\\nng tradisyonal at \\r\\nmodernong midyang \\r\\nakma sa kontekstong \\r\\npilipino \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Paunang aktibidad I \\r\\n1.1. Share sa mga paksa \\r\\nbalita ng taon \\r\\n2. Talakayan Virtual \\r\\n2.1. Diskasyon sa \\r\\npamamagitan ng paggamit ng \\r\\npower point presentation \\r\\n1. Paunang aktibidad: modyul \\r\\n1.1. Think-pair and share as \\r\\na ispesipikong paksa sa \\r\\npag-aaral ng panitikan \\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pagpapalarawan sa nakaugat na reyalidad ng \\r\\nlipunang Pilipino \\r\\n2. Pagpapatalakay sa paksang aralin \\r\\n2.1 Paggamit ng Power Point \\r\\nPresentation \\r\\n2.2 Sagutan sa bawat tanong ng mga mag aaral \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Gumawa ng reaksyon \\r\\npapel na tumatalakay sa \\r\\nkasalukuyang sitwasyon ng ating panitikan \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Digital Timeline ng mga Salitang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n3. \\\"Salita ng Taon\\\" na Pagboto at Aktibidad sa Pagsusuri\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Laro ng Pagtutugma ng mga Idyomang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Blog ng Wikang Pilipino\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Pagtatanghal ng Grupo (Rubric)\\r\\n2. Resulta ng Pagsusulit\\r\\n3. Mga Tala\\r\\n4. Asignatura\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Gumawa ng Reaksyon papel na tumatalakay sa kasalukuyang sitwasyon\\r\\nng ating panitikan,\",\"Week 2\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nAng Filipinong may \\r\\ntemplang Bisaya sa \\r\\nkamay ng makatang \\r\\ntagalog na si Delucia \\r\\nT. Anonuemo ni S. Antonio \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Matukoy ang mga mapagkakatiwalaan \\r\\nmakabubuka at \\r\\nkapaki-pakinabang na \\r\\nsanggunian sa \\r\\npagdadalumat at \\r\\npananaliksik. \\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Makagawa ng malawak at makabuluhang \\r\\nKonsepto at teoryang local at dayuhan na akma sa konteksta ng komunidad at bansa, \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Ilarawan ang nilatha ng makatang tagalog na si Delucia T. Anonuemo. \\r\\n2. Pagtalakay \\r\\n2.1 Basahin at sagutin ang mga tanong sa Module 2  OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Paunang Aktibidad Modyul \\r\\nII \\r\\n1.1 Paghambing at \\r\\npagtutuklas sa batayang \\r\\nkaalaman na pagpapatubig \\r\\nng palay noon at ngayon. \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo- \\r\\n2.1 Panimulang \\r\\nGawain: diskusyon gamit ang power point presentation \\r\\n2.2 concept mapping sa kaugnayan sa paksa batay sa \\r\\nmodyul. \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Sa pamamagitan ng mga larawan, ibigay ang pag \\r\\nunawa sa mga uri ng pagpapatubig noon at sa \\r\\nmakabagong panahon \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Comparative Analysis Worksheet\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Digital Timeline ng Buhay at mga Akda ni Anonuemo\\r\\n\\r\\n4. \\\"Salitang Bisaya sa mga Tula ni Anonuemo\\\" na Word Cloud\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Talakayan sa Forum o Blog\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n 1. Resulta ng Pagsusulit\\r\\n2. Mga Tala\\r\\n3. Digital Timeline Presentation\\r\\n4. Sanaysay sa Comparative Analysis\\r\\n5. Buod ng Talakayan sa Forum o Blog\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 3\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDalumat sa \\r\\nkasaysayan ng \\r\\nkapilipinuhan \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mga primaryang batis na nakasulat at di nakasulat. \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Maisaalang alang ang mga historyador ang magbatis o sanggunian ng \\r\\nkasaysayan \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maisaisa ang \\r\\nprimaryang batis na \\r\\nnakasulat at di nakasulat. \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Paghambing na \\r\\npagtalakay sa \\r\\nmagkakaugnay na paksa. \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Basahin ang kasaysayan \\r\\nng kapilipinuhan \\r\\n2. Pagtalakay \\r\\n2.1 Ibigay ang sariling \\r\\nreaksyon batay sa mga \\r\\nhistoryador ng \\r\\nkapilipinuhan \\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1.Paunang Aktibidad; Modyul 3 \\r\\n1.1 Pagtalakay gamit ang KWL chart tungkol sa kasaysayan ng kapilipinuhan \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo: \\r\\n2.1 Diskusyon gamit ang Power Point Presentation at panoorin ang video sa Learning \\r\\nManagement System \\r\\n(LMS). \\r\\n2.2 Sumulat ng maikling \\r\\nsanaysay tungkol \\r\\nsa kasaysayan ng \\r\\nkapilipinuhan \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Paghahanap ng Primaryang Batis\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Digital na Arkiba\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Paglikha ng Timeline\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Debate\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Pagsulat ng Historical Fiction\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Imbentaryo ng Primaryang Batis\\r\\n2. Annotated Bibliography\\r\\n3. Digital Exhibit\\r\\n4. Sanaysay sa Kasaysayan\\r\\n5. Kuwento ng Historical Fiction\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 4\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDalumat sa Filipino. \\r\\nMakabagong Emilio \\r\\nJacinto \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mga akdang naisulat \\r\\nsa panahon ng \\r\\nkatipunan \\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Pagkakaiba \\r\\nng makabagong \\r\\nEmilio Jacinto sa \\r\\nlumang Emilio \\r\\nJacinto \\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maipaliwanag \\r\\nang kahalagahan ng \\r\\nisang huwarang \\r\\nbayani. \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Nakapagpahay \\r\\nag ng mga saloobin \\r\\nhinggil sa makabagong \\r\\nbayani\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1.1 pahambing ng \\r\\npagtalakay sa mag \\r\\nnakaugnay na akda. \\r\\n1.2 ibahagi ang iyong \\r\\nsaloobin sa panimulang \\r\\ngawain sa modyul. \\r\\n2. Lesson proper: \\r\\n2.1 Basahin at intindihin \\r\\nang tinalakay sa modyul na \\r\\nnakapaloob dito \\r\\n2.2 Mga tanong at sagot.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: Paunang Aktibidad: Modyul 4 \\r\\n1.1 Pangkatang \\r\\ntalakayan tanong at sagot tungkol sa teksto. \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo: \\r\\n2.1 PANOORIN ANG \\r\\nVIDEO SA Learning \\r\\nManagement System (LMS) \\r\\n3. Pagbubuod \\r\\nsa tinalakay para sa modyul \\r\\n OFF-SITE: \\r\\n1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Paglikha ng Komiks\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Pagsulat ng Liham\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Paggawa ng Music Video\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Paglikha ng Digital Art\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Komiks\\r\\n2. Sanaysay sa Debate\\r\\n3. Liham kay Emilio Jacinto\\r\\n4. Analysis ng Music Video\\r\\n5. Reflection Paper\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 5\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBangka at Lipunan \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Natutukoy \\r\\nang gumamit na \\r\\nsimbolo \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Ilahad ang \\r\\nKaugnay na bangka \\r\\nSa sistemang \\r\\nPolitikal sa ating \\r\\nbansa \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Nakakatukoy ang \\r\\nmga salik na nagtangi \\r\\nbangka ng Pillipino \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Makapag \\r\\npapaliwanag ang mga \\r\\nkamahayag ayun sa \\r\\nnabuo kaugnay at \\r\\nbumabalot na bangkang \\r\\nsinimbulong bangkang \\r\\nPilipino \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1.1 ibahagi ang iyong \\r\\nsaloobing sa panimulang Gawain \\r\\n1.2 Markang pagbigkas. \\r\\n2.Lesson proper: \\r\\n2.1 Basahin at Analisahin ang tanong na  nakapaloob \\r\\nsa talakayan sa modyul \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: \\r\\n1. Paunang Aktibidad; \\r\\nModyul 5 \\r\\n1.1 Think-pair and \\r\\nshare sa mga ispesipikong teksto, \\r\\n2. Birtwal na Pagtuturo; \\r\\ngamit ang power point presentation at panoorin \\r\\nang video sa Learning \\r\\nManagement \\r\\nSystem (LMS) \\r\\n2.2 Mga tanong at sagot. Host\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Nakakakilala ang \\r\\nnagging paggamit ng \\r\\nsimbolismo ang bangka sa \\r\\npaglalatag ng katutubong \\r\\nlipunang Pilipino bago ang \\r\\nkolomissasyong kastila \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Unawain at ipaliwanag ang \\r\\nawitin ni \'Francis \\r\\nMagalona na \\r\\n\\\"Ako ay Pilipino\\u201d \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Paglikha ng Diorama\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Pagsusuri ng mga Sining Biswal\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Pagsasagawa ng Panayam\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Resulta ng pagsusulit\\r\\n2. Pagtatanghal ng grupo\\r\\n3. Diorama\\r\\n4. Art Analysis Paper\\r\\n5. Transcript ng Panayam\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 6\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPrelim Exam\",\"Week 7\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nRebulasyong Pilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mga Kakintal\\u00f3n \\r\\nmay malaking bahagl \\r\\nsa pakikibaka sa \\r\\ntunay na pang \\r\\nbansang \\r\\ndemokratikong \\r\\nInglenes \\r\\nng buong \\r\\nsambayanang \\r\\npilipino \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Nakatutukoy ang \\r\\nmakabuluhang \\r\\nkapakinabangan ng \\r\\nbangunea \\r\\nsa pagdadalumat at \\r\\npananaliksik \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Nakapagpapahayag ng mabisang \\r\\nopinion ukol sa lipunan at Rebolusyon \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Nakapagpaliw \\r\\nanag ng kahalagahan \\r\\nng Demokratikong \\r\\nRebulasyon \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Paunang Aktibidad modyul 7 \\r\\n1.1 ibahagi ang iyong \\r\\nsaloobin sa panimulang \\r\\ngawian \\r\\n2. Lesson Proper: \\r\\n2.1 Basahin at intindihin \\r\\nang talakayan at sagutin ang \\r\\nmga katanungan na \\r\\nnakapaloob dito \\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: \\r\\n1. Paunang Aktibidad modyul 7 \\r\\n1.1 ibahagi ang iyong \\r\\nsaloobin sa panimulang \\r\\ngawlan \\r\\n2.Magsulat ng maikling \\r\\nsanaysay hinggil sa binasang \\r\\nakda\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Paglikha ng Infographic\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Debate ng Pagganap\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Timeline ng Kasaysayan\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Reflective Journal\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Pagpapakita ng Pananaliksik ng Grupo\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Infographic na naka-print o nasa digital na format, na ipapakita sa klase.\\r\\n2. Video recording ng debate o nakasulat na script ng mga talakayan na isinagawa.\\r\\n3. Isang hand-written o typed na journal entry na ipapasa sa guro.\\r\\n4. PowerPoint presentation, poster, o video ng grupo na ipapakita sa harap ng klase.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 8\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nEDUKASYON:  bilang Lungsod at katwirang \\r\\nLalawigan\\r\\n \\r\\n1. Ang pagkakaiba batay sa katwirang lungsod at \\r\\nkatwirang lalawigan \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Anu ano \\r\\nang pananaw ng \\r\\ntaga lalawigan at \\r\\ntaga lungsod sa \\r\\nEdukasyon \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Makapagpapali \\r\\nwanag ng kahalagahan \\r\\nng EDUKASYON bilang tagpuan Katwirang \\r\\nlalawigan. \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Makapag \\r\\npahayag ng mga \\r\\nmakabuluhang kaisipan \\r\\nsa pamamagitan ng \\r\\ntradisyon ng Pilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Naisa-isip ang \\r\\nkultura at iba ang \\r\\naspetong panlipunan \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Paunang Aktibidad: \\r\\nModyul 8 \\r\\n1.1 Concept mapping \\r\\n1.2 Think pair \\r\\nshare sa ispesipikong \\r\\nteksto \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo: \\r\\n2.1 Talakayan at \\r\\ndiskusyon gamit ang \\r\\npowerpoint presentation.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Basahin ang pagkakaiba \\r\\nng edukasyon sa \\r\\nlungsod at katwirang \\r\\nlalawigan \\r\\n2. Sagutan ang mga \\r\\nnakatakdang mga \\r\\ngawain \\r\\n3.Sumulat ng \\r\\npatalang buod ng mga \\r\\nmahahalagang \\r\\npangyayare \\r\\nmula sa akdang bansa.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Visual Aid: Venn Diagram\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Pagsusuri ng Dokumento\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Interactive Map \\r\\n\\r\\n5. Cultural Exhibit\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Nakumpletong Venn diagram na ipapasa ng mga mag-aaral pagkatapos ng talakayan.\\r\\n2. Nakasulat na summary at analysis ng mga napag-aralan.\\r\\n3. Concept presentation (maaaring sa pamamagitan ng visual aid tulad ng PowerPoint o Manila paper) at isang maikling report.\\r\\n4. Mga written observations at insights mula sa interactive map activity.\\r\\n5. Reflection paper tungkol sa mga natutunan mula sa cultural exhibit.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 9\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nAng pinagmulan ng kaisipan Feminista sa \\r\\nPilipinas \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mga \\r\\npinagmulan \\r\\nng kaisipan Feminista sa \\r\\nPilipinas \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Mga sanhi at bunga ng mga \\r\\nSuliraning pinagmulan ang \\r\\nkaisipan Feminista sa Pilipinas \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Natutukoy ng \\r\\npantay sa pagtingin sa \\r\\nibat-ibang or intasyon \\r\\npang kasarian \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Naiisa isa ang \\r\\nmahhalagang pangyayari \\r\\nsa araling binasa. \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Naunawaan ang \\r\\nmga pagkakaiba-iba ng \\r\\nbawat tao sa isang \\r\\nlipunan \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Paunang aktibidad module 9 \\r\\n1.1 Tanong at sagot tungkol \\r\\nsa teksto \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo \\r\\n2.1 Talakayang birtwal at \\r\\ndiskusyon sa \\r\\npamamagitang ng Power \\r\\nPoint Presentation \\r\\n3. Pagbubuod para sa \\r\\nnatalakay\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Maisa-isa ang mga \\r\\npinagmulang kaisipang \\r\\nFeminista sa Pilipino \\r\\n2. Pagtalakay \\r\\n2.1 Ilahad sa \\r\\npamamagitan ng sariling \\r\\nopinion ang saloobin sa \\r\\nmga suliranin pinagmulan \\r\\nang kaisipang Feminista \\r\\nsa Pilipinas \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Historical Case Study: Magbibigay ang guro ng mga case study na naglalarawan ng mahahalagang pangyayari sa kasaysayan ng kaisipang feminista sa Pilipinas.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. 2. Graphic Organizer: Concept Map: Ang guro ay magpapagawa ng concept map sa mga mag-aaral upang ilarawan ang mga sanhi at bunga ng mga suliraning nagbunsod sa kaisipang feminista sa Pilipinas.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Panel Discussion\\r\\nGawain: Ang guro ay mag-oorganisa ng isang panel discussion kung saan ang mga mag-aaral ay tatalakayin ang iba\'t ibang pananaw at karanasan ukol sa oryentasyon pangkasarian.\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Isang nakasulat na buod at pagsusuri ng bawat case study na ipapasa sa guro.\\r\\n2. Nakumpletong concept map na naka-print o nakasulat sa papel.\\r\\n3. Nakasulat na ulat ng mga tanong, argumento, at konklusyon mula sa panel discussion.\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 10\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nEkspresyong bakla sa Rebolusyong \\r\\nPilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mga \\r\\npananaw sa \\r\\nsalitang bakla s\\u00e1 \\r\\nlarangan ng araling \\r\\nFilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Mga sanhi tungo sa pagpapalaya ng mga bakla sa ating lipunan\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Nakatutukoy ang kamalayan sa magaganap sa ating bansa at magkaroon din ang partisipasyon tungo sa ikauunlad nila \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Nakapagpahayag \\r\\nkaisipan sa pamamagitan \\r\\nng tradisyunal at modern midyang akma sa paksa \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Nalalaman \\r\\nang kaisapan ng \\r\\nbawat mag-aaral \\r\\nang pagkakaiba \\r\\nng bawat tao sa isang \\r\\nlipunan\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Paunang Aktibidad: Modyul 10 \\r\\n1.1 isipin, ipares at \\r\\nibahagi sa mga ispesipikong \\r\\nteksto. \\r\\n2. Birtwal na Pagtuturo: \\r\\n2.1 Talakayang virtual at \\r\\ndiscussion gamit ang \\r\\nPower point Presentation. \\r\\n2.1 panoorin ang video sa \\r\\nLearning Management \\r\\nSystem(LMS) \\r\\n2.3 Mga tanong at sagot HOST. \\r\\n2.Lesson Proper: \\r\\n2.1 basahin at intindihin \\r\\nang talakayan sa modyul at \\r\\ngawin at sagutin ang mga \\r\\ntanong na nakapaloob dito\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: \\r\\n1. Ilarawan ang \\r\\nEspansyong bakla sa \\r\\nRebolusyong Pilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Pagtalakay \\r\\n2.1 Basahin o panoorin \\r\\nsa facebook, twitter, \\r\\ninstagram ang tungkol sa \\r\\nmakabagong panitikan sa \\r\\npanahon ng Rebolusyon \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Timeline ng Kasaysayan: Maghanda ng timeline na naglalaman ng mga pangunahing kaganapan na may kaugnayan sa ekspresyong bakla sa panahon ng Rebolusyong Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Interactive Map: Gumawa ng interactive map na nagpapakita ng mga lugar sa Pilipinas kung saan aktibong ipinaglalaban ang karapatan ng mga bakla noong panahon ng Rebolusyong Pilipino.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Case Study Handouts: Magbigay ang guro ng mga case study handouts na naglalarawan ng mga indibidwal na may kinalaman sa ekspresyong bakla noong panahon ng rebolusyon.\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Discussion Guide: Gumawa ang guro ng discussion guide na naglalaman ng mga tanong at tema para sa klase upang masusing talakayin ang ekspresyong bakla at ang kanilang papel sa lipunan noong panahon ng rebolusyon\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Nakumpletong timeline na naka-print o nasa digital na format na nagpapakita ng mga mahahalagang kaganapan.\\r\\n2. Interactive map na ipapasa ng mga mag-aaral, maaaring nasa papel o digital na format.\\r\\n3. Nakasulat na pagsusuri at reaksyon ng mga mag-aaral sa mga case study handouts.\\r\\n4. Discussion guide na ipapasa sa mga mag-aaral at gagamitin sa klase para sa structured discussion.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 11\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSikolohiyang \\r\\nPilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mapahalagaha \\r\\nn ang pakikipag \\r\\nkapwa at \\r\\npagbabagong dagal \\r\\nng mga, Pilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Sumasaklaw\\r\\nang Disipilna ang \\r\\nsiklohiyong Pilipino \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maunawaan ang ambag ng siklohiyang Pilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Masusuri ang kahalagahan na naidudulot ng kaalaran sa sikolohiya \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Mauunawaan \\r\\nang pangtuklas ng \\r\\nsarili sa aspektong \\r\\npanlipunan \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Paunang Aktibidad: Modyul 11 \\r\\n1.1 KWL tsart\\/gamit \\r\\nang graphic organizer \\r\\nsa pagtatalakay ng \\r\\npaksa \\r\\n2. Birtwal na Pagtuturo: \\r\\n2.1 Talakayang Virtual \\r\\nat diskusyon gamit ang \\r\\npower point Presentation \\r\\n2.2 panoorin ang \\r\\nvideo sa Learning \\r\\nManagement \\r\\nSystem(LMS) \\r\\n2.3 Mga tanong at sagot Host \\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1.1 Ang kapintalan na \\r\\ndapat pahalagahan sa silikohiyang Pilipino \\r\\n1.2 Tuklasin ang pagbabagong dagal ng mga Pilipino \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo \\r\\n2.1 Talakayang birtwal at diskusyon gamit ang Power Point Presentation \\r\\n2.2 Mga tanong at sagot host \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Kulturang Kategorya Card Sort: Magbigay ng mga card na naglalaman ng iba\'t ibang aspeto ng sikolohiyang Pilipino (hal. \\\"Pakikipagkapwa,\\\" \\\"Pagbubuklod ng Pamilya,\\\" \\\"Bahala Na Attitude\\\").\\r\\n\\r\\n2.Concept Mapping Activity: Gumawa ng concept map na nagpapakita ng mga pangunahing ideya at konsepto ng sikolohiyang Pilipino.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Case Study Analysis: Magbigay ng mga case studies na naglalarawan ng iba\'t ibang sitwasyon na may kinalaman sa sikolohiyang Pilipino.\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Nakasort na mga card at isang pangkatang ulat na nagpapaliwanag ng pagkakaayos ng mga aspeto.\\r\\n2. Nakumpletong concept map na may mga detalyadong koneksyon at ideya na ipapasa sa guro.\\r\\n3. Nakasulat na pagsusuri at rekomendasyon para sa bawat case study.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 12\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMidterm Exam\",\"Week 13\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSAD CAPITAL \\r\\n1. Isang pamana ng Rebolusyon sa Pilipinas. \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Nasusuri ang sinulat ni M.H.R.X. ang aklat \\r\\nng SAD CAPITAL \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Layunin ang \\r\\nkontra modernidad \\r\\nang magtaguyod ng \\r\\nisang Rebolusyong \\r\\nmagbabago sa \\r\\nimpogalistang order.\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Masusuri ang krisis ng mga Rebolusyon \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Mapahalaga ang pag aaral ng ekonomiya at politika \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Mauunawaan ang manggagawang Pilipino \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Sagutin sa \\r\\ninyong palagay bakit \\r\\ntinawag na isang das \\r\\nkapital \\r\\n2. Anu-ano ang \\r\\nmga katangian ng \\r\\ntulang sumibol sa \\r\\npanahon ng hapon? \\r\\nng at sagot. Host  OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n.,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Nailalarawan sa \\r\\npamamagitan ng isinulat \\r\\nni MHRX ang SAD Capital \\r\\n2. Pagtalakay \\r\\nng \\r\\naralin sa pamamagitan \\r\\nPower Point Presentation \\r\\n2.1 Gumawa ng \\r\\n\\u201cClaster Diagram\\u201d sa mga \\r\\nkrisis ng Rebolusyon \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Worksheet ng Paghahambing: Magbigay ng worksheet na naglalaman ng mga tanong para sa paghahambing ng mga ideya sa \\\"SAD Capital\\\" at mga historikal na rebolusyon sa Pilipinas.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. PowerPoint Presentation ng Kontra-Modernidad\\r\\nGawain: Magbuo ng isang PowerPoint presentation na nagpapaliwanag ng kontra-modernidad sa \\\"SAD Capital\\\" at ang konteksto nito sa rebolusyon.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Role-Playing Scenarios Template: Maghanda ng mga template para sa role-playing scenarios na magpapakita ng mga pangunahing sitwasyon mula sa \\\"SAD Capital.\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Nakumpletong worksheet na naglalaman ng mga sagot at pagsusuri.\\r\\n2. Transcript ng debate na nagpapakita ng mga argumento at pananaw ng bawat grupo.\\r\\n3. Video recording o nakasulat na script ng role-playing scenarios na nagpapakita ng kanilang interpretasyon ng mga ideya sa libro.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 14\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nKontra Modernidad \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Masinsin at \\r\\nmapanuring pagtuklas \\r\\nsa sarili ang maling \\r\\npagpapahayag ng \\r\\nkabihasnan \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Maibabala \\r\\nngkas ang \\r\\ntrajiktoning \\r\\nimahinasyong \\r\\nmakabansa\\u2019t \\r\\nmakamasa \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Makasusuri \\r\\nmag taguyod ng \\r\\nisang Rebolusyong \\r\\nmagbabago sa \\r\\nimperyalistang order \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Makapalaganap ng makatang katanungan, \\r\\nmagkakapantay-pantay at kasaganahan para sa lahat \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Nauuwaan ang pagtuklas ng sarili sa aspektong panlipunan \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Ibahagi ang iyong saloobin sa panimulang Gawain patungkol sa sitwasyon. \\r\\n2. Panoorin ang \\r\\nvideong naka upload sa \\r\\ninyong (LMS) \\r\\n3. Mga pagsasanay  OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Paunang aktibidad: modyul 14 \\r\\n1.1 pangkatang \\r\\npagbabasa at pagunawa sa teksto \\r\\n1.2 \\\"the clash\\\" tanong at sagot \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo \\r\\n2.1 talakayang virtual \\r\\ngamit ang Power-Point Presentation at panoorin ang video sa Learning Management System(LMS) \\r\\n2. Lesson Proper: \\r\\n2.1 Basahin at \\r\\nunawain ang mga \\r\\ntanong na nakapaloob sa modyul at sagutin ang \\r\\nmga tanong na nakapaloob dito \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Gabay sa Masinsin at Mapanuring Pagsusuri\\r\\nGawain: Gumawa ng gabay na magbibigay sa mga mag-aaral ng mga hakbang para sa masinsin at mapanuring pagsusuri ng mga konsepto ng kontra-modernidad.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Listahan ng mga Tanong para sa Talakayan\\r\\nGawain: Maghanda ng listahan ng mga tanong na magagamit sa klase para sa pagtalakay ng mga ideya ng kontra-modernidad.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Worksheet para sa Pagbuo ng Ideya ng Rebolusyon\\r\\nGawain: Magbigay ng worksheet na magtutulong sa mga mag-aaral na bumuo ng kanilang sariling mga ideya para sa isang rebolusyon na magbabago sa imperyalistang kaayusan.\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Nakasulat na gabay na magagamit ng guro sa pagtuturo at ng mga mag-aaral sa pagsusuri.\\r\\n2. Listahan ng mga tanong para sa talakayan na ipapasa sa mga mag-aaral.\\r\\n3. Worksheet para sa Pagbuo ng Ideya ng Rebolusyon\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 15\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBigwas sa Neoliberalismo, Alternatibo sa Kapitalismo: Adbokasing Pangwika at Sosyalistang Programa sa Nobelang Mga Ibong Mandaragit,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maipaliwanag ang kahalagahan ng wikang Filipino sa  pagdadalumat o pagteteorya.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Maisaalang-alang ang kultura at iba pang \\r\\naspektong panlipunan sa pagsasagawa ng pananaliksik.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Malinang ang Filipino bilang daluyan ng inter\\/multidisiplinaring pagdadalumat at pananaliksik na nakaugat sa mga realidad ng lipunang Pilipino.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Maisabuhay ang nilalaman ang \\r\\nteolohiya na \\r\\nbatid no tao sa \\r\\nwikang Hebreo \\r\\n2. Pagtalakay sa mga \\r\\ntanong at sagot \\r\\n- Binigyan \\r\\nhambing ang pagkakaib \\r\\nng neoliberal sa \\r\\nPilipinas(Rubiks) \\r\\n3. Sumulat \\r\\nNo sanaysay tungkol sapag bigwal sa neoliberal\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Paunang Aktibidad: Modyul 15 \\r\\n1 sa pamamagitan ng \\r\\nConcept Mapping-Migrasyon \\r\\n2. Birtwal na pagtuturo: \\r\\n2.1 Talakayang virtual \\r\\nay dis cission gamit ang power point presentation \\r\\n2.2 Panoorin ang \\r\\nvideo sa Learning \\r\\nManagement \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Pagsusuri ng Teksto na Worksheet\\r\\nGawain: Magbigay ng worksheet na naglalaman ng mga tanong para sa pagsusuri ng kahalagahan ng wikang Filipino sa pagdadalumat sa \\\"Mga Ibong Mandaragit\\\".\\r\\n\\r\\n2. PowerPoint Presentation sa Kultura at Pananaliksik\\r\\nGawain: Maghanda ng PowerPoint presentation na nagpapaliwanag kung paano isinasama ang kultura at iba pang aspektong panlipunan sa pananaliksik batay sa \\\"Mga Ibong Mandaragit\\\".\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Case Study Analysis Sheet\\r\\nMagbigay ng case study analysis sheet na naglalaman ng mga halimbawa ng pananaliksik na isinagawa sa konteksto ng Filipino wika at kulturang panlipunan.\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Nakahandang worksheet na magagamit ng mga mag-aaral para sa pagsusuri ng teksto.\\r\\n2. Nakahandang case study analysis sheet na ipapasa sa mga mag-aaral para sa pagsusuri.\\r\\n3. Template para sa research proposal na magagamit ng mga mag-aaral sa kanilang pananaliksik.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 16\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPananaliksik tungkol \\r\\nsa teolohiyang \\r\\nPilipino. \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mailahad ang teolohiya \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Maibabahagi ang mabuting \\r\\nbalita ni Hesukristo \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Maisabuhay \\r\\nang nilalaman ang \\r\\nteolohiya na batid ng \\r\\ntao sa wikang Hebreo \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Makatukoy \\r\\nangmga \\r\\nmapagkakatiwalaan \\r\\nkapaki-pakinabang sa \\r\\npagdadalumat at \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Makapgpapahay \\r\\nag ng mga \\r\\nnakasalukuyan \\r\\nkaisapan sa \\r\\npamamagitan ng \\r\\ntradisyunal kaisipan sa \\r\\npamamagitan ng \\r\\nkontekstong Pilipino \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Mapapahalagahan\\r\\nang teyolohiyang \\r\\nkulture at iba pang \\r\\naspektong panlipinan sa pagsasagawa ng \\r\\npananaliksik \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Worksyap sa pagsulat \\r\\nng wika \\\"Dahoy ang \\r\\nbuhay \\\"Ako ang daan,ako \\r\\nang buhay \\\"Ako ang \\r\\npag-asa Ang ibat ibang \\r\\ndahilan ng gahting mga \\r\\nkababyang Pillpino na \\r\\nkaugnay ang \\r\\nnebliberalismo  OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: Paunang aktibidad: Modyul \\r\\n16 \\r\\n1.1 ibahagi ang iyong saloobin \\r\\nsa panimulang Gawin. \\r\\n2. Lesson Proper: \\r\\n2.1 basahin ang mga \\r\\ntanong na napakaloob dito \\r\\n3. Birtwal na pagtuturo \\r\\n3.1 pagsasabuhay sa \\r\\npaksang gwain \\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. PowerPoint Presentation sa Teolohiya at Mabuting Balita: Maghanda ng PowerPoint presentation na nagpapaliwanag ng teolohiya sa kontekstong Pilipino at kung paano maibabahagi ang mabuting balita ni Hesukristo sa konteksto ng kultura.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Worksheet para sa Paghahambing ng Tradisyunal at Kontemporaryong Pananaw sa Teolohiya: Maghanda ng worksheet na naglalaman ng mga tanong at aktibidad para sa paghahambing ng tradisyunal at kontemporaryong pananaw sa teolohiya\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Template para sa Research Proposal sa Teolohiyang Pilipino: Magbigay ng template para sa paggawa ng research proposal na nakatuon sa teolohiyang Pilipino.\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Activity sheet na magagamit ng mga mag-aaral para sa pagsusuri at pagtalakay ng teolohiya sa kontekstong Pilipino.\\r\\n2. Handouts na naglalaman ng mga case study para sa pagsusuri sa klase.\\r\\n3. Template para sa research proposal na magagamit ng mga mag-aaral sa kanilang pananaliksik tungkol sa teolohiyang Pilipino.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 17\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMula Tore \\r\\npagtungong \\r\\nPalengke \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Tungkulin ng lahat \\r\\nng progresibong guro \\r\\nat mag-aaral ang \\r\\npagpapalaganap ng \\r\\nsiymlipiko at \\r\\nmakamasang \\r\\nEdukasyon \\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Malinang ang\\r\\nIsang Edukasyon na \\r\\nNag tataguyod ng \\r\\nkapakanan ng bansa \\r\\n\\r\\n2. Nakapagoapaliwanag ng sariling paraan palengke sa paksang tinatalakay.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Mapapahalagaha \\r\\nn ang sailing Teorya ng \\r\\nmga Pilipino sa \\r\\nlba\'t-Ibang larangan\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Ilarawana ng tore pagtungong \\r\\npalengke \\r\\n1.2 Sagutan mula sa \\r\\npaksang tinalakay sa power point presentation \\r\\n1.3 Gumawa ng \\r\\n\\u201ccluster diagram\\u201d mula sa paksang tinalakay \\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Paunang Aktbid \\r\\nModyul 17 \\r\\n1.1 ibahagi ang yong \\r\\nsaloobin sa panimulang \\r\\nGawain ng sa Modyul \\r\\n2. Lesson Proper: \\r\\n2.1 Panoorin ang video \\r\\nPresentation sa inyong LMS \\r\\n2,.2 Mga tanong at sagot HOST\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Basahin ang in-upload na lesson proper sa iyong Learning Management System para sa karagdagang pagkatuto.\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Activity Sheet sa Progresibong Edukasyon: Maghanda ng activity sheet na naglalaman ng mga tanong at aktibidad na naglalayong mapalaganap ang silipikong edukasyon at makamasang edukasyon.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Role-Playing Activity sa Pagpapalaganap ng Edukasyon: Magdaos ng role-playing activity kung saan ang mga mag-aaral ay gaganap bilang mga guro, mag-aaral, o iba pang tauhan na nagtatrabaho upang palaganapin ang silipikong at makamasang edukasyon.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. PowerPoint Presentation sa Edukasyon at Kapakanan ng Bansa: Maghanda ng PowerPoint presentation na nagpapaliwanag kung paano maaaring gamitin ang edukasyon upang itaguyod ang kapakanan ng bansa\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Activity sheet na magagamit ng mga mag-aaral para sa pagsusuri at pagpapalaganap ng progresibong edukasyon.\\r\\n2. Feedback forms na magagamit ng mga mag-aaral para sa pagsusuri ng kanilang mga ginampanang role at mga natutunan mula sa activity.\\r\\n3. Discussion guide na magagamit ng guro sa klase para sa mga talakayan tungkol sa teorya ng mga Pilipino.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Sa pagtatapos ng panghuling pagsusulit, ang mag-aaral ay dapat na makasagot ng tama ng hindi bababa sa 50% ng kabuuang bilang ng mga aytem.\",\"Week 18\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Exam\"}',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,'Ang DALUMATFIL ay isang maagwat na kursong nagpapalawak at nagpapalalim sa kasanayan sa malalim at mapanuring pagbasa, pagsulat, at pananaliksik sa wikang Filipino sa iba’t ibang\r\nlarangan, sa konteksto ng kontemporaryong sitwasyon at mga pangangailangan ng bansa at ng mga mamamayang Pilipino. Partikular na nakatuon ang kursong ito sa makrokasanayang pagbasa\r\nat pagsulat, gamit ang mga makabuluhang pananaliksik sa wikang Filipino, bilang lunsaran ng pagpapalawak at pagpapalalim sa kasanayan, kakayahan at kamalayan ng mga estudyante na malikhain\r\nat mapanuring makapagdalumat o “makapag-teorya” sa wikang Filipino, batay sa mga piling lokal at dayuhang konsepto at teorya na akma sa konteksto ng komunidad at bansa.','[{\"pilo\":\"Proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies).\",\"ctpss\":\"p\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Understanding of basic concept across the domains of knowledge.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Application of different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative artistic and scientific textual and visual experimental, observation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Capacity to personally interpret the human experience.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Ability to view the contemporary world from both Philippine and global perspective.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Appreciation of human condition.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Basic work-related skills and knowledge.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Application of computing and information technology to assist and facilitate research\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Working effectively in a group.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"}]','[{\"cilo\":\"1. Maipaliwanag ang kahalagahan ng wikang Filipino sa pagdadalumat o pagteteorya.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"2. Matukoy ang mga mapagkakatiwalaan, makabuluhan at kapaki-pakinabang  na sanggunian sa pagdadalumat at pananaliksik.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"3. Malikhain at mapanuring makapag-ambag sa pagpapaliwanag at pagpapalawak ng piling makabuluhang konsepto at teoryang lokal at dayuhan na akma sa konteksto ng komunidad at bansa.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"4. Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga batayang kasanayan sa pananaliksik.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"5. Makapagbasa at makapagbuod ng impormasyon, estadistika, datos atbp. mula sa mga babasahing nakasulat sa Filipino sa iba\\u2019t iba ng larangan.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"6. Makapagsalin ng mga artikulo, pananaliksik atbp. na makapag-aambag sa patuloy na intelektwalisasyon ng wikang Filipino.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"7. Makapagpahayag ng mga makabuluhang kaisipan sa pamamagitan ng tradisyonal  at modernong midyang akma sa kontekstong Pilipino.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"8. Makagawa ng mga malikhain at mapanghikayat na presentasyon ng impormasyon  at analisis na akma sa iba\\u2019t ibang konteksto.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"9. Malinang ang Filipino bilang daluyan ng inter\\/multidisiplinaring pagdadalumat at pananaliksik na nakaugat sa mga realidad ng lipunang Pilipino.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"10. Makabuo ng isang sanaysay hinggil sa isang mungkahing rebisyon o ekspansyon ng isang umiiral na konsepto o teorya, o kaya\\u2019y isang mungkahing bagong konsepto o teorya na akam sa mga realidad ng lipunang Pilipino.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"11. Mapalalim ang pagpapahalaga sa sariling teorya ng mga Pilipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"12. Maisaalang-alang ang kultura at iba pang aspektong panlipunan sa pagsasagawa ng pananaliksik.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"13. Mapahalagahan ang dinamikong ugnayan ng teorya at praktika sa pananaliksik\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"14. Makapag-ambag sa pagtataguyod ng wikang Filipino bilang daluyan ng makabuluhan at mataas na antas ng diskurso na akma at nakaugat sa lipunang Pilipino, bilang wika ng pananaliksik na nakaayon sa pangangailangan ng komunidad at bansa\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"}]','General Education Program aims to:\r\nIntellectual competencies\r\n1. proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\r\n2. understanding of basic concept across the domains of knowledge\r\n3. application of different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative artistic and scientific textual and visual experimental,observation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically\r\nPersonal and civil responsibilities\r\n1. capacity to personally interpret the human experience\r\n2. ability to view the contemporary world from both Philippine and global perspective\r\n3. appreciation of human condition  \r\nPractical Skills\r\n1.  basic work-related skills and knowledge\r\n2. application of computing and information technology to assist and facilitate research\r\n3. working effectively in a group','Sa pagtatapos ng kurso, inaaasahang matututuhan ng mga mag-aaral ang mga sumusunod:\r\nKaalaman\r\n1. Maipaliwanag ang kahalagahan ng wikang Filipino sa pagdadalumat o pagteteorya.\r\n2. Matukoy ang mga mapagkakatiwalaan, makabuluhan at kapaki-pakinabang na sanggunian sa pagdadalumat at pananaliksik.\r\n3. Malikhain at mapanuring makapag-ambag sa pagpapaliwanag at pagpapalawak ng piling makabuluhang konsepto at teoryang lokal at dayuhan na akma sa konteksto ng komunidad at bansa.\r\nKasanayan\r\n4. Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga batayang kasanayan sa pananaliksik.\r\n5. Makapagbasa at makapagbuod ng impormasyon, estadistika, datos atbp. mula sa mga babasahing nakasulat sa Filipino sa iba’t iba ng larangan.\r\n6. Makapagsalin ng mga artikulo, pananaliksik atbp. na makapag-aambag sa patuloy na intelektwalisasyon ng wikang Filipino.\r\n7. Makapagpahayag ng mga makabuluhang kaisipan sa pamamagitan ng tradisyonal at modernong midyang akma sa kontekstong Pilipino.\r\n8. Makagawa ng mga malikhain at mapanghikayat na presentasyon ng impormasyon at analisis na akma sa iba’t ibang konteksto.\r\n9. Malinang ang Filipino bilang daluyan ng inter/multidisiplinaring pagdadalumat at pananaliksik na nakaugat sa mga realidad ng lipunang Pilipino.\r\n10. Makabuo ng isang sanaysay hinggil sa isang mungkahing rebisyon o ekspansyon ng isang umiiral na konsepto o teorya, o kaya’y isang mungkahing bagong konsepto o teorya na akam sa mga realidad ng lipunang Pilipino.\r\nHalagahan\r\n11. Mapalalim ang pagpapahalaga sa sariling teorya ng mga Pilipino sa iba’t ibang larangan.\r\n12. Maisaalang-alang ang kultura at iba pang aspektong panlipunan sa pagsasagawa ng pananaliksik.\r\n13. Mapahalagahan ang dinamikong ugnayan ng teorya at praktika sa pananaliksik\r\n14. Makapag-ambag sa pagtataguyod ng wikang Filipino bilang daluyan ng makabuluhan at mataas na antas ng diskurso na akma at nakaugat sa lipunang Pilipino, bilang wika ng pananaliksik na nakaayon sa pangangailangan ng komunidad at bansa','Narito ang tatlong inaasahang kakayahan na inaasahang makakamit ng mga estudyante sa pagtatapos ng kursong Dalumat ng/sa Filipino:\r\n1. Masuri ang papel ng wikang Filipino sa pagbuo at paggamit ng mga teoretikal na balangkas sa konteksto ng lipunang Pilipino.\r\n2. Maipamalas ang kakayahang kritikal na suriin at malikhaing makapag-ambag sa pagpapalawak ng mga lokal at dayuhang konsepto at teorya, tinitiyak ang kanilang\r\nkaugnayan sa komunidad at bansa.\r\n3. Magamit ang kasanayan sa pananaliksik upang epektibong matukoy at masuri ang mapagkakatiwalaang sanggunian sa pagsusulong at intelektwalisasyon ng wikang\r\nFilipino sa iba\'t ibang larangan.','CHED MEMO NO.57, Series of 2017 at MGA SILABUS SA, FILIPINO\r\nRubin et. Al., 2018, Retorika (Pandalukhasa)','BCP Learning Management System https.: bcpeducollege.leamingcommons.com/course/view.php?id=2171 Rubin et. Al., 2018 , Retorika (Pandalukhasa)','Student must be able to:\r\n1. complete at least 80% of student participation;\r\n2. demonstrate punctuality according to his/her schedule; and,\r\n3. accomplish alternative assessment (if needed)\r\n    3.1. when student fail to comply or perform poorly in a major examination and/or non-participation because of valid reason e.g. health, force majeure needs to provide alternative assessment such as project, presentation, oral examination, and research output.','Cluster Leader: \r\nMs. Michelle Arias, LPT\r\n\r\nMember:\r\nMs. Meredel Ansong, LPT','Cluster Leader:\r\nMs. Michelle Arias, LPT\r\nEmail Address: ariasmichellesison@gmail.com \r\nConsultation Hours: \r\nMonday-Tuesday, 8:30AM-10:30AM\r\nTime and Venue: MV Faculty-5TH FLOOR\r\n\r\nFaculty Member:\r\nMs. Meredel Ansong, LPT \r\nEmail Address: ansongmeredel@gmail.com \r\nConsultation Hours: \r\nMonday-Tuesday, 1PM-2:30PM\r\nTime and Venue: MV Faculty-5TH FLOOR','MICHELLE ARIAS, LPT','MICHAEL L. BERSAMIN, LPT','CHARLIE I. CARIÑO, Ph.D.','2026-02-06 15:33:21','2026-02-06 15:33:21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(35,'GE 1','UNDERSTANDING THE SELF','Minor','General Education','CHED',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'{\"Week 0\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives, Philosophy and School Organizational Structure School Policies Orientation in Online and Modular Learning System,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nRecite, internalize and explain the BCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives and Philosophy\\r\\nDeepen knowledge on the school\'s policies, guidelines, rules and regulations.\\r\\nFamiliarize on the new normal system of education through online, modular learning system and Blended Learning Delivery Modality (BLDM),, Assessment: ONSITE: Identify the Vision and Mission statements of BCP.\\r\\nCritically analyze these statements in 500 words, focusing on the following:\\r\\nThe clarity and coherence of the statements.\\r\\nHow these statements reflect the school\'s commitment to education.\\r\\nThe alignment of these statements with the current educational landscape.\\r\\nVerify that the BCP VMGO are align with the school goals thru checklist (PMED tools) OFFSITE: Navigate LMS and know the function of each feature.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Read and internalize the following printed materials for Students and Parents Orientation: OFF-SITE: Presentation and Lecture Discussion (PowerPoint Presentation) of Students and Parents Orientation:,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nInstructional Materials\\r\\nVideo Presentation of BCP Hymn\\r\\nYouTube Video Title: BESTLINK COLLEGE OF THE PHILIPPINES HYMN (BCP hymn)\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NuEYO11Wb4E\\r\\nStudent Hand Book\\r\\nLearning Management System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCheck alignment report\",\"Week 1\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Self from\\r\\nVarious Perspectives\\r\\n\\r\\nPhilosophers:\\r\\n1.Socrates\\r\\n2.Plato\\r\\n3.St. Augustine\\r\\n4. Rene Descartes\\r\\n5.John Locke,\\r\\n6.David Hume\\r\\n7.Immanuel Kant\\r\\n8.Sigmund Freud\\r\\n9.Gilbert Ryle\\r\\n10.Maurice Merleau-Ponty\\r\\n11. Paul Churchland\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Analyze and compare the different representations and conceptualizations of the self from various philosophical perspectives.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on and articulate personal responses to the influences, factors, and forces that shape their own self-identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Create a visual or multimedia presentation that illustrates the evolution of self-concept according to the discussed philosophers.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Read and analyze all the perspectives from various philosophers.\\r\\n2. Get familiarized with all the philosophers and their beliefs.\\r\\n3. Participate in a group discussion to critically evaluate and present the influences of these philosophers on modern understandings of self and identity.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 1 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Preliminary Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Watch the personality test video and discuss in groups whether the results align with their self-perception and why.\\r\\n\\r\\nMyers-Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI) Personality Test\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=j2fWj5bXbmo \\r\\n\\r\\nLink of MBTI Personality Test:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.truity.com\\/test\\/type-finder-personality-test-new \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Discussion:\\r\\n2.1. Analyze the perspectives from various philosophers through interactive lectures.\\r\\n2.2. Create a timeline mapping the evolution of self-concept through the discussed philosophers.\\r\\n2.3. Facilitate a debate on the relevance of these philosophical perspectives in the digital age, integrating AI\'s impact on self-identity\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: pages 1-20 \\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nYouTube Video: Myers-Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI) Personality Test\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=j2fWj5bXbmo \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Multimedia Content relevant to the philosophers and theories discussed\\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Write a reflective essay on how understanding different philosophical perspectives on self can influence personal growth.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of the philosophical perspectives and their contributions to self-concept.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\n3.1 Group presentations on the evolution of self-concept.\\r\\n3.2 Forum discussions on integrating AI in understanding self and identity.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 2\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSociology\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Self in Modern Society\\r\\n2. Social Construction\\r\\n3. Modernity and the Self.\\r\\n4. Theory of \\r\\nStructuration\\r\\n5. Reflexive Process of Self-Identify\\r\\n6. Modern Self and Lifestyle Choice\\r\\n7. Mead and the Social Self\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Compare and contrast how the self has been represented across the different disciplines and perspectives.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on personal experiences and relate them to the theory of structuration and the concept of the modern self.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Create a digital or physical graphic organizer that illustrates the relationship between social constructs and self-identity.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Peer-to-peer discussion of current situations or past experiences related to the topic.\\r\\n2. Answer Activities No. 3 on page 34; and No. 4 pages 40-41.\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 2 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Provide different words related to the concept of Sociology using a graphic organizer.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1. Watch a video for additional information: YouTube Video\\r\\n\\r\\nSociology and Self:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=vzXFAiXnfGU  \\r\\n\\r\\n2.2. Interactive Discussion: Relate their current situation or past experiences related to the topic.\\r\\n\\r\\n2.3. Group Activity: Create a presentation on how modernity and social constructs influence self-identity, incorporating digital tools and multimedia elemen\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books:  pages 23-40\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nYouTube Video: \\r\\n\\r\\nSociology and Self:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=vzXFAiXnfGU \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Multimedia Content relevant to the sociology and self-identity topics\\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Write a reflective essay on how understanding different sociological perspectives on self can influence personal and social development.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of the sociological perspectives and their contributions to self-concept.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nGroup presentations on the relationship between social constructs and self-identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 3\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nAnthropology\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Well-Known Philosophers\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Self, Person and Personhood\\r\\nSelf and Culture\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Social Class and Culture.\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Demonstrate critical and reflective thought in analyzing the development of one\\u2019s self and identity by developing a theory of the self.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Differentiate social classes and their roles in society, reflecting on personal beliefs and values.\\r\\n \\r\\n3. Create a visual representation (e.g., infographic, poster) that illustrates the relationship between self, culture, and social class.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Present a list of well-known philosophers who conceptualized anthropology and discuss their social class and culture in class.\\r\\n2. Answer Activity No. 6 on pages 59-60.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 3 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: \\r\\n1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Enumerate all the well-known philosophers who conceptualized anthropology.\\r\\n1.2. Determine their social class and culture.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1. Critique the video of Bamboo\\u2019s song \\u201cTatsulok\\u201d \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nLink to Video:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=hI3T_D8TCUk \\r\\n\\r\\n2.2. Group Activity: \\r\\nCreate an interactive presentation on the influence of social class and culture on self-identity using digital tools.\\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: pages 43-59\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nYouTube Video: Bamboo \\u2013 Tatsulok\\r\\nLink to Lyrics:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.songlyrics.com\\/bamboo\\/tatsulok-lyrics\\/\\r\\n\\r\\nLink to Video:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=hI3T_D8TCUk \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Multimedia Content relevant to anthropology and self-identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Write a reflective essay on the impact of culture and social class on self-identity, referencing specific philosophers.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess knowledge on well-known philosophers, their social class, and culture.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nGroup presentations on how culture and social class influence self-identity.\\r\\n4. Forum discussions on personal experiences related to social class and culture.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 4\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPsychology\\r\\n\\r\\n1. I and Me\\r\\n2. Real Self and Ideal Self\\r\\n3. Multiple and Unified Self\\r\\n4. True and False Self\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Analyze the diversity of self-representations in society and compare them across different contexts.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on personal experiences and identify how different aspects of the self (real, ideal, multiple, unified, true, false) manifest in these experiences.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Create a digital storytelling project that illustrates the diversity of the self in different societal contexts, using AI tools for enhanced storytelling.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Compare all the diversity of \\\"self\\\" in our society using Venn Diagrams.\\r\\n2. Think-Pair-Share the cases and experiences when they can relate to a particular self in society.\\r\\n3. Answer Activity No. 7 on pages 74-76.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 4 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Differentiate all the diversity of \\\"self\\\" in our society using Venn Diagrams.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lesson Proper:\\r\\n2.1. Interactive discussion on the concept of self-diversity.\\r\\n2.2. Share cases and experiences when they can relate to a particular self in society.\\r\\n2.3. Group Activity: Create a digital storytelling project using AI tools to illustrate the diversity of the self in different societal contexts.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: pages 61-74\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nThat Little Voice https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=Ll56imVATLk \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Multimedia Content relevant to the diversity of self-representations\\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Write a reflective essay on the diversity of self-representations in society and how they manifest in personal experiences.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess knowledge on different aspects of the self (real, ideal, multiple, unified, true, false) and their societal implications.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nGroup presentations on digital storytelling projects illustrating the diversity of the self in different societal contexts.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n 1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio\",\"Week 5\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Self in Western and Oriental \\/ Eastern Thought\\r\\n\\r\\n1.Individualistic Self & Collective Self\\r\\n2. Self-Construction of Self\\r\\n3. Self and Confucianism\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Analyze the differences between Individualistic and Collective Self in various cultural contexts.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on personal and cultural influences on self-construction and how this shape individual identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Create a multimedia presentation illustrating the impact of Confucianism on self-construction in Eastern cultures, using digital tools and AI for enhanced visuals.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. 1. Write an essay about the differences between Individualistic and Collective Self.\\r\\n2. Answer Activity No. 8 on pages 94-95 and Activity 9 on pages 101-102.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 5 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Describe the differences between Individualistic and Collective Self.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lesson Proper:\\r\\n2.1. Interactive discussion on the impact of individualistic and collective cultural perspectives on self-construction.\\r\\n2.2. Discuss the concept of Confucianism and its influence on the self in Eastern cultures.\\r\\n2.3. Group Activity: Create a multimedia presentation illustrating the impact of Confucianism on self-construction in Eastern cultures, using digital tools and AI for enhanced visuals.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: pages 77-101\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nUnderstanding Collectivism and Individualism\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=RT-bZ33yB3c \\r\\n\\r\\n6. Multimedia Content relevant to the differences between individualistic and Collective Self in various cultural contexts\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\n\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Write a reflective essay on the impact of individualistic and collective perspectives on self-construction.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess knowledge on the concepts of individualistic and collective self, and Confucianism\\u2019s influence on self-construction.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nGroup presentations on multimedia projects illustrating the impact of Confucianism on self-construction in Eastern cultures.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 6\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPrelim Exam\",\"Week 7\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\n\\r\\nPhysical Self\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Body Adornment and Its Types\\r\\n2. Body Modification and Its Types\\r\\n3. Context of Beauty\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Analyze and evaluate different aspects of body adornment and modification across cultures.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on personal beliefs and societal standards of beauty, and how they influence self-identity and self-esteem.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Create a digital collage representing various forms of body adornment and modification, incorporating elements from different cultures.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Participate in a question-and-answer session about beauty.\\r\\n2. Analyze body adornment, body modification, and their types.\\r\\n3. Answer Activity No. 10 on page 111, Activity 11 on page 115, and Activity 12 on pages 121-122.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 7 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Provide different words related to the word \\\"BEAUTY\\\" in a graphic organizer.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1. Watch a documentary on societal beauty standards and discuss its implications.\\r\\n\\r\\nBeauty - Documentary on Societal Beauty Standards\\r\\nLink to the Video:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=8eAL4JNQQU8 \\r\\n\\r\\n2.2. Analyze the types of body adornment and body modification and their cultural significance.\\r\\n2.3. Group Activity: Create a digital collage representing various forms of body adornment and modification, incorporating elements\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference:                 pages 103-120 Books:Magpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nBeauty - Documentary on Societal Beauty Standards\\r\\nLink to the Video:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=8eAL4JNQQU8 \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Multimedia Content relevant to body adornment and modification\\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on how body adornment and modification practices affect self-identity and societal perceptions of beauty.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess knowledge and understanding of body adornment, body modification, and their cultural contexts.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nGroup Task: Watch and discuss a documentary on societal beauty standards, then create a presentation on how these standards impact personal identity and self-esteem.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 8\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSexual Self\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Sexual Self\\r\\n2. Reproductive System\\r\\n3. Biological Changes in Men and Women\\r\\n4. Phases of the Sexual Response Cycle\\r\\n5. Response Cycle\\r\\n6. Psychosexual Stages\\r\\n7. Erogenous Zone\\r\\n8. Biology of Love and Attraction\\r\\n9. Diversity of Sexual Behaviors\\r\\n10. Gender Sensitivity, Identity, and Sexual Orientation\\r\\n11. HIV\\/AIDS\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Examine how various influences and organizations shape different elements of self and identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Contemplate the significance of comprehending one\'s sexual self and its effect on personal identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Develop an engaging and educational presentation about HIV\\/AIDS, highlighting its symptoms, modes of transmission, and methods of prevention\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. List down important notes on the signs, symptoms, transmission, and causes of HIV\\/AIDS.\\r\\n2. Answer Activity 13 on pages 132-133, Activity 14 on pages 141-142, Activity 15 on pages 149-150, and Activity 16 on pages 166-167.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 8&9 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Show and explain a picture of the reproductive system.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1. Watch and discuss a video on biological changes in men and women.\\r\\n\\r\\nBiological Changes\\r\\nLink to Video:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=TlfsGKDoVIQ \\r\\n\\r\\n2.2. Explain the phases of the sexual response cycle and the psychosexual stages.\\r\\n2.3. Group Activity: Create an interactive presentation on the biology of love and attraction, incorporating multimedia elements.\\r\\n2.4. Interactive Q&A on the diversity of sexual behaviors.\\r\\n2.5. Conduct a role-playing activity on how to educate peers about HIV\\/AIDS, focusing on prevention and stigma reduction.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: \\r\\npages 123-166 \\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nYouTube Video: \\r\\nBiological Changes\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=TlfsGKDoVIQ \\r\\n\\r\\nHIV\\/AIDS Transmission\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=5g1ijpBI6Dk \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on the influence of biological changes and societal expectations on self-identity and sexual behavior.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of the reproductive system, biological changes in men and women, and the phases of the sexual response cycle.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nPair Activity: Develop a peer education program on HIV\\/AIDS, including role-playing scenarios to practice communication and educational skills.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n 1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 9\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSexual Self\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Sexual Self\\r\\n2. Reproductive System\\r\\n3. Biological Changes in Men and Women\\r\\n4. Phases of the Sexual Response Cycle\\r\\n5. Response Cycle\\r\\n6. Psychosexual Stages\\r\\n7. Erogenous Zone\\r\\n8. Biology of Love and Attraction\\r\\n9. Diversity of Sexual Behaviors\\r\\n10. Gender Sensitivity, Identity, and Sexual Orientation\\r\\n11. HIV\\/AIDS\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Examine how various influences and organizations shape different elements of self and identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Contemplate the significance of comprehending one\'s sexual self and its effect on personal identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Develop an engaging and educational presentation about HIV\\/AIDS, highlighting its symptoms, modes of transmission, and methods of prevention\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. List down important notes on the signs, symptoms, transmission, and causes of HIV\\/AIDS.\\r\\n2. Answer Activity 13 on pages 132-133, Activity 14 on pages 141-142, Activity 15 on pages 149-150, and Activity 16 on pages 166-167.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 8&9 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1. Show and explain a picture of the reproductive system.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1. Watch and discuss a video on biological changes in men and women.\\r\\n\\r\\nBiological Changes\\r\\nLink to Video:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=TlfsGKDoVIQ \\r\\n\\r\\n2.2. Explain the phases of the sexual response cycle and the psychosexual stages.\\r\\n2.3. Group Activity: Create an interactive presentation on the biology of love and attraction, incorporating multimedia elements.\\r\\n2.4. Interactive Q&A on the diversity of sexual behaviors.\\r\\n2.5. Conduct a role-playing activity on how to educate peers about HIV\\/AIDS, focusing on prevention and stigma reduction.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: \\r\\npages 123-166 \\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nYouTube Video: \\r\\nBiological Changes\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=TlfsGKDoVIQ \\r\\n\\r\\nHIV\\/AIDS Transmission\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=5g1ijpBI6Dk \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on the influence of biological changes and societal expectations on self-identity and sexual behavior.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of the reproductive system, biological changes in men and women, and the phases of the sexual response cycle.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nPair Activity: Develop a peer education program on HIV\\/AIDS, including role-playing scenarios to practice communication and educational skills.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n 1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 10\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Material\\/ Economic Self\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Comparing Solid & Liquid Consumption\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Psychology of Buying\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Thoroughly examine and distinguish between the consumption of solid and liquid items, and their effects on identity and self-perception.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Consider individual purchasing behaviors and the psychological factors that influence them.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Create a multimedia presentation on the psychology of purchasing, integrating digital technologies and AI components.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Pre-Activity: Compare and contrast solid and liquid consumption using a Venn Diagram.\\r\\n2. Lesson Proper:\\r\\n2.1 Interactive discussion on solid and liquid consumption.\\r\\n2.2 Delineate the psychology of buying and its daily life reflections through a multimedia presentation created by students in pairs.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 10 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1 Compare and contrast solid and liquid consumption using a Venn Diagram.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lesson Proper:\\r\\n2.1 Conduct an interactive discussion on the differences and impacts of solid and liquid consumption.\\r\\n2.2 Watch and discuss a video on the psychology of buying.\\r\\n2.3 Group Activity: Create and present a multimedia project on the psychology of buying, including digital tools and AI-generated content. Each group should analyze different marketing strategies and their psychological impacts on consumers.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: \\r\\npages 169-180\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nImportance of Consumer Behavior: Understanding the Buying Mind\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=s-t-PqOaX1E \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Multimedia Content relevant to the Psychology of Buying\\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on personal buying habits and the psychological factors influencing them.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of the psychology of buying and the differences between solid and liquid consumption.\\r\\n3. Group Project: \\r\\nDevelop a multimedia presentation on the psychology of buying, using AI tools for visual aids and analysis. Each group should focus on a different aspect of consumer behavior, such as advertising tactics, online shopping trends, or the impact of social media influencers.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in\",\"Week 11\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSpiritual Self\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Filipino Culture & Religion\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Filipino Belief & Values\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Spirituality & Meaning of Life\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Assess the effect of Filipino cultural, religious, and value systems on one\'s spiritual identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on how one\'s own spiritual beliefs compare to or contrast with the broader Filipino cultural and religious practices.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Design a digital presentation that illustrates the range of spiritual beliefs and practices found within Filipino culture.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group discussion on the influence of Filipino culture and religion on individual spiritual beliefs.\\r\\n2. Interactive presentation on different Filipino cultural and religious practices.\\r\\n3. Create a graphic organizer detailing the different aspects of spirituality and the meaning of life as influenced by Filipino culture.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 11 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1 Watch the movie \\u201cDed na si Lolo\\u201d that highlights different beliefs, cultures, and traditions. Write a reflection on the movie. \\r\\n\\r\\nMovie Link:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=5kLf-jwDJB0 \\r\\n\\r\\nLecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1 Conduct an interactive discussion on the different Filipino cultures, religions, beliefs, and values.\\r\\n2.2 Create a group project where students research and present on different aspects of Filipino spirituality, incorporating digital tools and multimedia elements.\\r\\n2.3 Use a graphic organizer to explore and discuss various interpretations of the meaning of life in Filipino culture.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: \\r\\npages 183-196\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\n\\u201cDed na si Lolo\\u201d Movie Link:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=5kLf-jwDJB0 \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on how personal spiritual beliefs align with or differ from broader Filipino cultural and religious practices.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of Filipino cultural and religious practices and their influence on the spiritual self.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nInteractive Discussion: Explore and discuss the meaning of life as influenced by Filipino culture, creating a collaborative graphic organizer.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 12\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMidterm Exam\",\"Week 13\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Political Self\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Three Major Types of Government\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Individuals & The State\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Analyze the theoretical foundations of different government systems and their influence on the individual and society.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on how personal values correspond with different forms of government and the individual\'s relationship with the state.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Produce a digital presentation or video detailing the primary features of the three major types of government.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Think-Pair-Share about your ideas of what kind of Ideal Government we should have.\\r\\n2. Discuss the relationship between individuals and the state.\\r\\n3. Answer Activity 20 on page 207 and Activity 21 on pages 208-209.\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 13 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity (Q & A - Debate)\\r\\n1.1 Engage in a debate on the type of government we currently have and discuss its strengths and weaknesses.\\r\\n1.2 Recitation among students to share initial thoughts and perspectives.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1 Conduct an interactive lecture on the three major types of government.\\r\\n2.2 Explain the relationship between individuals and the state through case studies and real-life examples.\\r\\n2.3 Facilitate group discussions where students compare the different types of government and their implications on personal and societal levels.\\r\\n2.4 Use AI tools to simulate different government structures and analyze their impact on societal well-being\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books:\\r\\nPages 197-207\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Online Resources:\\r\\nPOLITICAL Self | Origins: Family, Church, Peers, and Social & Mass Media | Understanding the Self: \\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=4hdEHzq0kYs \\r\\n\\r\\n6. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on how different types of government influence individual identity and societal values.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of the three major types of government and the relationship between individuals and the state.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nGroup Project: Research and create a digital simulation or presentation on different types of government, utilizing AI tools to model their impact on society.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in\",\"Week 14\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Digital Self\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Self-Presentation\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Self-Disclosure vs. Public Self\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Impression Management\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Managing the Digital Self\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Examine how digital environments influence self-presentation and identity management.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Consider how your online self-presentation aligns with your personal values and identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Develop a multimedia presentation on effective strategies for managing your digital identity.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Think-Pair-Share activity about personal experiences with digital self-presentation.\\r\\n2. Group presentation on effective digital self-management strategies.\\r\\n3. Reflective essay on the relationship between self-disclosure and public self in digital environments.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 14&15 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1 Discussion on the differences between Self-Disclosure and Public Self.\\r\\n1.2 Share first impressions about chosen classmates and discuss the impact of first impressions on digital self-presentation.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1 Interactive lecture on impression management and strategies for managing the digital self.\\r\\n2.2 Group activity: Create and present a multimedia project on digital self-management.\\r\\n2.3 Debate: Discuss the ethical implications of digital self-presentation and management.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: \\r\\npages 211-226\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nImpression Management and Self-Monitoring | Intro to Human Communication | Study Hall\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=uDsLm3O-4GI \\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on the ethical considerations of digital self-presentation.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of self-presentation, self-disclosure, and impression management in digital environments.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nIndividual Task: Create a blog post or social media profile that reflects personal values and identity, demonstrating effective self-management.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in\",\"Week 15\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Digital Self\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Self-Presentation\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Self-Disclosure vs. Public Self\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Impression Management\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Managing the Digital Self\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Examine how digital environments influence self-presentation and identity management.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Consider how your online self-presentation aligns with your personal values and identity.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Develop a multimedia presentation on effective strategies for managing your digital identity.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Think-Pair-Share activity about personal experiences with digital self-presentation.\\r\\n2. Group presentation on effective digital self-management strategies.\\r\\n3. Reflective essay on the relationship between self-disclosure and public self in digital environments.\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 14&15 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1 Discussion on the differences between Self-Disclosure and Public Self.\\r\\n1.2 Share first impressions about chosen classmates and discuss the impact of first impressions on digital self-presentation.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1 Interactive lecture on impression management and strategies for managing the digital self.\\r\\n2.2 Group activity: Create and present a multimedia project on digital self-management.\\r\\n2.3 Debate: Discuss the ethical implications of digital self-presentation and management.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books: \\r\\npages 211-226\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Online Resources:\\r\\nImpression Management and Self-Monitoring | Intro to Human Communication | Study Hall\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=uDsLm3O-4GI \\r\\n\\r\\n7. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on the ethical considerations of digital self-presentation.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of self-presentation, self-disclosure, and impression management in digital environments.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nIndividual Task: Create a blog post or social media profile that reflects personal values and identity, demonstrating effective self-management.\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 16\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nManaging and Caring for the Self\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning to be a Better Student\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Learning Strategies and Techniques\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Metacognition\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Setting Goals for Success\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Health, Stress, and Coping\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Kinds of Stressors\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Coping Strategies\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Evaluate and apply various learning strategies and techniques to enhance academic performance and personal growth.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on personal stressors and coping strategies, sharing insights with peers to foster mutual support.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Develop a personalized action plan for managing stress and achieving academic and personal goals.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Think-Pair-Share: Share your effective learning style and discuss its benefits with a partner.\\r\\n2. Write your #POTD (Problem of the Day) and let other students give their advice on it.\\r\\n3. Answer Activities 23 (page 255), 24 (pages 256-257), and Activity 25 (pages 263; 269; 275). \\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 16&17 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1 Discuss various learning strategies and techniques and how they can be applied.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1 Interactive discussion on metacognition with real-life examples shared by students.\\r\\n2.2 Activity: Students write down a personal #POTD and share it with the class for group advice.\\r\\n2.3 Group workshop: Develop stress management plans and set personal goals for academic success.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books:\\r\\npages 229-269\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Multimedia content on learning strategies and metacognition.\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Online Resources:\\r\\nStudy Skills & Evidence-Based Learning Strategies\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=d7viLjsHruY \\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on personal stressors and coping mechanisms, including peer advice received during class.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of learning strategies, metacognition, and stress management techniques.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nIndividual Task: Develop and present a personal action plan for managing stress and setting goals.\\r\\nGroup Task: Conduct a workshop on effective stress management techniques and goal-setting strategies, presenting it to the class.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 17\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nManaging and Caring for the Self\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning to be a Better Student\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Learning Strategies and Techniques\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Metacognition\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Setting Goals for Success\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Health, Stress, and Coping\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Kinds of Stressors\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Coping Strategies\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Evaluate and apply various learning strategies and techniques to enhance academic performance and personal growth.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Reflect on personal stressors and coping strategies, sharing insights with peers to foster mutual support.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Develop a personalized action plan for managing stress and achieving academic and \\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Think-Pair-Share: Share your effective learning style and discuss its benefits with a partner.\\r\\n2. Write your #POTD (Problem of the Day) and let other students give their advice on it.\\r\\n3. Answer Activities 23 (page 255), 24 (pages 256-257), and Activity 25 (pages 263; 269; 275).\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 16&17 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pre-Activity:\\r\\n1.1 Discuss various learning strategies and techniques and how they can be applied.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Lecture Discussion:\\r\\n2.1 Interactive discussion on metacognition with real-life examples shared by students.\\r\\n2.2 Activity: Students write down a personal #POTD and share it with the class for group advice.\\r\\n2.3 Group workshop: Develop stress management plans and set personal goals for academic success.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n    1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\n1. Textbooks and Reference Books:\\r\\npages 229-269\\r\\nMagpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): BCP LMS\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Internet Connection\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Network Access Account\\r\\n\\r\\n5. Lecture Notes and PowerPoint Slides\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Multimedia content on learning strategies and metacognition.\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Online Resources:\\r\\nStudy Skills & Evidence-Based Learning Strategies\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=d7viLjsHruY \\r\\n\\r\\n8. Daily Learning Plan\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1. Assignment: Reflective essay on personal stressors and coping mechanisms, including peer advice received during class.\\r\\n2. Quiz Objectives: Assess understanding of learning strategies, metacognition, and stress management techniques.\\r\\n3. Class Activity:\\r\\nIndividual Task: Develop and present a personal action plan for managing stress and setting goals.\\r\\nGroup Task: Conduct a workshop on effective stress management techniques and goal-setting strategies, presenting it to the class.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Compile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 18\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Exam\"}',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,'This Course deals in acquiring fundamentals skills in nature of identity and forces that affect the development and maintenance of personal identity. Adolescence is a developmental stage commonly thought to be a time of physical, emotional, and psychological vulnerability. Foremost among the concerns of this life stage are issues of self and identity. The course is intended to enable the process of exploration and thereby help students arrive at an understanding of the concepts of personality, self and identity. (CMO No. 20, S.2023)','[{\"pilo\":\"Proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Understanding of basic concept across the domains of knowledge.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Application of different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative artistic and scientific textual and visual experimental, observation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Capacity to personally interpret the human experience.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Ability to view the contemporary world from both Philippine and global perspective.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Appreciation of human condition.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Basic work-related skills and knowledge\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Application of computing and information technology to assist and facilitate research\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"}]','[{\"cilo\":\"Application of computing and information technology to assist and facilitate researc\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Compare and contrast how the self has been represented across different disciplines and perspectives.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\". Examine the different influences, factors, and forces that shape the self.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Demonstrate critical and reflective thought in analyzing the development of one\'s self and identity by developing a theory of the self.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"Demonstrate critical, reflective thought in integrating the various aspects of self and identity.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"Identify the different forces and institutions that impact the development of various aspects of self and identity.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Examine one\'s self against the different aspects of self-discussed in class.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"Understand the theoretical underpinnings for how to manage and care for different aspects of the self\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Understand the theoretical underpinnings for how to manage and care for different aspects of the self\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"Acquire and hone new skills and learnings for better managing o\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Apply these new skills to one\'s self and functioning for a better quality of life\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"}]','General Education Program aims to:\r\n Intellectual competencies\r\n 1. proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\r\n 2. understanding of basic concept across the domains of knowledge\r\n 3. application of different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative artistic and scientific textual and visual experimental, observation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically\r\n Personal and civil responsibilities\r\n  1. capacity to personally interpret the human experience\r\n  2. ability to view the contemporary world from both Philippine and global perspective\r\n3. appreciation of human condition  \r\n                                                                       Practical Skills\r\n                                                                   1.  basic work-related skills and knowledge\r\n                                                                   2. application of computing and information technology to assist and facilitate research\r\n                                                                   3. working effectively in a group','At the end of the course, the students will be able to:\r\n\r\nThe Self from Various Perspectives\r\n1. Discuss the different representations and conceptualizations of the self from various disciplinal perspectives\r\n2. Compare and contrast how the self has been represented across different disciplines and perspectives\r\n3. Examine the different influences, factors, and forces that shape the self\r\n4. Demonstrate critical and reflective thought in analyzing the development of one\'s self and identity by developing a theory of the self\r\nUnpacking The Self\r\n5. Explore the different aspects of self and identity\r\n6. Demonstrate critical, reflective thought in integrating the various aspects of self and identity\r\n7. Identify the different forces and institutions that impact the development of various aspects of self and identity\r\n8. Examine one\'s self against the different aspects of self-discussed in class\r\nManaging and Caring for The Self\r\n9. Understand the theoretical underpinnings for how to manage and care for different aspects of the self\r\n10. Acquire and hone new skills and learnings for better managing of one\'s self and behaviors\r\n11. Apply these new skills to one\'s self and functioning for a better quality of life','At the end of this course, student should be able to:\r\n\r\n\r\ndevelop proficient and effective communication skills by articulating the various perspectives on the self, utilizing both written and oral communication, and integrating new technologies to present these ideas clearly and cohesively.\r\napply analytical modes by critically examining and contrasting different representations and conceptualizations of the self across various disciplines, employing both quantitative and qualitative methods to explore the influences and factors shaping identity; and\r\ninterpret the human experience and appreciate the human condition by reflecting on personal experiences in relation to the broader societal and global contexts, fostering an understanding of the self that is informed by both local and global perspectives.','Magpantay, C.D., & Danao, R.R. (2018). Understanding the Self. Rizal: Jenher Publishing House.','BCP Learning Management System (LMS):  https://bcpeducollege.elearningcommons.com/login/index.php \r\nOnline Resources: YouTube, etc.','Student must be able to:\r\n1. complete at least 80% of student participation;\r\n2. demonstrate punctuality according to his/her schedule; and,\r\n3. accomplish alternative assessment (if needed)\r\n    3.1. when student fail to comply or perform poorly in a major examination and/or non-participation because of valid reason e.g. health, force majeure needs to provide alternative assessment such as project, presentation, oral examination, and research output.','Cluster Leader: \r\nMs. Eliza O. Gomba, LPT\r\n\r\nMember:\r\nMs. Divine Grace S. Rapsing, LPT','Cluster Leader:\r\nMs. Eliza O. Gomba, LPT\r\nEmail Address: missyelayg.bcps@gmail.com \r\nConsultation Hours: \r\nMonday-Thursday, 3-5PM\r\nTime and Venue: General Education Office\r\n\r\nFaculty Member:\r\nMs. Divine Grace Rapsing\r\nEmail Address: rapsingdivine.12@gmail.com \r\nConsultation Hours: \r\nMonday, 1PM-7PM\r\nTime and Venue: CRAD Office','ELIZA O. GOMBA, LPT','MICHAEL L. BERSAMIN, LPT','CHARLIE I. CARIÑO, Ph.D.','2026-02-06 16:01:21','2026-02-06 16:01:21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(36,'GE 3','THE CONTEMPORARY WORLD','Minor','General Education','CHED',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'{\"Week 0\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives, Philosophy and School Organizational Structure School Policies Orientation in Online and Modular Learning System,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nRecite, internalize and explain the BCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives and Philosophy\\r\\nDeepen knowledge on the school\'s policies, guidelines, rules and regulations.\\r\\nFamiliarize on the new normal system of education through online, modular learning system and Blended Learning Delivery Modality (BLDM),, Assessment: ONSITE: Identify the Vision and Mission statements of BCP.\\r\\nCritically analyze these statements in 500 words, focusing on the following:\\r\\nThe clarity and coherence of the statements.\\r\\nHow these statements reflect the school\'s commitment to education.\\r\\nThe alignment of these statements with the current educational landscape.\\r\\nVerify that the BCP VMGO are align with the school goals thru checklist (PMED tools) OFFSITE: Navigate LMS and know the function of each feature.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Read and internalize the following printed materials for Students and Parents Orientation: OFF-SITE: Presentation and Lecture Discussion (PowerPoint Presentation) of Students and Parents Orientation:,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nInstructional Materials\\r\\nVideo Presentation of BCP Hymn\\r\\nYouTube Video Title: BESTLINK COLLEGE OF THE PHILIPPINES HYMN (BCP hymn)\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NuEYO11Wb4E\\r\\nStudent Hand Book\\r\\nLearning Management System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCheck alignment report\",\"Week 1\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nIntroduction to The Contemporary World: Understanding Globalization,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Define globalization from various perspectives. 2. Articulate their initial understanding and personal experiences of globalization. 3. Discuss the relevance of studying globalization in the contemporary era (2026 context).,, Assessment: ONSITE: Oral Recitation: Sharing personal definitions of globalization. OFFSITE: Pre-course Survey\\/Questionnaire on global awareness and experiences.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive Lecture-Discussion on the etymology and various definitions of globalization. Brainstorming session: \'What does globalization mean to me?\' OFF-SITE: Video Watching: \'What is Globalization?\' (e.g., a short documentary or explainer video). Online Reading: Introductory articles on globalization.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nCourse Syllabus, PowerPoint Presentation: \'Introduction to Globalization\'. Video URL: \'Globalization Explained\' (e.g., from World Economic Forum). Online article links.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nPersonal definition of globalization (short paragraph).\",\"Week 2\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nTheories and Dimensions of Globalization,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Differentiate between various theories of globalization (e.g., world-systems theory, hyperglobalist, skeptical, transformationalist). 2. Identify the different dimensions of globalization (economic, political, socio-cultural, environmental, technological). 3. Provide examples of each dimension in contemporary society.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Group Activity: \'Globalization Dimensions Scavenger Hunt\' (identifying real-world examples). Short Quiz on key terms and theories. OFFSITE: Reflection Paper: \'Which theory of globalization best explains today\'s world?\',, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on major theories of globalization. Small Group Discussion: Analyzing case studies representing different dimensions. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Chapters\\/articles on globalization theories and dimensions. Forum Discussion: Posting and commenting on the chosen theory.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 1 & 2. Handouts on globalization theories. Case study examples (news articles, short reports). Learning Management System (LMS) discussion board.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCompleted \'Globalization Dimensions\' worksheet. Reflection Paper (500 words).\",\"Week 3\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nEconomic Globalization: Global Market and Trade,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Explain the evolution and mechanisms of economic globalization. 2. Analyze the role of international financial institutions (e.g., WTO, IMF, World Bank) in global trade. 3. Evaluate the impacts of global economic integration on different countries, particularly developing nations.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Debate: \'Is free trade truly beneficial for all nations?\' OFFSITE: Research Paper Outline: \'Impact of a specific international economic institution on a chosen country\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on the history and components of economic globalization. Role-playing activity: Representing different countries\\/institutions in a trade negotiation scenario. OFF-SITE: Online Research on the World Trade Organization (WTO) and its functions. Reading: Articles on global supply chains and trade agreements (e.g., RCEP, CPTPP).,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 3. Infographics on global trade statistics. Video: \'How the WTO Works\'. Academic articles on economic globalization.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nDebate position paper (group). Research Paper Outline.\",\"Week 4\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPolitical Globalization: Global Governance and International Cooperation,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Describe the concept of political globalization and its manifestations. 2. Identify key international governmental organizations (IGOs) and their functions. 3. Critically assess the challenges and prospects of global governance in addressing transnational issues (e.g., climate change, cyber security).,, Assessment: ONSITE: Group Presentation: \'The Role of a Specific IGO in Global Affairs\'. OFFSITE: Case Study Analysis: \'The UN\'s response to a contemporary global crisis\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on the rise of IGOs and international law. Simulation: \'Model UN\' or \'ASEAN Meeting\' discussing a global issue. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: UN Charter, articles on regional blocs (e.g., EU, ASEAN). Video documentaries on international diplomacy.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 4. Websites of UN, ASEAN, EU. News articles on current geopolitical events. Documentaries on international relations.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nGroup Presentation slides\\/report. Written Case Study Analysis.\",\"Week 5\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nCultural Globalization and Media,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Explain the processes and impacts of cultural globalization. 2. Analyze the role of global media in shaping cultural flows and identities. 3. Evaluate the concepts of cultural homogenization, hybridization, and resistance in the context of globalization.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Film Analysis: \'Globalization in Pop Culture\'. OFFSITE: Photo Essay\\/Digital Storytelling: \'My Globalized Culture\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on cultural globalization, media saturation, and identity. Class discussion: Examples of global culture (music, movies, food) and local responses. OFF-SITE: Watching a foreign film or TV series with global appeal. Reading: Articles on cultural imperialism vs. glocalization. Social media analysis.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 5. Selected film\\/TV series clips. Articles on cultural studies and media theory. Examples of global brands and local adaptations.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nFilm analysis worksheet. Photo Essay or Digital Storytelling project.\",\"Week 6\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPrelim Exam\",\"Week 7\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Global City and Global Demography,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Define \'global city\' and identify its key characteristics and functions. 2. Analyze the socio-economic implications of global cities on local populations and national development. 3. Explain the concept of global demography and its impact on resource distribution, labor, and social structures.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Infographic Presentation: \'Profile of a Global City (e.g., Tokyo, London, Singapore, NYC)\'. OFFSITE: Demographic Data Analysis: \'Interpreting global population trends\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on Saskia Sassen\'s concept of the global city. Group activity: Identifying global cities and their roles. Discussion on demographic transition theory and global population issues. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Articles on specific global cities. Data exploration on UN Population Division website. Video: \'The World\'s Megacities\'.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 7. Maps of global city networks. UN World Population Prospects data. Articles on urbanization and demographic shifts.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nGroup Infographic. Written data analysis report.\",\"Week 8\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nGlobal Divides: Inequality and Sustainable Development,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Discuss the historical and contemporary factors contributing to global inequalities (e.g., North-South divide). 2. Explain the concept of sustainable development and its critical dimensions (economic, social, environmental). 3. Evaluate the progress and challenges in achieving the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) by 2026.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Problem-Solving Workshop: \'Addressing a specific SDG in a local context\'. OFFSITE: Policy Brief: \'Recommendations for achieving an SDG in the Philippines\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on global stratification and development theories. Collaborative activity: Mapping global inequalities. Group discussion on the 17 SDGs and their interconnectedness. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: UN SDG reports, articles on poverty and inequality. Video: \'The Story of the SDGs\'.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 8. UN SDG website. World Bank\\/IMF reports on global inequality. Case studies of successful\\/unsuccessful SDG initiatives.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nWorkshop output (e.g., action plan). Policy Brief (750 words).\",\"Week 9\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nGlobal Migration: Drivers, Patterns, and Impacts,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Identify the push and pull factors driving global migration in the 21st century. 2. Describe the major patterns and routes of international migration, including forced migration. 3. Analyze the socio-economic, political, and cultural impacts of migration on both sending and receiving countries (e.g., remittances, diaspora, integration challenges).,, Assessment: ONSITE: Panel Discussion: \'Perspectives on Migration: Migrant, Host, Policy Maker\'. OFFSITE: Interview\\/Research Report: \'The Migrant Experience\' (based on a real or simulated interview).,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on theories of migration and current trends. Guest Speaker (optional): A returning overseas Filipino worker or an expert on migration. Class debate on immigration policies. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: UNHCR reports, articles on OFW experiences. Watching documentaries on migration stories. Researching migration statistics.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 9. UNHCR Global Trends Report. IOM (International Organization for Migration) website. News articles on current migration crises. Personal narratives\\/testimonials.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nPanel discussion summary (group). Interview\\/Research Report.\",\"Week 10\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nThe Role of Religion in Global Society,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Explain the enduring and evolving role of religion in a secularizing and globalized world. 2. Analyze how religion influences political conflicts, social movements, and cultural identities globally. 3. Discuss the challenges and opportunities for interfaith dialogue and cooperation in promoting global peace and understanding.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Group Presentation: \'Religion\'s Impact on a Specific Global Issue (e.g., peacebuilding, human rights, environmentalism)\'. OFFSITE: Reflection Paper: \'Religion in a Globalized World: Conflict or Cohesion?\',, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on religion and globalization. Small group discussion: Examining case studies where religion plays a significant global role. Interfaith dialogue simulation. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Academic articles on religion and international relations. Video documentaries on global religious diversity. Researching major world religions and their global presence.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 10. Articles from Pew Research Center on religion. Documentaries on religious movements or conflicts. Readings on interfaith initiatives.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nGroup Presentation. Reflection Paper (600 words).\",\"Week 11\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nGlobal Food Security and Environmental Challenges,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Define global food security and identify its key pillars and challenges (e.g., climate change, poverty, conflict). 2. Analyze the interconnectedness of global food systems, climate change, and environmental degradation. 3. Propose solutions and sustainable practices to address global food insecurity and environmental crises.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Action Plan Development: \'Sustainable Food Systems for the Future\'. OFFSITE: Research Essay: \'The Impact of Climate Change on Food Security in Southeast Asia\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on global food systems, climate change science, and environmental governance. Workshop: Brainstorming local and global solutions for sustainability. Expert guest speaker (e.g., from an agricultural or environmental NGO). OFF-SITE: Online Reading: FAO reports, IPCC reports summaries, articles on regenerative agriculture. Documentaries on climate change and food production. Virtual field trip to a sustainable farm.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 11. FAO (Food and Agriculture Organization) website. IPCC (Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change) reports. Documentaries like \'Our Planet\'.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nGroup Action Plan. Research Essay (800 words).\",\"Week 12\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMidterm Exam\",\"Week 13\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nGlobal Health Issues and Pandemics,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Identify major global health challenges, including infectious diseases, non-communicable diseases, and health inequalities. 2. Analyze the socio-economic and political factors influencing global health outcomes. 3. Evaluate international responses to pandemics and propose strategies for strengthening global health governance in a post-2020s world.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Simulation Exercise: \'Responding to a Novel Global Health Threat\'. OFFSITE: Position Paper: \'Improving Global Pandemic Preparedness and Response\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on global health history (e.g., HIV\\/AIDS, COVID-19) and current trends. Case study analysis: \'Lessons from the COVID-19 Pandemic\'. Group discussion on vaccine equity and health diplomacy. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: WHO reports, articles on health disparities. Watching documentaries on past pandemics or global health crises. Researching health policies in different countries.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 13. WHO (World Health Organization) website. Lancet articles on global health. News archives on recent pandemics. Policy documents on global health security.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nSimulation debriefing report. Position Paper (700 words).\",\"Week 14\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nGlobal Citizenship and Ethics in a Globalized World,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Define global citizenship and its implications for individual and collective responsibility. 2. Discuss ethical dilemmas arising from globalization (e.g., human rights, corporate social responsibility, digital ethics). 3. Develop a personal framework for ethical decision-making in a global context.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Ethical Dilemma Workshop: \'Resolving Global Moral Challenges\'. OFFSITE: Personal Creed\\/Manifesto of Global Citizenship.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture on global ethics and citizenship. Socratic seminar on real-world ethical dilemmas. Group activity: Analyzing corporate social responsibility reports. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Articles on global ethics, human rights declarations. Video: \'What does it mean to be a Global Citizen?\' Reflective journaling on personal values in a global context.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 14. Universal Declaration of Human Rights. Case studies of ethical corporate practices. Philosophical texts on cosmopolitanism. TED Talks on global citizenship.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nWorkshop outcomes\\/recommendations. Personal Global Citizenship Manifesto (500 words).\",\"Week 15\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nContemporary Global Challenges and Future Trends (2026 Perspective),, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Identify emerging global challenges and trends (e.g., artificial intelligence, cyber warfare, new geopolitical alignments, space exploration). 2. Analyze the potential impacts of these trends on various aspects of human society. 3. Speculate on the future of globalization and humanity in the coming decades.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Futures Thinking Workshop: \'Scenario Planning for 2050\'. OFFSITE: Trend Analysis Report: \'The Impact of AI on the Global Workforce\'.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive lecture on emerging technologies and geopolitical shifts. Brainstorming session: \'What will the world look like in 2050?\' Group discussion: Ethical implications of AI and advanced technologies. OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Reports from think tanks (e.g., World Economic Forum, RAND Corp) on future trends. Watching documentaries on technological advancements. Researching specific emerging challenges.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTextbook Chapter 15. World Economic Forum reports. Articles from \'Foreign Affairs\' or \'The Economist\'. Documentaries on AI, quantum computing, space. Futurism blogs\\/websites.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nWorkshop scenario plans (group). Trend Analysis Report (800 words).\",\"Week 16\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nSynthesis and Application: Navigating the Contemporary World,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Synthesize key concepts and theories learned throughout the course. 2. Apply interdisciplinary perspectives to analyze complex contemporary global issues. 3. Formulate informed opinions and practical strategies for engaging with a globalized world.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Capstone Project Presentation: \'Addressing a Global Challenge\'. OFFSITE: Comprehensive Course Portfolio\\/E-portfolio.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Student presentations of capstone projects. Peer feedback session. Open forum for course reflection and Q&A. OFF-SITE: Review of all course materials. Preparation of Capstone Project and Course Portfolio. Self-assessment of learning journey.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nAll previous course materials, project guidelines, rubric for Capstone Project. Digital portfolio platform.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCapstone Project (e.g., policy proposal, advocacy campaign, research project). Completed Course Portfolio.\",\"Week 17\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Examination and Course Evaluation,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAt the end of the week, students will be able to: 1. Demonstrate a comprehensive understanding of the nature, theories, and impacts of globalization. 2. Critically analyze contemporary global issues and their interconnections. 3. Articulate informed perspectives on navigating the complexities of the contemporary world.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Final Examination (comprehensive written exam). OFFSITE: Course Evaluation Survey.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Review session for the final exam. Individual consultation. OFF-SITE: Self-study and preparation for the final examination. Completion of course evaluation.,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nReview materials, study guides, sample questions. Online course evaluation system.,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCompleted Final Examination. Submitted Course Evaluation.\",\"Week 18\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Exam\"}',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,'Contemporary World deals with the nature of the global community, the present global market; political tends of the world as well as the economic\r\ndevelopments of the present era. It further includes the appreciation of practical, intellectual, and the applicability of the concepts regarding the modernity of\r\nsociety in daily life. The course begins with the views and the nature of the concepts behind the theory of globalization as well as the application of the ideas\r\nas being emphasized in this so-called modern world; furthermore, students are encouraged to go beyond the conventional understanding of modernity in this\r\npresent time. The course also covers the role of religion in the global society, the rationale behind the influx of migration in many parts of the world especially\r\nin the European countries and its impacts to the economy and social conditions of the world. The course then proceeds to theories and concepts that are\r\nrelated to the present global state of affairs in which these philosophies can provide understanding in dealing with the various aspects of present-day living,\r\nsuch as managing one’s daily activities, traveling and working in foreign lands and making social choices. These aspects will provide further opportunities for\r\nactual undertakings in broad range of exercises that bring out the various dimensions of social perspectives as a way of knowing, and to test the students’\r\ncomprehension and capacity as well as ability. (CMO No. 20, series of 2013).','[{\"pilo\":\"Analyze texts (written, visual, oral, etc.) critically\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Demonstrate proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Use basic concepts across the domains of knowledge\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Demonstrate critical, analytical, and creative thinking.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Examine the contemporary world from both Phil. And global perspectives\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Take responsibility for knowing and being Filipino\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Reflect critically on shared concern\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Contribute personally and meaningfully to the country\\u2019s development\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Work effectively in a group\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Use current technology to assist and facilitate learning and research\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Manage one\\u2019s knowledge, skills, and values for responsible productive living\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Organize one\\u2019s self for lifelong learning\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','[{\"cilo\":\"Acquire knowledge about the experiences of Filipino people in the past from pre-history to present\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Develop intellectual skills, such as comprehension, analysis, interpretation and evaluation of facts and information of Philippine History through oral defense\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Inculcate among the students\\u2019 certain values such as patriotism and nationalism\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Criticize the importance of strategic location of the Philippines and understand its role in the history of the Filipino people\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Generate a wider perspective of the history of the Filipinos and to appreciate our rich cultural heritage\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','General Education Program aims to:\r\nIntellectual competencies\r\n1. proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\r\n2. understanding of basic concept across the domains of knowledge\r\n\r\n3. application of different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative artistic and scientific textual and visual experimental,\r\n\r\nobservation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically\r\nPersonal and civil responsibilities\r\n1. capacity to personally interpret the human experience\r\n2. ability to view the contemporary world from both Philippine and global perspective\r\n3. appreciation of human condition\r\nPractical Skills\r\n1. basic work-related skills and knowledge\r\n\r\n2. application of computing and information technology to assist and facilitate research\r\n3. working effectively in a group','At the end of the semester, the students will be able to:\r\nKnowledge\r\nExpress their ideas and arguments in written form, and learn to improve their analytical writing skills.\r\n\r\nSeek general explanatory principles, reflect upon what really matters, look for alternatives to widely-accepted views, and learn to distinguish what is significant from what is not.\r\n\r\nDevelop, establish, reconstruct, and evaluate arguments in any field or endeavor\r\nProvide practice at exploring, defending, and constructively criticizing ideas and claims with others\r\n\r\nSkills\r\nAbility to conduct research into philosophical topics, drawing on other disciplines when appropriate\r\n\r\nAbility to analyze and comprehend philosophical texts, particularly with respect to recognizing, expressing, and evaluating argument\r\nAbility to summarize and explain difficult ideas and concepts using language appropriate to the field\r\nAbility to understand reality from different perspectives and thus to understand that different people will define issues in different ways\r\n\r\nValues\r\nConstructively criticizing ideas and claims with others; and\r\nFamiliar with some of the major figures and schools of thought in the intellectual tradition, and develop an appetite for further study and learning.','At the end of this course, student should be able to:\r\n1. understand the History of Social Science and Philosophy;\r\n2. examine the differences of Political Theory and Political Philosophy;\r\n3. understand the proper utilization of Knowledge, volunteerism such as Social Works and the Ways of Knowing; and,\r\n4. understand the Concepts of Social Science and Theories of Philosophy\r\n4.1. Positivism and Empiricism;\r\n4.2. Epistemology, Ontology and Axiology;\r\n4.3. Nature of Meaningful Behavior;\r\n4.4. Importance of Culture and being a Human Persons in the Society; and\r\n4.5. Theories of Social Stratification.','Dolorical, Duke. T, (2019). The Contemporary World.1st ed. Quezon City. LJ Graphics and Literacy Exponent, Inc., 2019','Videos:\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I8DtrbvWa5A','Student must be able to:\r\n1. complete at least 80% of student participation;\r\n2. demonstrate punctuality according to his/her schedule; and,\r\n3. accomplish alternative assessment (if needed)\r\n3.1. when student fail to comply or perform poorly in a major examination and/or non-participation because of valid\r\nreason e.g. health, force majeure need to provide alternative assessment such as project, presentation, oral examination, and research output.','Cluster Leader:\r\nMary Joyce C. Cabiles, MPA\r\nCluster Members:','Faculty Member:\r\n\r\nEmail Address:\r\ncabilesemjhay@gmail.com\r\nConsultation Hours: 10:30-12:30\r\nTime and Venue:\r\nMain Campus – BSHM','MARY JOYCE C. CABILES, MPA','MICHAEL L. BERSAMIN, LPT','CHARLIE I. CARIÑO, Ph.D.','2026-02-06 16:02:40','2026-02-06 16:02:40',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(37,'FILDIS','FILIPINO SA IBA’T IBANG DISIPLINA','Minor','General Education','CHED',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'{\"Week 0\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives, Philosophy and School Organizational Structure School Policies Orientation in Online and Modular Learning System,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nRecite, internalize and explain the BCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives and Philosophy\\r\\nDeepen knowledge on the school\'s policies, guidelines, rules and regulations.\\r\\nFamiliarize on the new normal system of education through online, modular learning system and Blended Learning Delivery Modality (BLDM),, Assessment: ONSITE: Identify the Vision and Mission statements of BCP.\\r\\nCritically analyze these statements in 500 words, focusing on the following:\\r\\nThe clarity and coherence of the statements.\\r\\nHow these statements reflect the school\'s commitment to education.\\r\\nThe alignment of these statements with the current educational landscape.\\r\\nVerify that the BCP VMGO are align with the school goals thru checklist (PMED tools) OFFSITE: Navigate LMS and know the function of each feature.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Read and internalize the following printed materials for Students and Parents Orientation: OFF-SITE: Presentation and Lecture Discussion (PowerPoint Presentation) of Students and Parents Orientation:,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nInstructional Materials\\r\\nVideo Presentation of BCP Hymn\\r\\nYouTube Video Title: BESTLINK COLLEGE OF THE PHILIPPINES HYMN (BCP hymn)\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NuEYO11Wb4E\\r\\nStudent Hand Book\\r\\nLearning Management System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCheck alignment report\",\"Week 1\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nAng Filipino bilang Wikang Pambansa\\r\\n\\r\\nAng Multilingguwal na Pilipinas at iba pang Multilingguwal na Bansa\\r\\n\\r\\nAng Pagsibol ng Wikang Pambansa\\r\\n\\r\\nAng Hamon ng Mother-Tounge-Based Multilingual Education\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maipaliwanag ang ugnayan ng mga wastong layunin at gamit ng wikang Filipino bilang wikang pambansa.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Makilala ang mga bansang Multilingual din ang gamit sa Edukasyon\\r\\n3. Maunawaan ang Mother- Tongue-Based Multilingual Education\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPangkatang Presentasyon: Pumili sa mga sumusunod na paksa na tatalakayin sa malikhaing paraan ng inyong pangkat sa klase.\\r\\n\\r\\nPilipino: lahing multilingguwal at multikultural\\r\\nEbolusyon ng Wikang Pambansa\\r\\nWika ko\\/namin sa pagkatuto\\r\\nSampung Pangunahing wika ng bansa, iba iba ngunit nagkakaisa\\r\\n\\r\\nSagutan ang pahina 20 hanggang 25 sa inyong libro.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nSumulat ng isang sanaysay kung paano nagagampanan ng Filipino ang pagiging wikang Pambansa nito. Ipasa ito sa Google Drive.\\r\\n\\r\\nKumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain: \\r\\n1.1. Panuorin at pakinggan ang bidyo \\u201cTara Byahe Tayo\\u201d mula sa bersyon ng OPM All Star\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cTara Byahe Tayo\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=-bNw-Z2ibYw\\r\\n\\r\\nPinapakita sa liriko kung gaano kayaman ang bansang Pilipinas sa maraming aspeto.\\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na tanong\\r\\nAno ang nais ipabatid ng awit sa mga nakikinig?\\r\\nMasasabi bang maayos ang kultura ng mga Pilipino sa Pilipinas batay sa awit?\\r\\nMaari kayang may iba pang nais ipabatid ang awit tungkol sa Pilipinas?\\r\\nTalakayan:\\r\\nPagtalakay sa aralin gamit ang PowerPoint Presentation\\r\\nPagbabahagi ng kaalaman sa kapwa kamag-aral sa pamamagitan ng aktibidad na pinamagatang \\u201cTanong mo, Sagot ko\\u201d\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain: \\r\\n1.1. Panuorin at pakinggan ang bidyo \\u201cTara Byahe Tayo\\u201d mula sa bersyon ng OPM All Star\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cTara Byahe Tayo\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=-bNw-Z2ibYw\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\nNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\nPaglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House.  (Pahina 2-19)\\r\\n2. Online Resources: YouTube Video: \\u201cTara Byahe Tayo\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=-bNw-Z2ibYw\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\n30%\\r\\n30%\\r\\n40%\\r\\n100%\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:             \\r\\n\\r\\nPrelim\\r\\nMidterm\\r\\nFinals\\r\\nOverall\\r\\n30%\\r\\n30%\\r\\n40%\\r\\n100%\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPangkatang Presentasyon\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nSanaysay\\r\\n\\r\\nRubrik: Pamantayan sa pagsulat ng sanaysay\\r\\n\\r\\nIntroduksyon- 25%\\r\\nDiskusyon- 25%\\r\\nOrganisayon ng mga ideya- 25%\\r\\nKonklusyon- 25%\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio\",\"Week 2\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nWikang Filipino: Ang Wika ng Bayan at maging ng Akademya\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Ang Tungkulin ng Wikang Pambansa\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Ang Pagsilang ng Tanggol Wika\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Filipino Bilang Wika ng Akademya\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Wikang Akademiko ang Wikang Filipino\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Magamit ang Wikang Filipino sa iba\\u2019t-ibang tiyak na sitwasyon pangkomunikasyon sa lipunan at Paaralang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Makapagpahayag ng mga makabuluhang kaisipan sa pamamagitan ng tradisyonal at modernong midya.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Maipaliwanag ang iba\\u2019t ibang argumento ng Tanggol Wika\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n1. Pangkatang Gawain: Tumingin-tingin sa paligid. Magtala ng paskil (anunsyo\\/islogan, babala at mga senyas, atbp.) na nasa Filipino. Ilahad ang naging obserbasyon.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Sagutan ang pahina 47-48 sa inyong libro.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Manaliksik hinggil sa mga sumusunod at gawan ng bionote.\\r\\n1.1 Eugene Y. Evasco\\r\\n1.2 koichiro Matsura\\r\\n1.3 Dr. David San Juan\\r\\n1.4 Bienvenido Lumbera\\r\\n1.5 Pamela Constantino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.1 Panuorin at pakinggan ang bidyo na may pamagat na \\u201cSulong Wikang Filipino!\\u201d\\r\\nBienvenido Lumbera\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/sLJsYViUzGQ?si=84Shxy1zOn6a87av\\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na tanong:\\r\\n1.1 Gaano kaimportante ang paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa pag-aaral ng mga Pilipino?\\r\\n1.2 Maaari nga bang gamitin ang wikang Filipino sa pagtuturo ng Agham at Matimatika?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Talakayan:\\r\\n2.1 Diskusyon sa pamamagitan ng pangkatang gawain\\r\\n2.2 Bilang isang mag- aaral sangayon kaba sa paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa paaralan?\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Pangkalahatang Gawain at ebalwasyon\\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain:\\r\\n1.1 Panuorin at pakinggan ang Bidyo na may pamagat na \\u201cSulong Wikang Filipino!\\u201d \\r\\nBienvenido Lumbera\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/sLJsYViUzGQ?si=84Shxy1zOn6a87av\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n2.2 Nilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n2.3 Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 29-45)\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Poster\\r\\n3. Learning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Online Resources: YouTube Video: \\u201cSulong Wikang Filipino!\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/sLJsYViUzGQ?si=84Shxy1zOn6a87av\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPangkatang Presentasyon\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nBionote\\r\\n\\r\\n Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 3\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFilipino bilang Wika ng Saliksik sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan\\r\\n  1. Agham at Teknolohiya\\r\\n2. Negosyo at Industriya\\r\\n3. Edukasyon\\r\\n4. Politika\\r\\n5. Pananaliksik ng mga Guro\\r\\n6. Pananaliksik ng mga mag-aaral\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maipaliwanag ang kahalagahan ng pananaliksik sa iba\\u2019t ibang larang.\\r\\n2. Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga batayang kasanayan sa pananaliksik.\\r\\n 3. Makapagbuod makapagbuod ng impormasyon, estadistika, datos atbp. mula sa mga babasahing nakasulat sa Filipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Indibiwal na gawain: Magbigay ng mga halimbawa kung paano nakakatulong ang pananaliksik sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan.\\r\\n \\r\\n1.1 Agham at Teknolohiya\\r\\n1.2 Negosyo at Industriya\\r\\n1.3 Edukasyon\\r\\n1.4 Politika \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Magtungo sa laybrari ng ating eskwelahan at alamin kung may mga pananaliksik na nakasulat sa Filipino.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang gawain:\\r\\n1.1. Tukuyin ang salitang kinakaangkupan sa mga larawan (4 na larawan, 1 salita)\\r\\n1.2 Mula sa panimulang gawain, ibigay ang kahulugan ng mga nabuong salita.\\r\\n \\r\\n2. Talakayan\\r\\n  2.1. Pangkatang Gawain:\\r\\n Basahin at ipaliwanag ang mga sumusunod:\\r\\n\\r\\n2.2 Unang Pangkat: Pananaliksik sa Agham at Teknolohiya\\r\\n\\r\\n2.3 Ikalawang Pangkat:\\r\\n      Pananaliksik sa Negosyo at Industriya\\r\\n\\r\\n2.4 Ikatlong Pangkat: Pananaliksik sa Edukasyon\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Ikaapat na Pangkat:\\r\\nPananaliksik sa Politika\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Panimulang gawain:\\r\\n1.1. Tukuyin ang salitang kinakaangkupan sa mga larawan (4 na larawan, 1 salita)\\r\\n1.2 Mula sa panimulang gawain, ibigay ang kahulugan ng mga nabuong salita.\\r\\n \\r\\n2.\\tLearning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n2.1\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n2.2\\tPaglalahat\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 53-69)\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Rubriks\\r\\n3. Learning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nIndibiwal na gawain\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 4\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMga Terminong Ingles mula s iba\\u2019t ibang larangang isinalin sa Filipino \\r\\n\\r\\nMga Katawagan sa:\\r\\n1. Edukasyong Panteknolohiya at pangkabuhayan\\r\\n2.Pagbobrodkas\\r\\n3.Pamamahayag\\r\\n4. Pelikula\\r\\n5. Kasaysayan\\r\\n6. Mga Akronim \\/ Katawagang Pansosyalmidya\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1.  Mapalalim ang pagpapahalaga sa sariling wika at magamit ito ng maayos sa lipunan at kulturang Filipino.\\r\\n2. Makagawa ng mga mapanghikayat na presentasyon ng Impormasyon at analisis na akma sa iba\\u2019t- ibang teksto sa paggamit ng wikang Filipino.\\r\\n3. Malaman ang iba\\u2019t ibang salita na nabuo sa Telebisyon.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n 1. Pangkatang Gawain: Bumuo ng 5 miyembro at bumuo ng maikling presentasyon gamit ang mga katawagang pansosyalmidya.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Sagutan ang pahina 91-94 sa inyong libro.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Maghanap ng isang balita sa pahayagan na nasa Wikang Ingles at isalin ito sa Wikang Filipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain\\r\\n 1.1 Panoorin at pakinggan mabuti ang isang Investigative Documentaries ni Malou Mangahas tungkol sa paggamit ng mga kabataang Filipino sa Jejemon\\/ Swagger at Bekimon\\r\\n\\r\\nInvestigative Documentaries \\u2013 \\u201cJejemon and the Filipino Language\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/N4WOdJW_3K0\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Talakayan: \\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na tanong:\\r\\n\\r\\n2.1 Paano nakaapekto ang paggamit ng Jejemon sa pagsusulat ng mga Kabataang Filipino? \\r\\n2.2 Bilang isang mag-aaral masasabi mob a nadapat isama sa barayti ng wikang Filipino ang Jejemon?\\r\\n2.3 Naging maganda ba ang pagkakaroon ng jejemon sa wikang Filipino?\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Interaktubong diskusyon sa pamamagitan ng pagbibigay ng mga terminong Ingles na may katumbas sa Filipino.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain\\r\\n 1.1 Panoorin at pakinggan mabuti ang isang Investigative Documentaries ni Malou Mangahas tungkol sa paggamit ng mga kabataang Filipino sa Jejemon\\/ Swagger at Bekimon\\r\\n\\r\\nInvestigative Documentaries \\u2013 \\u201cJejemon and the Filipino Language\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/N4WOdJW_3K0\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n2.1 Nilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n2.2 Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 70-89)\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Learning Plan\\r\\n3. Rubrik\\r\\n4. Pahayagan\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Online Resources: YouTube Video: https:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/N4WOdJW_3K0,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPangkatang Gawain\\r\\n\\r\\nIskor sa libro\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 5\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFilipino sa Pambansang Industriyalisasyon \\r\\n1. Ano ang Pambansang Industriyalisasyon?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Ang mga industriya para sa maunlad na ekonomiya\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Ang mga rekursong mayroon sa Pilipinas na mgagamit sa industriya\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1.  Maipaliwanag ang kahulugan ng Pambansang Industriyalisasyon\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Malaman ang Kahalagayan ng Industriyaliyasyon sa bansa.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Maisa-isa ang mga kakulangan ng Pilipinas pagdating sa Pambansang Industriyalisasyon\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Sagutan ang mga sumusunod na katanungan:\\r\\n1.1 Ano ang Pambansang Industriyalisasyon\\r\\n1.2 Bakit mahalagang paunlarin ang mga industriya para sa maunlad na ekonomiya?\\r\\n1.3 Kaya ba nating magindustriyalisa?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Sagutan ang pahina 111-115 sa inyong libro.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Alamin ang kalagayan ng industriyalisasyon ng ibang bansa at ihambing sa Pilipinas gamit ang diagram.\\r\\nPilipinas -> Pagkakatulad\\r\\n -> Bansang ________\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain: Modyul 5.\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1 Pakinggan at unawain ang liriko ng awitin. \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cTrabaho, Negosyo, Kabuhayan Kaya natin yan!\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/C5 dj74-AaCI\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Gabay na Tanong:\\r\\n\\r\\n2.1 Ano ang nais ipabatid ng\\r\\nAwit?\\r\\n2.2 Masasabi bang mayaman\\r\\nang Pilipinas?\\r\\n2.3 Ano ang nais isulong ng\\r\\nKanta?\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Talakayan\\r\\n     \\r\\nDiskusyon gamit ang PowerPoint Presentation at sagutin ang mga tanong na nakapaloob.\\r\\n\\r\\n3.2 Pangkalahatang Gawain at ebalwasyon\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain: Modyul 5.\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1 Pakinggan at unawain ang liriko ng awitin. \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cTrabaho, Negosyo, Kabuhayan Kaya natin yan!\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/C5 dj74-AaCI\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n2.1 Nilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n2.2 Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 101-110)\\r\\n2. Learning Plan\\r\\n3. Artikulo na may kinalaman sa paksa\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Online Resources: YouTube Video: https:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/C5 dj74-AaCI,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nIndibidwal na gawain\\r\\n\\r\\nIskor sa libro\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nDiagram\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 6\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPrelim Exam\",\"Week 7\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFilipino sa Humanidades\\r\\n\\r\\n \\u201cAng mga liriko ni Gary Granada bilang repleksyon ng pulitika, Nasyonalismo at kalagayan ng Bansa.\\u201d (bahagi ng pananaliksik ni Joel Costa Malabana\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1.Maunawaan ang mga liriko ni Gary Granada.\\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Maipaliwanag ang halaga ng paggamit ng kanta sa pakikibaka.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Makasulat ng awitin na may patungkol sa isyung panlipunan.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pangkatang Gawain: Bumuo ng liriko na may temang patungkol sa mga isyung panlipunan sa bansa.\\r\\n1.1 Ibahagi at awitin ito sa klase.\\r\\n1.2 Ipaliwanag ang dahilan kung paano nabuo ang liriko.\\r\\n1.3 Ibahagi kung sino o ano ang naging inspirasyon sa pagbuo ng awitin.\\r\\n   1.4     Ano ang aral na makukuha sa awiting isinulat?\\r\\n\\r\\n2 Sagutan ang pahina 125-126 sa libro.\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\nHumanap ng alagad ng sining (manunulat, pintor atbp.) na maihahalintulad kay Gary Granada. Ilahad ang iyong mga naging batayan.\\r\\n\\r\\nKumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang gawain: \\r\\n1.1. Suriin ang mga kanta ni Gary Granada. \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cBahay\\u201d \\u2013 Gary Granada\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=j6QF_yyjpS0\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cManggagawa\\u201d \\u2013 Gary Granada\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=ypSIQ6zDiEA\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cDam\\u201d \\u2013 Gary Granada\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=UN-9mKUsi68\\r\\n2. Talakayan: Gabay na Tanong\\r\\n2.1. Ano ang nais ipabatid ng awit ni Gary Granada?\\r\\n2.2 Kanino niya inaalalay ang mga awitin na ito?\\r\\n2.3 Ano ang kahalagahan ng paggamit ng Wikang Filipino sa pagsulat ng mga awiting nabanggit?\\r\\n3. Pakinggan ang iba pang awitin ni Gary Granada at alamin kung patungkol saan ang mga ito.\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Pangkalahatang Gawain at ebalwasyon.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\nPanimulang Gawain\\r\\nNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n        1.3 Paglalahat\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n \\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 117-124)\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Plan\\r\\nRubrik\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\nOnline Resources: YouTube Video:\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=j6QF_yyjpS0\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPangkatang Gawain\\r\\n\\r\\nIskor sa libro\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 8\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFilipino sa Usaping Agraryo \\r\\nAgraryo, agricultural na Lipunan\\r\\n\\r\\nKawalang lupa\\r\\n\\r\\nUpa sa lupa\\r\\n\\r\\nMababang sahod at iba pang pagsasamantala\\r\\n\\r\\nPagpapaigting ng tunay na reporma sa lupa\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Masuri ang kalagayan ng agraryo sa Pilipinas\\r\\n2. Malaman ang kalagayan ng mga magsasaka sa Bansa.\\r\\n3. Mabigyan ng importansya ang mga magsasaka sa Pilipinas\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1.  Sumulat ng repleksyong papel hinggil sa natapos na paksa. Wakasan ang sanaysay sa pamamagitan ng pagbanggit ng iyong magagawa para sa mga magsasaka ng ating bansa. \\r\\n\\r\\n2.   Sagutan ang pahina 141-143 sa libro. OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Bumuo ng mga programa na makatutulong sa mga magsasaka ng Bansa.\\r\\n\\r\\n2.   Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain:\\r\\n1.1. Panoorin, pakinggan ng mabuti at unawain ang bidyo \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cPag-aalsang Agraryo noong 1745\\u201d https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=dbFC0ASEYDU\\r\\nTalakayan: \\r\\nGabay na tanong\\r\\n2.1. Paano nakakaapekto ang pangyayaring ito sa kasalukuyan sa Pilipinas?\\r\\n2.2 Tama ba ang ginawang pag-aalsa ng mga katutubo?\\r\\n2.3 Sa iyong palagay, nangyayari pa kaya ito sa kasalukuyan?\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Pagbabahagi ng mga kaalaman tungkol sa usaping agraryo sa Bansa sa pamamagitan ng pangkatang aktibidad.\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1\\tPanimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 129-140)\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\nOnline Resources: YouTube: https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=dbFC0ASEYDU,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nRepleksyong Papel\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagbuo ng programa\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 9\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFilipino sa Serbisyong Panlipunan \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cMungkahing Salin sa mga Paalala, Alituntunin, Panuto, at Direksyon sa mga Piling Pampublikong Ospital\\u201d ni Ranee Rose A. Garol\\r\\nFilipino sa Edukasyon\\r\\n\\u201cKabisaan ng Wikang Filipino at Alternatibong Sistema ng Pagkatuto (ALS)  sa pagtuturo sa mga Piling Learning Center sa Pambansang Punong Rehiyon ng Pilipinas\\u201d ni Hermeline Aguilar\\r\\n\\r\\n   Filipino sa Negosyo,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nMasuri ang\\r\\nkahalagahan ng paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan.\\r\\n2. Malinang ang paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang serbisyo.\\r\\n3. Makabuo ng mga iba\\u2019t ibang programa na makatutulong sa mga usaping panlipunan, pang-edukasyon at pagpapatayo ng negosyo.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Bumuo ng maikling presentasyon ng pag-eendorso ng produkto.\\r\\n\\r\\nSagutan ang pahina 155, 162-163.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Gumawa ng posisyong papel na may paksang \\u201cWikang Filipino, Wika ng Akademya.\\u201d\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain:\\r\\n1.1 Panoorin at unawain ang bidyo.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cNews@1: Komisyon ng Wikang Filipino, patuloy na isinusulong ang pagpapahalaga sa wika\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=QLquiMlGfZg\\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na Tanong:\\r\\nSang-ayon ka ba sa paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang larang?\\r\\nAno ang masasabi mo sa paggamit ng wikang Ingles, imbis na wikang Filipino ang gamitin? \\r\\nMaaari kayang talagang gamiting ang mga wika sa Pilipinas bilang wiakng panturo?\\r\\n\\r\\nInteraktibong Talakayan sa pamamagitan ng Pangkatang aktibidad\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1\\tPanimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 145-167)\\r\\n\\r\\n2 Learning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n2 Online Resources: YouTube: \\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=QLquiMlGfZg\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n Pangkatang Presentasyon\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPosisyong Papel\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 10\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nWikang Filipino sa Akawnting\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cAng posibilidad na Paggamit ng Librong nakasulat sa Wikang Filipino sa pagtuturo ng Accounting.\\u201d ni Patrick M. Malabo\\r\\n\\r\\nWikang Filipino sa Literatura\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cPanimulang Pagsipat sa Kulturang Popular\\u201d ni Perlas S. Carpio\\r\\n\\r\\nWikang Filipino sa Inhinyerang Sibil\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nFilipino sa Medisina\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1.\\tMasuri ang\\r\\nkahalagahan ng paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan.\\r\\n\\r\\n2.\\tMalinang ang paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa Akawnting, literature, inhinyerang sibil at medisina\\r\\n\\r\\n3.\\tMakasulat ng panitikan gamit ang Wikang Filipino,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pangkatang gawain: Magtala ng kahalagahan ng paggamit ng Wikang Filipino sa Akawnting, Literatura, Inhinyerang sibil at Medisina.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Sagutan ang pahina 191 sa libro.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1.  Maghanap ng sipi ng project proposal na kinapapalooban ng budget, target date at kapakinabangan ng munting proyekto at sikaping isulat sa wikang Filipino.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang gawain: \\r\\n1.1 Panoorin ang balitang nasa bidyo.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cKWF: Isinusulong ang paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa kongreso.\\u201d\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/DbEWdC7hsKs\\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na Tanong:\\r\\nSang-ayon ka bas a paggamit ng Wikang Filipino sa Kongreso?\\r\\nGaano kahalaga ang paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa Kongreso?\\r\\nMasasabi bang makatuturan ang panukala ng KWF?\\r\\n2. Talakayan: \\r\\n2.1 Makagawa ng interaktibong diskusyon tungkol sa paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1.  Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1\\tPanimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n1.Sanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 169-190)\\r\\n\\r\\n2 Learning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n2 . Online Resources: YouTube: https:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/DbEWdC7hsKs\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPangkatang gawain\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsasaling Wika\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 11\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nRebyu ng mga Batayang Kaalaman sa Pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\n1.  Pananaliksik\\r\\n2. Kasanayan sa pagpili ng Batis ng Impormasyon\\r\\n3. Kasanayan sa Pagbabasa at Pagbubuod ng Impormasyon\\r\\n4. Kasanayan sa Pagpapakahulugan\\r\\n5. Kasanayan sa Pagbasa ng Talahanayan\\r\\n6. Kasanayan sa Pagbasa ng Flowchart\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1.  Matukoy ang kahalagahan ng pananaliksik.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Matukoy ang mga mapagkakatiwalaan, makabuluhan at kapakipakinabang nasanggunian sa pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\n3.  Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga batayang kaalaman sa pananaliksik\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Magbigay ng mga salitang may kaugnayan sa Pananaliksik at sumulat ng sanaysay tungkol dito\\r\\n\\r\\nSagutan ang pahina 222-224 sa libro\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1.  Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: Panimulang gawain: \\r\\n1.1 Basahin ang modyul 11 tungkol sa hakbangin sa pagbuo ng pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na Tanong:\\r\\n1.2Paano mapapaunlad ang paggawa ng isang pananaliksik gamit ang hakbang na ito?\\r\\n\\r\\n1.3. Mahalaga ba ang pagkakaroon ng hakbang sa paggawa ng pananaliksik?\\r\\nBakit mahalaga ang pananaliksik sa pagpapaunlad ng iba\\u2019t ibang larangan?\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nTalakayan: Makabuo ng interaktibong diskusyon tungkol sa mga kasanayan sa pananaliksik\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1.  Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1\\tPanimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nSanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 193-221)\\r\\n\\r\\n2 Learning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nSanaysay\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 12\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMidterm Exam\",\"Week 13\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nRebyu ng mga Batayang Kaalaman sa Pananaliksik\\r\\n1. Kasanayan sa Pagsasalin\\r\\n2. Mapagkakatiwalaan, makabuluhan at kapakipakinabang nasanggunian sa pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Mga balangkas na nilalaman ng kwantitatibong pananaliksik.\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maipaliwanag ang kahalagahan ng pananaliksik\\r\\n2. Matukoy ang mga mapagkakatiwalaan, makabuluhan at kapakipakinabang nasanggunian sa pananaliksik\\r\\n3. Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga batayang kaalaman sa pananaliksik\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nIsalin sa wikang Filipino ang artikulo sa ibaba ni Peter Wallace ng inquiredotnet na hango sa https:\\/\\/opinion.inquirer.net\\/110536\\/dengvaxia-facts-1 at inilathala noong Enero 25, 2018. OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\nIsalin sa wikang Filipino ang artikulo sa ibaba ni Peter Wallace ng inquiredotnet na hango sa https:\\/\\/opinion.inquirer.net\\/110536\\/dengvaxia-facts-1 at inilathala noong Enero 25, 2018.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang Gawain: \\r\\n       Modyul 13\\r\\nPanoorin ang bidyo ni drew arellano sa palabas na AHA. https:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/EU 8DYpj6QaY\\r\\nGabay na tanong:\\r\\nAno ang binibigay na impormasyon sa paksa?\\r\\nMasasabi ba na ginawan ng pananaliksik ang paksa?\\r\\nAno ang iyong gustong nakuhang impormasyon?\\r\\nSagot sa mga tanong.\\r\\n\\r\\nTalakayan:\\t\\r\\nDiskusyon gamit ang PowerPoint Presentation.\\r\\nMagpapangkat upang magtutulong tulong sa paggawa ng pananaliksik (Depende sa guro kung ilan ang miyembro ng pangkat at pormat ng pananaliksik)\\r\\n\\r\\n3.  Pangkalahatang Gawain at pagpapahalaga\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1.  Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1\\tPanimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nSanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. (Pahina 193-221)\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsasalin\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 14\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMga Uri ng Pananaliksik ayon sa Pamamaraan\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Deskriptibong Pamamaraan \\r\\n2. Historikal na Pamamaraan\\r\\n3. Eksperimental na Pamamaraan \\r\\n4. Etnograpikong Pamamaraan\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Malaman ang iba\\u2019t ibang uri ng pananaliksik ayon sa pamamaraan\\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Maipaliwanag ang mahigpit na ugnayan ng pagpapalakas ng wikang pambansa, sa pagtuklang ng mga uri at anyo ng pananaliksik sa iba\\u2019t ibang disiplina.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. aktibong makilahok sa talakayan\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pangkatang gawain: Gawin ang Ikaunang Kabanata ng isasagawang Pananaliksik\\r\\n2. Sagutan ang aklat sa Fildis pahina 241-244\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Magsulat ng Konseptong papel patungkol sa problema sa edukasyon na nangyayari ngayon sa Pilipinas, gumamit ng news Report o balita sa telebisyon at radio bilang batayan.\\r\\n\\r\\n2.  Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interaktibong talakayan:\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nKabanata 1\\r\\nPanimula\\r\\nKaligirang Kasaysayan ng Pag-aaral\\r\\nBatayang Teoretikal\\r\\nBalangkas Konseptuwal\\r\\nPaglalahad ng suliranin\\r\\nHipotesis o Asumpsyon\\r\\nKahalagahan ng pag-aaral\\r\\nSaklaw at hangganan ng pag-aaral\\r\\n OFF-SITE: \\r\\n1. Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1\\tPanimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nSanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. \\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Plan\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n Pananaliksik (Ikaunang Kabanata)\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 15\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMga Dulog at Teorya sa Pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Teorya ng \\u201cDating\\u201d\\r\\n2. Teoryang Bakod-Bukod- Buklod\\r\\n3. Pagbaklas \\/ Pagbagtas \\r\\n4. Pantayong Pananaw\\r\\n5. Pagdalumat- Salita\\r\\n\\r\\nFilipino bilang daluyan ng inter\\/multidisiplinaring diskurso at pananaliksik.,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1.  Malaman ang daluyan ng inter\\/multidisiplinaring diskurso at pananaliksik\\r\\n2. Maipaliwanag ng malinaw ang pagkakaiba-iba ng mga metodo sa pananaliksik sa lipunan\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Maitaguyod ang paggamit ng wikang Filipino sa Pananliksik sa iba pang disiplina,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Gawin ang Ikalawang Kabanata ng isasagawang Pananaliksik\\r\\n2. Sagutan ang pahina 251-252 sa akat. OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE:  1. Panimulang Gawain: \\r\\nModyul 15\\r\\n\\r\\nBago natin simulan ang talakayan narito ang isang segment ngi Mr. Xio patungkol sa Pantayong Pananaw (Kasaysayan sa wika at punto de bistang Pilipino) https:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/H 3i5X_7muwk\\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na tanong:\\r\\nAno ang nais ipabadit ni Dr. Salazar?\\r\\nMasasabi bang maaari ngang gamitin ang wikang Filipino sa pag aaral ng kasaysayan?\\r\\nSang-ayon kaba sa paggamit ng wikang Filipino sapag aaral ng kasaysayan ng Pilipinas?\\r\\n\\r\\nTalakayan:\\r\\n\\t\\r\\nDiskusyon sa pamamagitan ng PowerPoint Presentation OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1.1\\tPanimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nSanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPananaliksik (Ikalawang Kabanata)\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 16\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMga Batayang kaalaman sa metodolohiya sa pananaliksik panlipunan \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Mga iba pang pamamaraan sa pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Mga metodolohiya sa pananaliksik\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maipaliwanag ang kahalagahan ng metodo sa pananaliksik\\r\\n2. Matukoy ang iba pang pamamaraan sa pananaliksik\\r\\n3. Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga metodo sa pananaliksik.,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pangkatang Gawain: Gawin ang ikatlong kabanata ng Pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Sagutan sa aklat Fildis ang pahina 273-275\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interaktibong talakayan:\\r\\n\\r\\nKabanata 2\\r\\n\\r\\nSalik Pantao\\r\\nSalik Pampapel\\r\\nSalik Pang- elektroniko\\r\\n\\r\\nMga metodolohiya sa pananaliksik OFF-SITE: 1.            Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1. 1         Panimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nSanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPananaliksik (Ikatlong Kabanata)\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 17\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMga Instrument sa pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\nPakikipanayam\\r\\nMga paghahanda sa pakikinayam\\/Interbyu\\r\\nFoucs Group Discussion\\r\\nCommunity Discussion Forums\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nMaipaliwanag ang kahalagahan sa pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\nMatukoy ang mga mapagkakatiwalaang instrumento na gagamitin\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: On-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Isaayos ang pinal na isinagawang pananaliksik mula ikaunang kabanata hanggang ikatlong kabanata.\\r\\n2. Sagutan ang inyong aklat sa Fildis pahina 276-279.\\r\\n OFFSITE: Off-site\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class..,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Panimulang gawain: \\r\\n \\r\\nBago natin simulant ang talakayan narito isang dokumentaryo may pamagat na anak ng Maynila\\r\\n| Short Documentary Film on the Current Situation of Filipino Street Children https:\\/\\/youtu.be\\/l byrZkzeor4\\r\\n\\r\\nGabay na tanong:\\r\\nAno ang nais ipabatid ng dokumentaryo?\\r\\nBakit kaya maraming bata ang nasa lansangan?\\r\\nMalaki ba ang maaaring epekto nito sa ating bansa?\\r\\nSagot sa mga tanong.\\r\\n\\r\\nTalakayan:\\r\\n\\r\\n2.1 Diskusyon gamit ang PowerPoint Presentation\\r\\n\\r\\n2.2 Mga tanong at sagot.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Pangkalahatang Gawain at ebalwasyon\\r\\n OFF-SITE: Learning Management System\\r\\n\\r\\n1. 1         Panimulang Gawain\\r\\n1.2\\tNilalaman ng paksa\\r\\n1.3          Paglalahat\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nSanggunian:\\r\\nAguilar, Hermeline B. et. al. (2018).  Filipino sa Iba\\u2019t ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing  House. \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n\\r\\nPinal na Pananaliksik (Kabanata 1-3)\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Pinal na Pananaliksik\\r\\n\\r\\nPagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 18\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Exam\"}',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,'Ang FILDIS ay isang praktikal na kursong nagpapalawak at nagpapalalim sa kasanayan sa malalim at mapanuring pagbasa, pagsulat, at pananaliksik sa wikang Filipino sa iba’t ibang larangan, sa konteksto\r\nng kontemporaryong sitwasyon at mga pangangailangan ng bansa at ng mga mamamayang Pilipino. Nakatuon ang kursong ito sa makrokasanayang pagbasa at pagsulat, gamit ang mga makabuluhang pa\r\nnanaliksik sa wikang Filipino, bilang lunsaran ng pagsasagawa ng pananaliksik (mula sa pangangalap ng datos at pagsulat ng borador ng pananaliksik hanggang sa publikasyon at/o presentasyon nito) na\r\nnakaugat sa mga suliranin at realidad ng mga komunidad ng mga mamamayan sa bansa at maging sa komunidad ng mga Pilipino sa iba pang bansa. Saklaw rin ng kursong ito ang paglinang sa kasanayang\r\npagsasalita, partikular sa presentasyon ng pananaliksik sa iba’t ibang porma at venue. Pre-requisite sa kursong ito ang pagkuha ng kursong Konstektwalisadong Komunikasyon sa Filipino (KOMFIL).','[{\"pilo\":\"Proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Understanding of basic concepts across the domains of knowledge\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Application of different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative artistic and scientific textual and visual experimental, observation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Capacity to personally interpret the human experience\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Ability to view the contemporary world from both Philippine and global perspective\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Appreciation of human condition\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Basic work-related skills and knowledge\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Application of computing and information technology to assist and facilitate research\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Working effectively in a group\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','[{\"cilo\":\"Maipaliwanag ang ugnayan ng mga function ng wikang Filipino bilang wikang pambansa, wika ng bayan, at wika ng pananaliksik na nakaugat sa pangangailangan ng sambayanan.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Maipaliwanag ang mahigpit na ugnayan ng pagpapalakas ng wikang pambansa, pagpapatibay ng kolektibong identidad, at pambansang kaunlaran\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga batayang kasanayan sa pananaliksik\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"Makapagsagawa ng pananaliksik sa Filipino sa iba\\u2019t ibang larangan.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Makapagpahayag ng mga makabuluhang kaisipan sa pamamagitan ng tradisyonal at modernong midyang akma sa kontekstong Pilipino.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Malinang ang Filipino bilang daluyan ng inter\\/multidisiplinaring diskurso at pananaliksik na nakaugat sa mga realidad ng lipunang Pilipino.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Maisaalang-alang ang kultura at iba pang aspektong panlipunan sa pagsasagawa ng pananaliksik.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Makapag-ambag sa pagtataguyod ng wikang Filipino bilang daluyan ng makabuluhan at mataas na antas ng diskurso na akma at nakaugat sa lipunang Pilipino, bilang wika ng pananaliksik na nakaayon sa pangangailangan ng komunidad at bansa.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','General Education Program aims to:\r\nIntellectual competencies\r\n1. apply higher level of comprehension (textual, visual, etc.);\r\n2. communicate proficiently and effectively (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies; and\r\n3. understand the basic concepts across the domains of knowledge.\r\nPersonal and civil responsibilities\r\n1. understand self-assuredness in knowing and being Filipino\r\n2. reflect critically on shared concerns and think of innovative, creative solutions guided by ethical standards\r\n3. contribute personally and meaningfully to the country’s development.\r\nPractical Skills\r\n1. demonstrate basic work-related skills and knowledge;\r\n2. apply the computing and information technology to assist and facilitate research; and\r\n3. work effectively in a group.','Sa pagtatapos ng kurso, inaasahang matutunan ng mga mag-aaral ang mga sumusunod:\r\nKaalaman\r\n1. Maipaliwanag ang ugnayan ng mga function ng wikang Filipino bilang wikang pambansa, wika ng bayan, at wika ng pananaliksik na nakaugat sa pangangailangan ng sambayanan.\r\n2. Maisa-isa ang mga suliraning lokal at nasyonal ng komunidad na kinabibilangan.\r\n3. Matukoy ang mga mapagkakatiwalaan, makabuluhan at kapaki-pakinabang na sanggunian sa pananaliksik\r\nKasanayan\r\n1. Maisapraktika at mapaunlad pa ang mga batayang kasanayan sa pananaliksik.\r\n2. Makapagbasa at makapagbuod ng impormasyon, estadistika, datos at iba pa mula sa mga babasahing nakasulat sa Filipino sa iba’t ibang larangan.\r\n3. Makapagsalin ng mga artikulo, pananaliksik atbp. na makapag-aambag sa patuloy na intelektwalisasyon ng wikang Filipino.\r\nHalagahan\r\n1. Mapalalim ang pagpapahalaga sa sariling teorya ng mga Pilipino sa iba’t ibang larangan.\r\n\r\n2. Malinang ang adhikaing makibahagi sa pagbabagong panlipunan.\r\n3. Maisaalang-alang ang kultura at iba pang aspektong panlipunan sa pagsasagawa ng pananaliksik.\r\n\r\n4. Makapag-ambag sa pagtataguyod ng wikang Filipino bilang daluyan ng makabuluhan at mataas na antas ng diskurso na akma at nakaugat sa lipunang Pilipino, bilang wika ng pananaliksik na nakaayon sa\r\n\r\npangangailangan ng komunidad at bansa.','Sa pagtatapos ng kurso, inaasahang matutunan ng mga mag-aaral ang:\r\n1. malikhain at mapanuring mailapat sa pananaliksik ang piling makabuluhang konsepto at teoryang lokal at dayuhan na akma sa konteksto ng komunidad at bansa;\r\n2. makapagpahayag ng mga makabuluhang kaisipan sa pamamagitan ng tradisyonal at modernong midyang akma sa kontekstong Pilipino;\r\n3. makabuo ng papel o artikulo na maaaring ibahagi sa isang forum o kumperensya at/o ilathala sa isang akademikong journal at\r\n4. makapag-ambag sa pagtataguyod ng wikang Filipino bilang daluyan ng makabuluhan at mataas na antas ng diskurso na akma at nakaugat sa lipunang Pilipino, bilang wika ng\r\npananaliksik na nakaayon sa pangangailangan ng komunidad at bansa.','Aguilar, Hermeline. et. al. (2018). Filipino sa Iba’t Ibang Disiplina: Jenher Publishing House.','1. BCP Learning Management System (LMS): https://bcpeducollege.elearningcommons.com/login/index.php \r\n2. Online Resources: YouTube, etc.','Student must be able to:\r\ncomplete at least 80% of student participation;\r\ndemonstrate punctuality according to his/her schedule; and,\r\nalternative assessment.\r\nwhen student fail to comply or perform poorly in a major examination and/or non-participation because of valid reason e.g. health, force majeure\r\n         need to provide alternative assessment such as project, presentation, oral examination, and research output.\r\n.','Cluster Leader: \r\nGelyn T. Banal, LPT\r\n\r\nCluster Members:','Faculty Member:\r\nGelyn T. Banal, LPT\r\nEmail Address:\r\ngelbanal22@gmail.com\r\nConsultation Hours:\r\nTime and Venue: \r\nAnnex Campus – BSTM Program\r\nOffice of the Program Head','GELYN T. BANAL, LPT','MICHAEL L. BERSAMIN, LPT','CHARLIE I. CARIÑO, Ph.D.','2026-02-06 16:18:57','2026-02-06 16:18:57',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(39,'GE 4','MATHEMATICS IN THE MODERN WORLD','Minor','General Education','CHED',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'{\"Week 0\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives, Philosophy and School Organizational Structure School Policies Orientation in Online and Modular Learning System,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nRecite, internalize and explain the BCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives and Philosophy\\r\\nDeepen knowledge on the school\'s policies, guidelines, rules and regulations.\\r\\nFamiliarize on the new normal system of education through online, modular learning system and Blended Learning Delivery Modality (BLDM),, Assessment: ONSITE: Identify the Vision and Mission statements of BCP.\\r\\nCritically analyze these statements in 500 words, focusing on the following:\\r\\nThe clarity and coherence of the statements.\\r\\nHow these statements reflect the school\'s commitment to education.\\r\\nThe alignment of these statements with the current educational landscape.\\r\\nVerify that the BCP VMGO are align with the school goals thru checklist (PMED tools) OFFSITE: Navigate LMS and know the function of each feature.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Read and internalize the following printed materials for Students and Parents Orientation: OFF-SITE: Presentation and Lecture Discussion (PowerPoint Presentation) of Students and Parents Orientation:,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nInstructional Materials\\r\\nVideo Presentation of BCP Hymn\\r\\nYouTube Video Title: BESTLINK COLLEGE OF THE PHILIPPINES HYMN (BCP hymn)\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NuEYO11Wb4E\\r\\nStudent Hand Book\\r\\nLearning Management System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCheck alignment report\",\"Week 1\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDISCOVERING PATTERNS AND NUMBERS IN NATURE (PART 1)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Defining Mathematics\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Investigating Patterns and Numbers in Nature\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDiscuss and argue about the nature, definition, and application of Mathematics.\\r\\n\\r\\nInvestigate patterns in life and number patterns.\\r\\n\\r\\nWrite an original article that illustrate patterns in nature\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Written Activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 1 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Motivation of the Game \\u201cWhat\\u2019s yours?\\u201d (Peer Pre-Activity)\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions:\\r\\n2.1. Where can you see pattern and regularities?\\r\\n2.2. How is Mathematics essential in the Modern World?\\r\\n2.3. How is Mathematics essential to your future career?\\r\\n2.4. What are the numbers that usually may present a group, or a thing or an organization?\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Write an original article that illustrate patterns and number in nature.\\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nWritten Article Output\\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 2\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDISCOVERING PATTERNS AND NUMBERS IN NATURE (PART 2)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pascal\\u2019s Triangle\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Other number patterns\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDiscover and investigate patterns in Pascal\\u2019s Triangle and other number patterns; and\\r\\n\\r\\nExpress the appreciation from the investigated and discovered patterns\\r\\n\\r\\nSolve complex problems using Pascal\\u2019s Triangle and other number pattern\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 2 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Work in pairs to solve a series of problems using Pascal\\u2019s Triangle and other number patterns. Students will first construct Pascal\\u2019s Triangle up to the 10th row. Using this triangle, they will solve problems related to binomial expansions and find patterns in the triangle.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint      \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\non-site: \\r\\nGroup Output\\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 3\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDISCOVERING PATTERNS AND NUMBERS IN NATURE (PART 3)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Fibonacci Sequence\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Golden Ratio\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAnalyze the properties and applications of the Fibonacci Sequence and its relationship to the Golden Ratio.\\r\\n\\r\\nAppreciate the significance of the Fibonacci Sequence and the Golden Ratio in nature, art, and architecture.\\r\\n\\r\\nCreate visual representations and solve problems involving the Fibonacci Sequence and the Golden Ratio through hands-on activities and exercises.\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 3 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. Who discovered the Fibonacci sequence?\\r\\n1.2. How is each term in Fibonacci     sequence generated?\\r\\n1.3. Where can you see the application of Fibonacci?\\r\\n1.4. What is the equivalence of Fibonacci?\\r\\n1.5. What formula will you use to get the nth term of the Fibonacci sequence?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Work in pairs to create visual representations of the Fibonacci Sequence and the Golden Ratio. First, they will draw the Fibonacci Sequence up to the 10th term and illustrate how it forms a spiral. Next, they will calculate the Golden Ratio using the terms of the Fibonacci Sequence and identify its presence in various natural and man-made structures. Finally, they will solve problems related to these concepts. . And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook, p. 14.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Activity Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio\",\"Week 4\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICAL LANGUAGE AND SYMBOLS (PART 1)\\r\\n\\r\\n1.  The Language of Mathematics\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Expressions versus Sentences\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDiscuss and understand the language, symbols, and conventions used in mathematics.\\r\\n\\r\\nRecall and share mathematical symbols, vocabulary, rules, conventions, expressions, and sentences to foster a deeper appreciation for the structure of mathematical language \\r\\n\\r\\nCritically analyze written Mathematical texts and communicated ideas with precision and concise ness by applying the rules and conventions of the language of Math.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group written activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 4 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recall Vocabulary of Characters\\/ Symbols and Abbreviations by playing 1-2-3 Pass. Then introduce the concept on Language of Mathematics and lecture\\/discussion on mathematical expression and sentence. And formulate mathematical expression and sentence.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity\\/collaborative work on translation mathematical expression and sentences. . And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook, pp.24-26.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Written Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 5\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICAL LANGUAGE AND SYMBOLS (PART 2)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Translation from  English to Mathematical expressions\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Mathematical Terms in Filipino\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDiscuss the commonalities and differences between Mathematics and English as language through translation from expressions to sentence; and\\r\\n\\r\\nExpress appreciation that mathematical terms in Tagalog is useful language, which is precise, concise, and powerful.\\r\\n\\r\\nTranslate from English to Filipino Mathematical expressions.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group written activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 5 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. How is the language of Mathematics able to change the World?\\r\\n1.2. What is the difference between mathematical expression and mathematical sentence?\\r\\n1.3. How would   you   know   that   the equation has truth value?\\r\\n1.4. What are the mathematical symbols and their absolute meanings?\\r\\n1.5. What is the difference between Mathematical Sentence and Mathematical Convention?\\r\\n1.6. How are the basic operations translated in Filipino terms?\\r\\n1.7. What is the strategy in translating mathematic expressions into mathematical sentence?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, create a Venn Diagram to determine the similarities and differences between Mathematics and English as languages through translation from expressions to sentence and answer. And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook,pp. 35-36 and 42. \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Written Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 6\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPrelim Exam\",\"Week 7\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nLANGUAGE OF LOGIC (PART 1)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Truth value of propositional statements\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDefine key terms related to logic of language, symbols, and conventions of logical operators in mathematics.\\r\\n\\r\\nDetermine the truth value of Propositional statements.\\r\\n\\r\\nUse and perform operations on mathematical logic as a useful language\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group written activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluatio\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 7 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. How would you determine a propositional sentence?\\r\\n1.2. How would you determine mathematical proposition?\\r\\n1.3. How would you determine if the proposition has truth value?\\r\\n1.4. What are the logical operators?\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, use and perform operations on mathematical logic as a useful language to solve a series of problems that require applying these logical operations to form logical statements and expressions. . And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et. al., 2018) textbook,pp. 341\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Written Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio\",\"Week 8\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nLANGUAGE OF LOGIC (PART 2)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Translate statements in symbolic form and vice versa\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Determine the truth value of the statements\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nTranslate statements in symbolic form and trans late symbolic statements into English sentences.\\r\\n\\r\\nValue the process of determining the truth value of statements, recognizing its role in enhancing logical reasoning and critical thinking skills in both mathematical contexts and real-world situations.\\r\\n\\r\\nCreate original logical problem\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group Activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 8 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. What is the symbol for negation?\\r\\n1.2. What are the six logical operators and their meanings?\\r\\n1.3. When will the true statement become false and false statement become true?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group Activity, create original logical problems and evaluate their truth values\\r\\nOnce the problems are created, students will exchange them with classmates and evaluate the truth values of the statements. After solving the problems, students will discuss their reasoning and verify the solutions together. . And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook, pp. 344-345\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization \\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Written Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio\",\"Week 9\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPROBLEM SOLVING AND REASONING\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Inductive and Deductive Reasoning\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Polya\\u2019s Problem Solving Technique and Lesson\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Real-life Problem solving for the quick-witted\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDifferentiate between inductive and deductive reasoning.\\r\\n\\r\\nAppreciate the value of Polya\\u2019s Problem Solving Technique and its practical applications in both academic and real-life situations.\\r\\n\\r\\nEmploy Polya\\u2019s Problem Solving Technique to solve real-life problems efficiently, demonstrating quick-witted and effective problem-solving skills.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group Presentation Activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 9 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions \\r\\n1.1. How can you differentiate between inductive and deductive reasoning, and in what scenarios might each type be most effectively applied?\\r\\n1.2. What are the basic principles in Polya\\u2019s problem solving?\\r\\n1.3. What makes an argument sound?\\r\\n1.4. How would you represent the missing element of a real-life problem solving?\\r\\n1.5. When your business experiences a sudden downtrend what action would you take and what are the expected consequences of these actions?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group Activity, solve real-life problems using Polya\\u2019s Problem Solving Technique. Each group will present their problem, solution, and reasoning to the class, demonstrating quick-witted and effective problem-solving skills. . And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et. al., 2018) textbook, pp. 53-58. \\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Presentation \\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 10\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICS AS A TOOL FOR DATA MANAGEMENT (PART 1)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Sample size and sampling techniques\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Data gathering techniques\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDetermine the appropriate sample size and sampling techniques for various types of research studies.\\r\\n\\r\\nValue the role of effective data gathering techniques in ensuring the accuracy and reliability of research results.\\r\\n\\r\\nApply different sampling techniques and data gathering methods in practical research scenarios\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group presentation activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 10 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. What type of sampling technique is used when you use Facebook to know Who Will Win in the next election?\\r\\n1.2. What is the difference between qualitative research and quantitative research?\\r\\n1.3 What are the different kinds of sampling methods?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group Activity, work to design a simple research study on a given topic. Each group will determine the appropriate sample size, choose and apply a sampling technique (e.g., random sampling, stratified sampling), and select data gathering methods (e.g., surveys, interviews, observations). After designing their study, groups will present their sampling techniques and data gathering methods to the class, explaining their choices and how they applied them to their research scenario. . And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et. al., 2018) textbook, pp. 92-94.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization \\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Presentation\\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 11\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICS AS A TOOL FOR DATA MANAGEMENT (PART 2)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Proportions and percentages\\r\\n\\r\\n2.Assigning ranks\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDiscuss the management and interpretation of data using descriptive statistics.\\r\\n\\r\\nValue the importance of scientifically gathering, logically presenting, and critically interpreting data.\\r\\n\\r\\nPractice writing and presenting findings, drawing conclusions, and making inferences based on data analysis.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group presentation activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 11 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. How can descriptive statistics be used to effectively manage and interpret data?\\r\\n1.2. Why is it important to scientifically gather, logically present, and critically interpret data?\\r\\n1.3. What are the best practices for writing and presenting findings, drawing conclusions, and making inferences based on data analysis?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, work to gather and analyze a data set using descriptive statistics. Each group will collect data on a chosen topic, present the data logically using tables and graphs, and interpret the results. They will then write a report detailing their findings, draw conclusions, and make inferences based on their analysis. Finally, each group will present their report to the class, explaining their data collection methods, presentation techniques, and interpretation process. . And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World, Carino, et. al., 2018) textbook, pp. 96-98. \\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Presentation\\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 12\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMidterm Exam\",\"Week 13\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICS AS A TOOL FOR DATA MANAGEMENT (PART 3)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Measures of Central Tendency (mean, median, mode)\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nExplain the concept of central tendency.\\r\\n\\r\\nAppreciate the significance of using measures of central tendency to summarize and interpret data sets.\\r\\n\\r\\nApply methods to compute and compare the mean, median, and mode through practical data analysis exercises.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group presentation activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 13 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. What is the essence of central tendency?\\r\\n1.2. What is the role of mean median   mode?\\r\\n1.3. How would you compute the mean median and mode of grouped data?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, analyze a provided data set and compute the mean, median, and mode of the data and compare these measures of central tendency. Then discuss how each measure provides different insights into the data. Finally, they will present their findings to the class, highlighting the differences and similarities between the mean, median, and mode. And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook, pp. 110-117\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Presentation\\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 14\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICS AS A TOOL FOR DATA MANAGEMENT (PART 4)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Measures of Variability\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDefine measures of variability and identify their related components.\\r\\n\\r\\nAppreciate the concept of measuring variability in data analysis.\\r\\n\\r\\nCalculate various measures of variation, including range, quartiles, and standard deviation, through practical exercises.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 14 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. What is the essence of measures of variability?\\r\\n1.2. When is measure of viability significantly used to draw conclusion?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, analyze a provided data set and calculate the range, quartiles, and standard deviation of the data. After performing these calculations, students will compare their results and discuss how each measure of variation provides insights into the data\'s spread and distribution. And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook, pp. 125-133.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization \\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nGroup Presentation\\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio\",\"Week 15\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICS AS A TOOL FOR DATA MANAGEMENT (PART 5)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Linear Correlation\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nExplain correlation as a measure of relationship;\\r\\n\\r\\nAppreciate the significance of identifying and analyzing linear relationships between variables.\\r\\n\\r\\nConstruct a scatter diagram and the correlation table to show the relationship of the variables.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group Activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 15 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. What is correlation, and how does it measure the relationship between variables?\\r\\n1.2. Why is it important to identify and analyze linear relationships between variables?\\r\\n1.3. How can constructing a scatter diagram and correlation table help in visualizing and understanding the relationship between variables?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, work on provided data set to explore linear correlation. Plot the data on a scatterplot to visually inspect for linear relationships. Calculate the linear correlation coefficient (Pearson\'s r) to quantify the strength and direction of the relationship between variables.\\r\\nInterpret the results and discuss the implications of their findings. And answer the activities on Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook, pp. 185-187.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio.\",\"Week 16\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICS AS A TOOL FOR DATA MANAGEMENT (PART 6)\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Inferential Statistics \\u2013 (T- test)\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nList the steps in calculating the statistical significance;\\r\\n\\r\\nValue the significance of Interpreting the result of the calculated population sample; \\r\\n\\r\\nCalculate the solution to problems applying a T-test\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group Activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 16 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions\\r\\n1.1. What are the steps in calculating statistical significance?\\r\\n1.2. Why population sample is important to calculate solutions using t-Test?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, use a provided data set to solve problems involving a T-test. Calculate the T-test statistic to compare the means of two groups, interpret the results to determine if there is a significant difference between the groups, and discuss the implications of their findings based on the T-test results. \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization \\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n    1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n    1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n  Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: \\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio\",\"Week 17\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMATHEMATICS OF FINANCE \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Simple and Compound Interest \\r\\n2. Credit Cards and Consumer Loans\\r\\n3. Stocks, Bonds and Mutual Funds\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nExplain the concepts of simple and compound interest, credit cards, consumer loans, and investment options like stocks, bonds, and mutual funds.\\r\\n\\r\\nAppreciate the importance of financial mathematics in making informed decisions about personal finance, including borrowing, saving, and investing.\\r\\n\\r\\nCalculate interest on savings and loans, evaluate credit card and loan options, and analyze investment choices using practical financial scenarios.\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: 1. Group activity \\r\\n2. Rubrics for Activity  \\r\\n3. Evaluation\\r\\n OFFSITE: 1. Complete the Week 17 assignment uploaded in your Learning Management System (LMS). Once accomplished, download and print a copy, then submit it during the next face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Recitation during discussion.\\r\\nEssential Questions \\r\\n1. How do the concepts of simple and compound interest differ, and how do they affect financial decisions over time?\\r\\n1.2 What role do credit cards, consumer loans, and investment options like stocks, bonds, and mutual funds play in personal finance management?\\r\\n1.3 Why is financial mathematics important for making informed decisions about borrowing, saving, and investing?\\r\\n1.4 How can you calculate interest on savings and loans, evaluate the benefits and costs of credit cards and loans, and analyze investment opportunities to make sound financial choices?\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Group activity, work on the activities in Mathematics in the Modern World (Carino, et.al., 2018) textbook, pp. 288-291, 296-299, 315.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Generalization\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Learning Management System\\r\\n1.1. Preliminary Activity\\r\\n1.2. Lesson Proper\\r\\n1.3. Generalization\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Powerpoint \\r\\n Presentation\\r\\n- Internet Source:\\r\\n- E-books\\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site: rtfgv\\\\\\r\\nWritten Output \\r\\nQuiz Result\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\nCompile all downloaded materials from the Learning Management System (LMS) for inclusion in your subject portfolio\",\"Week 18\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Exam\"}',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,'Mathematics in the Modern World deals with the nature of mathematics, appreciation of its practical, intellectual, aesthetic dimensions, and application of mathematical tools in daily life. The course begins with an introduction to the nature of mathematics as an exploration of patterns (in nature and the environment) and as an application of inductive and deductive reasoning. By exploring these topics, students are encouraged to go beyond the typical understanding of mathematics as merely a set of formulas but as a source of aesthetics in pattern of nature, for example, and a rich language in itself (and of science) governed by logic and reasoning. The course then proceeds to survey ways in which mathematical provides a tool for understanding and dealing with various aspects of present-day living, such as managing personal finances, making social choices, appreciating geometric designs, understanding codes used in data transmission and security, and dividing limited resources fairly. These aspects will provide opportunities for actually doing mathematics in broad range of exercises that bring out the various dimensions of mathematics as a way of knowing and test the students’ understanding and capacity. (CMO No. 20, series of 2013).','[{\"pilo\":\"Discuss and argue about the nature of mathematics, what it is, how it is expressed, represented and used\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Used different type of reasoning to justify statements and arguments made about mathematics and mathematical concepts\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"Discuss the language and symbols of mathematics\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Use a variety of statistical tools to process and manage numerical data\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Use mathematics in other areas such as finance, voting, health and medicine, business, environment, arts and design, and recreation\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"Appreciate the nature and uses of mathematics in everyday life\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"Affirm honestly and integrity in the application of mathematics to various human endeavors\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','[{\"cilo\":\"Analyze texts (written, visual, oral, etc.) critically\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Demonstrate proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies)\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Use basic concepts across the domains of knowledge\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Demonstrate critical, analytical, and creative thinking\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Examine the contemporary world from both Phil. And global perspectives\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"ake responsibility for knowing and being Filipino\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Reflect critically on shared concern\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Contribute personally and meaningfully to the country\\u2019s development\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Work effectively in a group\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Use current technology to assist and facilitate learning and research\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"anage one\\u2019s knowledge, skills, and values for responsible productive living\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Organize one\\u2019s self for lifelong learning\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','General Education Program aims to:\r\nIntellectual Competencies\r\n1. analyze texts (written, visual, oral, etc.) critically;\r\n2. demonstrate proficient and effective communication (writing, speaking, and use of new technologies);\r\n3. use basic concepts across the domains of knowledge; and\r\n4. demonstrate critical, analytical, and creative thinking.\r\nPersonal and Civil Responsibility\r\n1. examine the contemporary world from both Phil. And global perspectives;\r\n2. take responsibility for knowing and being Filipino;\r\n3. reflect critically on shared concern; and\r\n4. contribute personally and meaningfully to the country’s development.\r\nPractical Skills\r\n1. work effectively in a group;\r\n2. use current technology to assist and facilitate learning and research;\r\n3. manage one’s knowledge, skills, and values for responsible and productive living; and\r\n4. organize one’s self for lifelong learning.','At the end of the semester, the students will be able to:\r\nKnowledge\r\n1. Discuss and argue about the nature of mathematics, what it is, how it is expressed, represented and used; \r\n2. Used different type of reasoning to justify statements and arguments made about mathematics and mathematical concepts; and\r\n3. Discuss the language and symbols of mathematics.\r\nSkills\r\n4. Use a variety of statistical tools to process and manage numerical data; and\r\n5. Use mathematics in other areas such as finance, voting, health and medicine, business, environment, arts and design, and recreation;\r\nValues\r\n6. Appreciate the nature and uses of mathematics in everyday life; and\r\n7. Affirm honestly and integrity in the application of mathematics to various human endeavors.','t the end of the course, students should be able to:\r\n1. Identify patterns in nature and regularities in the world. \r\n2. Articulate the importance of mathematics in one’s life.\r\n3. Argue about nature of mathematics, what it is, how it is expressed, represented and used.   \r\n4. Express appreciation for mathematics as human endeavor. \r\n5. Discuss the language, symbols and conventions of mathematics.\r\n6. Explain the nature of mathematics as a language. \r\n7. Perform operations on mathematical expression correctly.  \r\n8. Acknowledge that mathematics is useful language. \r\n9. Use different types of reasoning to justify statements and arguments made about mathematics and mathematical concepts.\r\n10. Write clear logical proofs.   \r\n11. Solving problems involving patterns and recreational problems following Polya’s four step.    \r\n12. Organize one’s method and approaches for proving and solving problem. \r\n13. Use a variety of statistical tools to process and manage numerical data.\r\n14. Use the method the method of linear regression and correlation to predict the value of a variable given certain condition.\r\n15. Advocate the use of statistical data in making important decisions. \r\n16. Support the use of mathematics in various aspects and endeavors of life.','Bangalisan (2020). Module on Mathematics in the Modern World, AA Publishing Inc. \r\nCarino, et.al. (2018). Mathematics in the Modern World, J&E Publishing\r\nDaligdig (2019). Mathematics in the Modern World, Lorimar Publishing, Inc. \r\nHipolito & Manlulu (2019). Mathematics in the Modern World, Rex Book Store Inc. \r\nAdina & Earnheart, (2022). Mathematics in the Modern World Second Edition, C&E Publishing, Inc.','Medallon & Calubaquib (2018). Mathematics in the Modern World Work Text, Mindshaper Co., Inc.\r\nSirug (2018). Mathematics in the Modern World, Mindshaper Co., Inc.\r\nAufmann et al. (2018). Mathematics in the Modern World Philippine Edition, Rex Book Store Inc.','Students must be able to:\r\n1. complete at least 80% of the student participation;\r\n2. demonstrate punctuality according to his/her schedule; and\r\n3. accomplish alternative assessment\r\n    3.1. when student fail to comply or perform poorly in major examination and/or nonparticipation because of valid reasons e.g., health, force majeure needs to provide alternative assessment such as \r\n           project, presentation, oral examination and research output.','Cluster Leader: \r\nMark John S. Kibo-Kibo, LPT','Faculty Member:\r\nMark John S. Kibo-Kibo, LPT\r\n\r\nEmail Address:\r\nmkibokibo27@gmail.com\r\n\r\nConsultation Hours:\r\n\r\nTime and Venue:\r\nMV Campus – BSBA Program\r\nOffice of the Program Head','MARK JOHN S. KIBO-KIBO, LPT','MICHAEL L. BERSAMIN, LPT','CHARLIE I. CARIÑO, Ph.D.','2026-02-06 16:37:26','2026-02-06 16:37:26',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(40,'NSTP 1','NATIONAL SERVICE TRAINING PROGRAM 1','Minor','NSTP 1','CHED',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'{\"Week 0\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives, Philosophy and School Organizational Structure School Policies Orientation in Online and Modular Learning System,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nRecite, internalize and explain the BCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives and Philosophy\\r\\nDeepen knowledge on the school\'s policies, guidelines, rules and regulations.\\r\\nFamiliarize on the new normal system of education through online, modular learning system and Blended Learning Delivery Modality (BLDM),, Assessment: ONSITE: Identify the Vision and Mission statements of BCP.\\r\\nCritically analyze these statements in 500 words, focusing on the following:\\r\\nThe clarity and coherence of the statements.\\r\\nHow these statements reflect the school\'s commitment to education.\\r\\nThe alignment of these statements with the current educational landscape.\\r\\nVerify that the BCP VMGO are align with the school goals thru checklist (PMED tools) OFFSITE: Navigate LMS and know the function of each feature.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Read and internalize the following printed materials for Students and Parents Orientation: OFF-SITE: Presentation and Lecture Discussion (PowerPoint Presentation) of Students and Parents Orientation:,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nInstructional Materials\\r\\nVideo Presentation of BCP Hymn\\r\\nYouTube Video Title: BESTLINK COLLEGE OF THE PHILIPPINES HYMN (BCP hymn)\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NuEYO11Wb4E\\r\\nStudent Hand Book\\r\\nLearning Management System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCheck alignment report\",\"Week 1\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nOrientation to National Service Training Program (NSTP) and Civic Welfare Training Service (CWTS),, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nExplain the philosophical and legal bases of NSTP; Identify the components of NSTP and its relevance to national development; Appreciate the significance of civic welfare and community service.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Oral Recitation on NSTP concepts, Short Quiz on NSTP Law OFFSITE: Reflection Paper: \'My Role as a Filipino Citizen\',, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive Lecture-Discussion on RA 9163 and CHED Memorandums; Q&A Session; Group Brainstorming on \'What is National Service?\' OFF-SITE: Video Watching: \'The Essence of NSTP\' (via LMS); Online Reading: CHED NSTP Handbook\\/Primer (provided URL),, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nRepublic Act 9163 (NSTP Law); CHED Memorandum Order No. 01, Series of 2016; NSTP Primer\\/Handbook; Presentation Slides; Whiteboard\\/Marker; Projector; Video URL: \'NSTP Orientation\',, Output Materials:\\r\\nCompleted Reflection Paper; Quiz Answer Sheet\",\"Week 2\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nUnderstanding the Self for Community Service: Values Formation, Leadership, and Communication,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nExamine personal values and their alignment with community service; Identify key leadership traits and communication styles essential for community work; Develop a personal action plan for self-improvement in preparation for community engagement.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Group Activity: \'My Leadership Style\' assessment; Peer Feedback Session on communication skills OFFSITE: Personal Values Clarification Worksheet; Short Essay: \'How My Values Shape My Service\',, Activities: ON-SITE: Experiential Learning: Team-building exercises; Role-playing scenarios for effective communication; Facilitated Discussion on Filipino values (e.g., Bayanihan, Pakikipagkapwa-tao) OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Articles on Servant Leadership and Interpersonal Communication (LMS links); Self-assessment quiz on communication effectiveness,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nLeadership style questionnaires; Communication skills rubrics; Handouts on Filipino values; Articles on Servant Leadership; Video: \'Effective Communication in Community Work\',, Output Materials:\\r\\nCompleted Values Clarification Worksheet; Personal Action Plan; Essay Submission\",\"Week 3\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDimensions of Development: Health and Safety for Community Well-being,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDiscuss the importance of public health and safety in community development; Identify common health issues and safety hazards in communities; Demonstrate basic first aid and emergency preparedness techniques.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Practical Demonstration: Basic First Aid (bandaging, CPR simulation); Group Presentation: \'Community Health and Safety Concerns\' OFFSITE: Research Paper: \'Common Health Issues in Philippine Communities and Prevention Strategies\'; Emergency Contact Information Sheet,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive Lecture on Public Health and Safety; Hands-on Workshop: Basic First Aid and Disaster Preparedness; Case Study Analysis: Community Health Crisis OFF-SITE: Online Module: \'Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Basics\' (LMS); Video Tutorials on Basic Life Support (BLS) and First Aid,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nFirst Aid Kit; CPR Mannequin (if available); DRRM Handbook (online); Presentation Slides on Public Health; Video URLs for First Aid and BLS; Articles on local health issues,, Output Materials:\\r\\nFirst Aid Skills Checklist (peer-evaluated); Group Presentation Output; Research Paper\",\"Week 4\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDimensions of Development: Environmental Protection and Sustainable Livelihood,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAnalyze pressing environmental issues in the Philippines and their impact on communities; Propose sustainable practices for environmental protection and resource management; Explore basic concepts of entrepreneurship and livelihood generation for community empowerment.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Debate: \'Economic Development vs. Environmental Protection\'; Group Activity: \'Designing a Sustainable Community Project\' OFFSITE: Environmental Scan Report of a local area; Business Plan Outline for a community-based livelihood project,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture-Discussion on Climate Change, Waste Management, and Biodiversity; Workshop on \'Green Initiatives\' and circular economy concepts; Brainstorming on sustainable livelihood opportunities OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Philippine Agenda 21 and Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) related to environment and poverty; Video Documentary: \'Environmental Challenges in the Philippines\',, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nPhilippine Agenda 21 document; UN SDGs framework; Presentation Slides on Environmental Science and Entrepreneurship; Case studies on successful community-based enterprises; Video URLs on environmental documentaries,, Output Materials:\\r\\nEnvironmental Scan Report; Sustainable Community Project Proposal (initial draft); Business Plan Outline\",\"Week 5\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDimensions of Development: Education and Social Welfare,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDiscuss the role of education in national development and community empowerment; Identify various social welfare concerns and programs; Propose initiatives that promote literacy, youth development, and social inclusion.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Panel Discussion: \'Challenges in Philippine Education\'; Role-play: \'Advocating for Social Welfare Programs\' OFFSITE: Concept Paper: \'A Literacy Program for Out-of-School Youth\'; Community Needs Assessment Survey (initial design),, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive Lecture on the Philippine Education System and Social Welfare Policies; Group Brainstorming on educational interventions; Discussion on vulnerable sectors (e.g., PWDs, indigenous peoples) OFF-SITE: Online Reading: Magna Carta for Disabled Persons, Indigenous Peoples\' Rights Act, CHED Memorandums on inclusive education; Case studies on successful social welfare projects,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nPhilippine Constitution (Education and Social Justice articles); CHED Memorandums on Education; Laws on Social Welfare (e.g., PWDs, IPs); Presentation Slides; Articles on inclusive education; Video: \'Stories of Social Inclusion\',, Output Materials:\\r\\nConcept Paper for a Literacy Program; Community Needs Assessment Survey (initial design)\",\"Week 6\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPrelim Exam\",\"Week 7\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nPrinciples of Community Organizing and Needs Assessment,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nExplain the core principles and phases of community organizing; Apply basic methodologies for conducting a community needs assessment; Identify priority needs and resources within a target community.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Group Presentation: \'Community Profile and Initial Needs Assessment\'; Role-play: \'Interviewing Community Members\' OFFSITE: Draft Community Needs Assessment Report (based on chosen community); Data Collection Tools (e.g., survey questionnaire, interview guide),, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture-Discussion on Community Organizing Participatory Action Research (COPAR); Workshop on data gathering techniques (e.g., FGD, KII, survey); Simulation of community mapping OFF-SITE: Online Reading: \'Guide to Community Needs Assessment\'; Video Tutorial: \'Conducting Focus Group Discussions\'; Online research on demographic data of potential target communities,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nCOPAR Handbook\\/Modules; Presentation Slides; Sample Community Needs Assessment Reports; Templates for survey questionnaires and interview guides; Online resources for demographic data (e.g., PSA),, Output Materials:\\r\\nCompleted Data Collection Tools; Draft Community Needs Assessment Report; Community Profile Presentation\",\"Week 8\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nProject Planning and Management for Community Engagement,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nFormulate clear project goals, objectives, and activities for a community service initiative; Develop a logical framework matrix (LFM) for a proposed project; Identify necessary resources and potential partners for project implementation.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Workshop: \'Developing a Logical Framework Matrix\'; Peer Review of Project Proposals OFFSITE: Detailed Community Project Proposal (including LFM, budget, and timeline); Resource Mobilization Plan,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive Lecture on Project Management Cycle; Hands-on Workshop: Project Proposal Writing (focus on SMART objectives, activities, and indicators); Brainstorming on fundraising strategies OFF-SITE: Online Tutorial: \'Introduction to Project Management\'; Online Reading: \'Grant Writing Basics for Non-Profits\'; Research on potential funding sources and partners for community projects,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nProject Management Handbook; Sample Project Proposals; Logical Framework Matrix Template; Budgeting templates; Presentation Slides; Online resources for grant applications,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCompleted Project Proposal; Resource Mobilization Plan; LFM Draft\",\"Week 9\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nEthics and Volunteerism in Community Service,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nArticulate ethical considerations and principles of responsible volunteerism in community work; Analyze potential ethical dilemmas in community engagement; Commit to upholding integrity, respect, and accountability in service.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Case Study Analysis: \'Ethical Dilemmas in Community Service\'; Group Discussion: \'Volunteer Rights and Responsibilities\' OFFSITE: Reflection Paper: \'My Ethical Stance as a Volunteer\'; Volunteer Pledge,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture-Discussion on Code of Ethics for Volunteers; Interactive session on cultural sensitivity and informed consent; Role-playing ethical scenarios OFF-SITE: Online Reading: \'The Universal Declaration on Volunteering\'; Video: \'Ethical Volunteering Best Practices\'; Online discussion forum on ethical challenges faced by volunteers,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nCode of Ethics for Volunteers; Universal Declaration on Volunteering; Presentation Slides; Case studies on ethical issues in community development; Video URLs on responsible volunteering,, Output Materials:\\r\\nReflection Paper; Signed Volunteer Pledge\",\"Week 10\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nTeamwork and Leadership in Community Action,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nDemonstrate effective teamwork and collaboration skills in a group setting; Apply various leadership styles appropriate for different community contexts; Resolve conflicts constructively within a team.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Group Project Simulation: \'Solving a Community Problem\'; Peer Evaluation of Teamwork and Leadership OFFSITE: Team Charter and Group Norms Document; Individual Reflection: \'My Contribution to Team Success\',, Activities: ON-SITE: Experiential Learning: Complex team-building challenges; Facilitated Discussion on group dynamics and conflict resolution; Workshop on situational leadership OFF-SITE: Online Module: \'Teamwork and Collaboration Skills\'; Video Series: \'Great Leaders in Community Development\'; Online self-assessment on conflict resolution styles,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTeam-building activity kits; Handouts on leadership theories (e.g., situational, transformational); Conflict resolution strategies; Presentation Slides; Video URLs on effective teams and leaders,, Output Materials:\\r\\nTeam Charter; Peer Evaluation Forms; Individual Reflection Paper\",\"Week 11\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nCommunication and Advocacy in Community Work,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nApply effective communication strategies for diverse community audiences; Develop compelling advocacy messages for social causes; Design a simple advocacy campaign for a chosen community issue.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Presentation: \'Advocacy Campaign Proposal\'; Public Speaking Practice (delivering an advocacy message) OFFSITE: Draft Advocacy Campaign Plan (including target audience, message, and channels); Press Release\\/Social Media Post Draft for advocacy,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive Lecture on Public Relations and Advocacy; Workshop on message framing and storytelling; Group activity: \'Developing a Slogan and Visual for a Cause\' OFF-SITE: Online Reading: \'Principles of Social Marketing\' and \'Crafting Effective Advocacy Messages\'; Video Tutorials on Public Speaking and Presentation Skills; Analysis of successful advocacy campaigns,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nPublic relations and advocacy handbooks; Presentation Slides; Examples of effective advocacy campaigns (local and international); Video URLs on public speaking tips; Social media guidelines,, Output Materials:\\r\\nAdvocacy Campaign Plan; Public Speaking Performance (assessed); Draft Press Release\\/Social Media Post\",\"Week 12\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMidterm Exam\",\"Week 13\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nRisk Management and Safety Protocols in Community Service,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nAnalyze potential risks and hazards associated with community service activities; Develop comprehensive safety protocols and emergency response plans; Ensure compliance with relevant safety regulations and guidelines.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Group Presentation: \'Risk Assessment and Mitigation Plan for a Specific Project\'; Scenario-based problem-solving on emergency response OFFSITE: Individual Risk Assessment Report for a hypothetical community project; Emergency Contact and Safety Protocol Checklist,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture-Discussion on Risk Management Frameworks (e.g., ISO 31000); Workshop on identifying, assessing, and mitigating risks; Simulation of emergency situations and response protocols OFF-SITE: Online Module: \'Occupational Safety and Health (OSH) Basics\'; Online Research on local safety regulations (e.g., DOLE, LGU ordinances); Video Tutorials on emergency procedures (e.g., fire safety, evacuation),, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nISO 31000 Risk Management Guidelines (summary); OSH standards; Local government unit (LGU) safety ordinances; Presentation Slides; Emergency contact templates; Video URLs on safety drills,, Output Materials:\\r\\nRisk Assessment and Mitigation Plan; Emergency Response Plan; Safety Protocol Checklist\",\"Week 14\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMonitoring and Evaluation of Community Projects,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nExplain the importance of monitoring and evaluation (M&E) in community development; Identify key indicators for measuring project success and impact; Develop a basic M&E plan for a community service project.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Workshop: \'Designing an M&E Framework\'; Group Presentation: \'Proposed M&E Plan for Our Project\' OFFSITE: Draft Monitoring and Evaluation Plan (with indicators and tools); Data Collection Log Template,, Activities: ON-SITE: Interactive Lecture on M&E concepts, types, and approaches; Hands-on activity: indicator development and data collection tool design; Discussion on ethical considerations in data collection OFF-SITE: Online Reading: \'Introduction to Monitoring and Evaluation for Development Projects\'; Video Tutorial: \'Logic Model in M&E\'; Research on best practices in M&E for community-based programs,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nM&E Handbooks (e.g., USAID, UNDP); Logic Model templates; Presentation Slides; Sample M&E plans; Data collection tool examples (e.g., survey, FGD guide); Video URLs on M&E basics,, Output Materials:\\r\\nDraft Monitoring and Evaluation Plan; Data Collection Log Template\",\"Week 15\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nDocumentation and Reporting for Community Projects,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nPrepare clear, concise, and comprehensive project documentation; Utilize appropriate formats for reporting project progress and outcomes; Effectively present project findings to various stakeholders.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Presentation: \'Project Progress Report\'; Peer Critique Session on reporting formats OFFSITE: Draft Project Progress Report (incorporating M&E data); Photo\\/Video Documentation Log,, Activities: ON-SITE: Lecture-Discussion on technical writing for project reports; Workshop on data visualization and infographic design; Practice sessions for oral presentations OFF-SITE: Online Reading: \'Guidelines for Effective Project Reporting\'; Video Tutorials on Microsoft Office (Word, PowerPoint) or Google Suite (Docs, Slides) for reporting; Online research on visual communication principles,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nTechnical writing guides; Sample project reports; Presentation Slides; Data visualization tools (e.g., Canva, Piktochart); Video URLs on effective presentations; Project documentation templates,, Output Materials:\\r\\nDraft Project Progress Report; Photo\\/Video Documentation Log; Presentation Slides\",\"Week 16\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nReflection and Future Engagement in Community Service,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nReflect critically on personal learning experiences and contributions throughout the NSTP CWTS program; Articulate a sustained commitment to civic responsibility and community engagement beyond the course; Identify opportunities for continued service and advocacy.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Sharing Session: \'My NSTP Journey and Future Commitments\'; Group Discussion: \'Challenges and Rewards of Community Service\' OFFSITE: Comprehensive Reflection Journal on the entire NSTP CWTS experience; Personal Advocacy Plan for continued civic engagement,, Activities: ON-SITE: Facilitated Reflection Activities (e.g., \'What I learned, How I grew, What I\'ll do next\'); Visioning exercise for future community involvement; Testimonial sharing OFF-SITE: Online Reading: \'Lifelong Learning for Social Change\'; Video: \'Inspiring Stories of Filipino Volunteers\'; Online forum for sharing insights and future plans,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nReflection journal prompts; Articles on lifelong learning and civic engagement; Presentation Slides; Video URLs of inspirational civic leaders; Online platforms for volunteer opportunities,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCompleted Reflection Journal; Personal Advocacy Plan\",\"Week 17\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Project Presentation and Course Synthesis,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nPresent a comprehensive and well-articulated community project proposal or actual project output (if applicable); Synthesize all key learnings and skills acquired throughout the NSTP CWTS program; Demonstrate readiness for responsible and effective community engagement.,, Assessment: ONSITE: Final Community Project Proposal Defense\\/Presentation; Oral Examination\\/Synthesis of Course Learnings OFFSITE: Finalized Community Project Proposal Document (incorporating feedback); Comprehensive Portfolio of all NSTP outputs,, Activities: ON-SITE: Formal Project Presentations with Q&A session; Peer and Instructor Evaluation of projects; Course Wrap-up and Feedback Session OFF-SITE: Review of all course materials and outputs; Preparation for final presentation and defense; Self-assessment of overall learning outcomes,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nProject proposal rubrics; Presentation guidelines; All previous course materials; Feedback forms; Projector; Whiteboard\\/Marker,, Output Materials:\\r\\nFinal Community Project Proposal Document; Project Presentation; Comprehensive NSTP Portfolio\",\"Week 18\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nFinal Exam\"}',NULL,3,NULL,NULL,'The Civic Welfare Training Service (CWTS) of the National Service Training Program (NSTP) is designed to encourage the improvement of the general welfare and the betterment of life\r\nof community members or the enhancement of its facilities, especially those devoted to improving health, education, safety, livelihood, environment, entrepreneurship, recreation, moral, patriotism,\r\nand nationalism of the citizenry, and other social welfare services. The CWTS Curricular Program consists of lecture and participatory discussion, team-building and bonding activities that are\r\ndesigned to highlight values and skills formation, especially that of teamwork, leadership, communication and risk-taking in the context of Community Organization and Development, management,\r\nEmpowerment, and Social Mobilization.','[{\"pilo\":\"understand the basic concepts across the domains of knowledge;\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"apply the different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative, artistic and scientific, textual and visual, experimental, observation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically. Personal and Civic Responsibilities\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"develop self-assuredness in knowing and being Filipino;\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"pilo\":\"reflect on moral norms\\/imperatives as they affect individuals and society;\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"understand and respect for human rights; and\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"contribute personally and meaningfully to the country\\u2019s development.\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"work effectively in a group;\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"pilo\":\"manage and handle problem-solving (include real- world problems); and\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"pilo\":\"demonstrate basic world-related skills and knowledge.\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"}]','[{\"cilo\":\"NSTP \\u2013CWTS\\/LTS Curricular Program\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Self-Awareness and Self-Management\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Moral Values and Values Development\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"P\"},{\"cilo\":\"Leaders and Leadership\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"Conduct Of Off-Campus Activities\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"L\"},{\"cilo\":\"Good Citizenship Values\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"O\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Team Building for Youth Organization\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Decision Making\",\"ctpss\":\"O\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Disaster Management\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Drug Abuse, Alcoholism and Cigarette Smoking\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"First Aid\",\"ctpss\":\"P\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"P\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Social Mobilization\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"L\",\"epp\":\"L\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Recreational Activities\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Entrepreneurship\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"},{\"cilo\":\"Peace Education\",\"ctpss\":\"L\",\"ecc\":\"P\",\"epp\":\"O\",\"glc\":\"O\"}]','General Education Program aims to:\r\nIntellectual Competencies\r\n1. understand the basic concepts across the domains of knowledge;\r\n2. demonstrate critical, analytical, and creative thinking; and\r\n3. apply the different analytical modes (quantitative and qualitative, artistic and scientific, textual and visual, experimental, observation, etc.) in tackling problems methodically.\r\nPersonal and Civic Responsibilities\r\n1. develop self-assuredness in knowing and being Filipino;\r\n2. reflect on moral norms/imperatives as they affect individuals and society;\r\n3. understand and respect for human rights; and\r\n4. contribute personally and meaningfully to the country’s development.\r\nPractical Skills\r\n1. work effectively in a group;\r\n2. manage and handle problem-solving (include real-world problems); and\r\n3. demonstrate basic world-related skills and knowledge.','At the end of the semester, the students will be able to:\r\nKnowledge\r\n1. recognize the development in the implementation of NSTP and related laws in this course; and\r\n2. analyze the impact of NSTP programs on community development and national progress.\r\nSkills\r\n1. propose activities that can contribute in community building and enhancement; and\r\n2. design and execute a project plan that addresses a specific community need.\r\nValues\r\n1. express ideas about the relation of oneself to the community;\r\n2. display acceptable behavior in participating and communicating with colleagues in planning and organizing community activities; and\r\n3. integrate Filipino culture like Bayanihan in conducting different activities.','At the end of this course, student should be able to:\r\n1. develop an awareness of civic duties, social issues, and their role as responsible citizens in nation-\r\nbuilding;\r\n2. enhance abilities in leadership, teamwork, and collaboration through practical\r\nexercises and group activities;\r\n3. foster an understanding of environmental issues and promote sustainable practices\r\nfor environmental conservation;\r\n4. encourage personal growth, self-discipline, and resilience through challenging experience and structured\r\ntraining; and\r\n5. instill ethical principles, integrity, and respect for diversity, promoting a sense of ethical responsibility in\r\ndecision-making and actions. be','1. Miguel, Cariño (2014), Civic Welfare Training Services (NSTP1), HISGOPHIL Publishing House, Inc.\r\n2. NSTP 1 (LMS), https://bcpedu.elearningcommons.com','1. Smart device with SMS, internet browser, social network, camera, calculator, google: chrome, docs, slides, sheets, meet, Microsoft: word,\r\nexcel, ppt, pdf, MODULES, Learning Management System (LMS) and other applications when needed.\r\n2. Internet connection\r\n3. Network access account\r\n4. Physical storage device or virtual drive.','Student must be able to:\r\n1. complete at least 80% of student participation;\r\n2. demonstrate punctuality according to his/her schedule;\r\n3. accomplish alternative assessment (if needed); and\r\n3.1. when student fail to comply or perform poorly in a major examination and/or non-participation on the off-campus tour because of valid reason e.g., health, force majeure needs\r\nto provide alternative assessment Parallel to the Off-Campus Activity and 90 hours of community service.\r\n4. comply the requirements for the off-campus tour\r\n4.1 PRE\r\n4.1.1. Parents Permit\r\n4.1.2. Students and parents’ orientation\r\n4.1.3. Payment official receipt\r\n4.2. DURING\r\n4.2.1. Water jug\r\n4.2.2. extra t-shirt etc.\r\n4.3. AFTER\r\n4.3.1. Submit Portfolio, Documentation, Reflection, narrative report','Cluster Leader: RENAN B. BARATA\r\nMembers : SHELLA JOY B. BAAYOS\r\nJUSTINE JOY A. VILLARUEL\r\nJAYSON MANLAPAZ','FACULTY MEMBER: RENAN B. BARATA\r\nEMAIL ADDRESS: rb.barata.51893@gmail.com\r\nCONSULTATION HOURS: 6 hours (Monday & Tuesday)\r\nTIME AND VENUE: 12:00 NN – 3:00 PM (NSTP OFFICE @ MV CAMPUS)','RENAN B. BARATA, LPT','MICHAEL L. BERSAMIN, LPT','CHARLIE I. CARIÑO, Ph.D.','2026-02-06 16:50:35','2026-02-06 16:50:35',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
(41,'SINESOS','SINESOSYUDAD SA PELIKULANG  PANLIPUNAN','Minor','General Education','CHED',NULL,NULL,NULL,3,'{\"Week 0\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives, Philosophy and School Organizational Structure School Policies Orientation in Online and Modular Learning System,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\nRecite, internalize and explain the BCP Vision, Mission, Goals, Objectives and Philosophy\\r\\nDeepen knowledge on the school\'s policies, guidelines, rules and regulations.\\r\\nFamiliarize on the new normal system of education through online, modular learning system and Blended Learning Delivery Modality (BLDM),, Assessment: ONSITE: Identify the Vision and Mission statements of BCP.\\r\\nCritically analyze these statements in 500 words, focusing on the following:\\r\\nThe clarity and coherence of the statements.\\r\\nHow these statements reflect the school\'s commitment to education.\\r\\nThe alignment of these statements with the current educational landscape.\\r\\nVerify that the BCP VMGO are align with the school goals thru checklist (PMED tools) OFFSITE: Navigate LMS and know the function of each feature.,, Activities: ON-SITE: Read and internalize the following printed materials for Students and Parents Orientation: OFF-SITE: Presentation and Lecture Discussion (PowerPoint Presentation) of Students and Parents Orientation:,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nInstructional Materials\\r\\nVideo Presentation of BCP Hymn\\r\\nYouTube Video Title: BESTLINK COLLEGE OF THE PHILIPPINES HYMN (BCP hymn)\\r\\nhttps:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NuEYO11Wb4E\\r\\nStudent Hand Book\\r\\nLearning Management System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nCheck alignment report\",\"Week 1\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nBatayang Kaalaman sa Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kahulugan ng Pelikula\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Mga Genre\\r\\nNg Pelikula,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Nasusuri ang isang dokyu-film o freeze story\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Naiisa-isa ang mga uri ng pelikula mula sa powerpoint na napanood o iba pang pahatid pangmadla\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Nagagamit at naisakatuparan ang makrokasanayang panonood,, Assessment: ONSITE: ONSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pakikiisa talakayan\\t\\r\\nsa OFFSITE: OFFSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class.,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pagbuo ng concept map tungkol sa Batayang Kalaaman sa Pelikulang panlipunan\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Basahin at  unawain  ang pagtatalakay sa Modyul 1 \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Pagtukoy sa mga Genre ng pelikula\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Pagbibigay ng pananaw tungkol sa aralin. OFF-SITE: 1. Pagbuo ng concept map tungkol sa Batayang Kalaaman sa Pelikulang panlipunan\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Virtual na pagtuturo (PowerPoint Presentation)\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Panonood ng Video sa Learning Management System (LMS) ng pagtatalakay (Linggo 1).\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Internet Source\\r\\n- Workbook \\r\\n- AI Apps\\/Website: \\r\\n  ChatGPT, \\r\\n  Gemini, etc \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Workbook Answer \\r\\n   (Compiled in \\r\\n   portfolio)\\r\\n- Group Presentation \\r\\n   (Rubric)\\r\\n- Quiz Result\\r\\n- Notes\\r\\n- Assignment \\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 2\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nKaligirang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Nakikilala ang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Nabibigyang-katuturan ang mga mahalagang kaganapan sa kasaysayan ng pelikulang pilipino,, Assessment: ONSITE: ONSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pakikiisa talakayan\\t\\r\\nsa\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: OFFSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class.,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pagbabahagi ng karanasan tungkol sa Kaligirang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Basahin at  unawain  ang pagtatalakay sa Modyul 3\\r\\n \\r\\n3. Pagbuo ng Venn Diagram tungkol sa Pelikula Noon at Ngayon\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Pagbibigay ng pananaw tungkol sa aralin. OFF-SITE: 1. Pagbabahagi ng karanasan  tungkol sa Kaligirang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Virtual na pagtuturo (PowerPoint Presentation)\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Panonood ng Video sa Learning Management System (LMS) ng pagtatalakay (Linggo 3).\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Internet Source\\r\\n- Workbook\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Workbook Answer \\r\\n   (Compiled in \\r\\n   portfolio)\\r\\n- Group Presentation \\r\\n  (Rubric)\\r\\n- Quiz Result\\r\\n- Notes\\r\\n- Assignment\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 3\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nKaligirang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Nakikilala ang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Nabibigyang-katuturan ang mga mahalagang kaganapan sa kasaysayan ng pelikulang pilipino\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: ONSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pakikiisa talakayan\\t\\r\\nsa\\r\\n OFFSITE: OFFSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pagbabahagi ng karanasan tungkol sa Kaligirang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Basahin at  unawain  ang pagtatalakay sa Modyul 3\\r\\n \\r\\n3. Pagbuo ng Venn Diagram tungkol sa Pelikula Noon at Ngayon\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Pagbibigay ng pananaw tungkol sa aralin.\\r\\n\\r\\n OFF-SITE: 1. Pagbabahagi ng karanasan  tungkol sa Kaligirang kasaysayan ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Virtual na pagtuturo (PowerPoint Presentation)\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Panonood ng Video sa Learning Management System (LMS) ng pagtatalakay (Linggo 3).\\r\\n,, Learning and Teaching Support Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Learning Plan\\r\\n- Internet Source\\r\\n- Workbook\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Learning \\r\\n  Management \\r\\n  System\\r\\n\\r\\n,, Output Materials:\\r\\nOn-site:\\r\\n- Workbook Answer \\r\\n   (Compiled in \\r\\n   portfolio)\\r\\n- Group Presentation \\r\\n  (Rubric)\\r\\n- Quiz Result\\r\\n- Notes\\r\\n- Assignment\\r\\n\\r\\nOff-site:\\r\\n- Pagsama samahin ang lahat ng na-download na materyales mula sa Learning Management System (LMS) para isama sa iyong subject portfolio.\",\"Week 4\":\"Detailed Lesson Content:\\r\\nMga Dulog sa Pagsusuri ng Pelikulang Panlipunan,, Student Intended Learning Outcomes:\\r\\n1. Maipaliwanag ang piling teorya sa pagsusuri ng pelikulang panlipunan.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Matukoy ang mga \\r\\nPelikulang panlipunan na makabuluhan sa kontekstong Pilipino\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Makapagpahayag ng mga makabuluhang kaisipan hinggil sa kabuluhan sa lipunan ng ga paksang pelikula\\r\\n,, Assessment: ONSITE: ONSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Pakikiisa talakayan\\t\\r\\nsa\\r\\n\\r\\n OFFSITE: OFFSITE: \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Kumpletuhin ang takdang-aralin para sa linggong ito na naka-upload sa iyong Learning Management System (LMS). Kapag natapos, i-download at i-print ang kopya, pagkatapos ay ipasa ito sa susunod na face-to-face class.\\r\\n,, Activities: ON-SITE: 1. Pagbabahagi ng karanasan  tungkol sa panonood ng Pelikulang Pilipino\\r\\n\